content: Best macro-nutrient app for weight loss, training, or general healthier lifestyle. Polished and intuitive interface. I prefer this over my fitness pal as I felt the latter was very clunky with far too many food input options. But just my opinion. I bought the premium version and it was well worth it. It has really helped me reach my health goals and foster a more mindful and sustainable lifestyle balance.

I've used the paid version for a couple of years and it's been great, but the recipe process is very much less so. You must enter your recipes into MyNetDiary so it can calculate nutrition, which is expected, but maintaining your recipes is absolutely frustrating. Recipes can't be updated once you've used them (ingredients, amounts, etc.). You must make a copy of the original recipe / make the changes you need / save the new copy / retire the old recipe / and finally rename the new one with the old name. MyNetDiary is pretty good at importing recipes, but you still have to use a separate recipe app to maintain your recipes. You make your changes in the separate app / copy your updated recipes to MyNetDiary under a new name / and then proceed as outlined above. Having to duplicate recipes in a more capable recipe app and then continually transferring them back to MyNetDiary is starting to become a deal breaker. I would love for this app to manage recipes better. Also, there is no formatting capability in the recipe notes field for simple things like bullets, headings, etc (eg. TinyMCE). This app deserves 5 stars; these devs are smart guys and should be able to figure this out. If these problems get resolved I will come back and update this review.
replyContent: Hello Steve, thank you very much for you thorough review. We will make sure the feedback reaches the devs. Have a great day ahead!

Customer service is also amazing. 10/10 the best nutrition app!

Great Nutrition App It takes some time to figure out navigating the app and customizing your settings, but once you figure it out, there is so much useful information it tells you other than just calories burned and calories consumed. This app is a game changer. You can add foods to thier database by taking pictures of nutrition values of packaged foods and it auto integrates values into app immediately for instant tracking.

All our best in health!

content: I started with Excel to record food intake due to a prediabetes disposition. This is because the app is ad-free and we have a support team to manage the data and help members, but I do appreciate you may not need this. Daisy, Nutracheck Team

content: Great app. helps me keep track of food without being overly complicated. Effective and simple
This is a wonderful app which allows me to Plan my day accordingly and stay on track. Lost 2 lbs first week. I Love It!!!
This app has been very useful but I am now trying to cancel my monthly payments and can't find out how. Not at all helpful
replyContent: Hi Siobhan, I'm sorry you've struggled cancelling. Open the Google Play Store > tap your profile icon (top right) > 'Payments & Subscriptions' > 'Subscriptions'. Or email us at customercare@nutracheck.co.uk and we will get this sorted for you. Hope this helps! Daisy, Nutracheck Team.

content: An excellent App. that I've been using for about 3 years. The Database is quite extensive & is no problem entering personal Foods, Meals, Recipe's etc. Nutritional analysis showing average personal intake over 1 day, 1 week or 1 month instantly shown. The Service Team are second too none, often getting replies long after normal working hours & weekends. Thanks to all at Nutracheck

absolutely fantastic app! I've struggled for years and hated calorie counting and have continued to fall until a friend told me about this app. It takes the horror out watching what you eat and focuses you in a good way. does all the work and ive lost 7lb in the 1st week!! I couldn't recommend trying this app more. try the app, make simple healthy changes and enjoy a new mindset. thank you so much Nutracheck 💕

Although the counting tools are good and the food database, appears to be good. It dosnt allow you to set your own goals, forcing to select from pre-selected nutrition goals, none of which match what I have been set, which totally ruins the app. £35 wasted.
replyContent: Hi Gareth. You can set your own targets in the app if you wish. Tap the blue menu button on your Diary page > 'Nutrient Goals' > 'Set My Own Goal'. If you're having a problem with this, please email us at customercare@nutracheck.co.uk. Hope this helps! Daisy, Nutracheck Team.

content: If you are in the correct head space you need look no further than this app to help you on your journey to weight loss or gain if you need to gain weight. This is a well informed app and I do recommend it to others if they are looking for tools to help them. This app has 5 or so plans you can choose from." If your ready give it a try" I don't think you will be sorry you did...
love this app. helps me stay on track with my weight and be mindful about what I eat. also links to other exercise apps like my fitbit.

Taught me how much I actually need to eat. *update* I started using this app when I did a sports nutrition course during the 1st lockdown. It's a really easy way to keep an eye on calories in and out and the challenges help you focus if you need it. I like the barcode reader and the recipe add. Will continue to use for the foreseeable.
Love it only gave 4 stars because I think it shoukd be available for children aswell. Otherwise spot on so easy and does exactly what you want easy basic and straight to the point
Started off great. Then week later said your membership has expired and need to purchase or carry on with free version but can only enter 6 items.
Such an easy platform to record your calories and exercise. Really great supportive people on there helping you to achieve your goals. Thanks.

I have only been using this for a week and I can honestly say that it's a great app for counting your calories! I don't think I'm prepared to spend £4 a month for it though but I was definitely tempted. It tracks your exercises and steps through Fitbit and other health apps so it seems very accurate!
I'd say a 4.5 because I'd like the option to pay for the app to not have ads. But I love the layout and it's easy to track everything!

Fonts may be great for young eyes....but I found the white font on pink unreadable. I could not find a way to change that setting. And the get started exercising video is just another too long V-shred commercial. I will be uninstalling....mostly for the readability issue.
Easyfit is literally just that. Easy and customizable. Fave macro tracking app I've found

Easy to get started, better than most calorie counter apps I've used in past that want you to purchase after using and not allow you access unless you buy premium. Happy with app so far, can really customize food would like if could add more caloric information like cholesterol and fibre
More food options are needed. The list is basic but otherwise a great app to help monitor exercise, water intake, weight etc

It works well but i wish it had more ways to calculate the calories of food after its prepared. Also a one time purchase option to get rid of ads for life. I hate subscription models except in a video game. I spend so little time inside the app it doesn't make sense to me to pay a sub. Your mileage may vary. Thank you for the app.

I can't seem to delete history and start again, very sad Eta: lost a star for the constant nag screen asking me to rate the app. Careful what you wish for. 1 star now because the w@nkers have started forcing unskippable video adds when you try to add calories. What nob heads!
The format of this app is awesome. The colors and everything about this app is an app that I will recommend to family and friends and will continue to use regularly. Thanks Mario for a great concept.
Does all I want without having to sign up or providing my email address. Ease of use 😌. Now holding myself accountable for caloric intake, and have lost 8 pounds in first week.
It's helping me a lot to mange my losing weight plan❤️ just if add the time to reach goal weight , it's modifying more 😁 But overall it's easy and helpful
Easy to use. Easy to add items. Easy to track food intake. Great for recording my exercise. All round a very good app. Would recommend to anyone 👍

Love the app initially but have had some issues recently. Currently when I add a food in, it adds the previous item, instead of the one I clicked on. So I have to delete the additional food and re-add, which isn't great. Also when I add new food items, it only keeps them for so long and then I have to create it again. Love the fact that you can monitor your weight, exercise, water intake all on one app and set a weight loss target.

Best app for me so far, the best part is...ITS OFFLINE so you can use it whenever wherever which practically makes my life a whole lot easier since I live somewhere with very poor signal. Also, I love being able to add icons and customize food - also create a meal by adding ingredients - background and other colors. All in all ..I LOVE THIS APP and I 1000% recommend for all beginners out there like me...let's keep going....we can do this!

I love 💕💕 this app so much, I just installed the app and I am really happy I did so .... This app is totally free, ♥️and it has all the features you need It counts calories, it track your water intake, it counts your total calories burned.... And so many other features I can't mention I recommend this app for anybody who is trying to loose or gain weight it is really helpful 🤩 It is a one in a million app💎💎 I really appreciate the developers of this app for this amazing job 👍👍😊....

I simply love this app. Has great flexibility for my personal use compared to other apps. I get to enter my own data if i wish. And seeing that cute tank encourages me to eat more and get it filled daily for my weight gain journey

I love how user friendly it is. It is everything I have looked for in a calorie counter app. I have been searching for a while for the perfect, yet simple and straightforward app, and this is it. Thank you for developing it.

One of the best health and fitness app I had been using it for two years And all the information about the macros and calories in the food is completely correct . I recommend this app for you if you are interest in calories and macros calculations . App rating ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐
Good for food journaling, tracking excercise, and weight loss. The best part is it's free 😁
Used on 2 seperate occasions for weight loss. Very user friendly. Tracks weight, water, caloric intake, and everything needed to stick to a diet and exercise routine.
Great app. Using it to gain weight while I lift weights. A little restricted on the food items but if you know your oz and calorie of the item it's easy to add.

I've been using it for a day. It's a straightforward tool that allows me to pay better attention to the foods I'm putting into my body and the exercises I do. My objective is less about weight loss and more about increased conscientiousness of my completely forgotten self-care routine. So far, so good! The ads on the app are also friendly and non-intrusive. I look forward to working with it.

Useful and easy to use. To be honest, before using this app, I couldn't see why loosing weight and getting fit is not happening with all efforts I thought Im putting toward my goal, now I can check my calorie intake and monitor my daily training to see how many calories im burning or taking during a week and change my routine life style to better one... Tnx to the publisher. you've done a great job with this app, especially that the basic and essential options of the app is free. Thank you.
Does not allow you to add all your food at once. You have to keep adding one at a time. Some foods like plain chicken and turkey slices are not on it.
Great app! Takes some playing around with the ounces to hone on the calories that you're trying to input, but it's open format doesn't limit your ability to track your calories.

It is really easy to add and adjust meals, but the ads with blaring sound and the ads that cover the whole app are extremely obnoxious. I have to close out of the app in order to get rid of them. I don't mind the quiet ads at the bottom, but the obnoxious ads seem like they would be problematic if you were in a meeting or a funeral.

Very easy to keep track of, not only your calories, but also protein, carbs and fat. It is also easy to add less usual food that you like. Daily intake estimate is helpful and easily adjusted for your preferences. Keeps track of your exercise times also.
Great App. Easy to use. Just give it a chance. *does have ads that come on every so often, but not annoying at all. I have enjoyed checking my calories/ workouts/and most important Goals.

That's an amazing app, the overall approach is ideal: it has the needed minimum of products data, providing you with great capabilities to create and customize your own products and meals (yeah in free version you might need to watch an Ad to get 6hrs of premium features, that's a great deal!). I tried a dozen of similar apps and that's the only one providing me with everything I need. Also it keeps your privacy: all the data is managed at you local phone, no account needed.

I loved this app for its customizable features. It isn't as good as myfitness pal when it came to logging food but it was good enough to track my macros and calories in more manual way. However it now makes you buy the premium to have customizable features. If it was easier to scan and log food like my fitness pal I would no trouble paying, however, being that the only reason I would pay is the customizable features its just a waste. I may as well use my fitness pal. So disappointing.

Look no further. This app is THE BEST calorie tracker you can get for free. The icons are colourful, you can customize the colours, there are many cultural dishes, you can create your meals from scratch or mix ingredients and since the latest update there's also a search box for all users, absolutely free! So simple & easy to get used to.

The app is easy to use, once you understand how to use it. Its simple and has the information needed except some food items that are not part of the US food customs such as varieties of fish, vegetables and fruits.

I really enjoy all the feature and it is easy to use, the only reason I am giving 4 out of five stars is the exercise list is limited and doesn't calculate calories burned, I have to adjust the time to get it to match or just raw calories burned based off my smart watch. Throughly enjoy the app even tho it's only bee. A week.

Using the app for 4 months. Helpful to track my macros, calories, etc. Some cultural discrepancies (like what is considered a small serving in the US is definitely a large here in the UK). Otherwise great app. However main issue are ads. They used to be max 10 secs long which was fine (it's a free app and the developer needs to make a living somehow) but now they're nearly 1 min long (you can't skip them) AND they automatically play sound (which is not ideal if you're using the app in public).

Fun, easy to use, and the upgrade allows u to search more easily. U can add foods and assign their info. U can also record ur exercise It made me control my food intake specialy after having a kitchen scale to weigh food portions. I love this app 🤩🤩

It is s really good app with nice icons and a good variety of prinstalled meals. A bit problematic is the nonexistence of water as n ingredient for cooked meals. Extremely annoying is the frequency of advertising which continuesly interrupts the app and completely destroys the fun of using it.

This has been great software for keeping track of what I eat (calories, protein, carbs, and fat), how long I’ve exercised during the week, and my weight. I've been using this for 3.5 weeks now, longer than I've ever used calorie counter software food before. I use a combination of preset foods and custom entries to track what I'm eating. (I weigh most of my food.) I exercise with a watch with a heart monitor so I enter the time and calories burned directly instead of using the preset exercise values. Once you get past the minimal learning curve and have entered any custom foods or meals you eat regularly, entering data only takes a few minutes each day. Does this software have all of the bells and whistles that other calorie tracking software has. No. And that is a good thing. All of the data is my phone, not in the cloud. Food information isn’t be stored in the cloud. I don’t have the option to scan bar codes. My data isn’t being sold. I don’t need to login. I can use use it anywhere and everywhere regardless of my data connection. I love it. The free version is supported via adds that generally aren’t annoying, and I could have kept using it happy, but I purchased the pro version of this app because I want to support developers who don't have in app purchases, don’t collect data, and don't require an app to have access to internet to function.

Started out alright, but as with most other free apps, they start spamming you with ads after asking you to review. It forced me to watch an ad every time I added calories and often when just changing menu. I stopped using this app and recommend you don't bother.
Eat what you like, just count the calories and it's working great for me. A little time consuming when you have to add items, like Chinese food or such, but worth it. Keeps me honest. :)

Great wee free app for meal logging, breaking down calories, fat, carbs and protein. Also section for logging exercise to increase calorie allowance. Sometimes glitches when you're logging a new meal and defaults to last item you logged, logging it twice. Also a lot of foods not included in the app (nothing with pastry or Indian in it's name) but very easy to create new foods and I just take nutritional info off another site if I don't have them

i like this app, its easy to use and has a lot of personalisation options. But it lacks a lot of food even some basic ones. Also the live step tracker isnt the best. Its count is off most of the time.

The app is good overall. The only issue is that it doesn't give you the manual entry to decide for yourself how many calories to eat. Instead they put what they believe is "accurate" according to your weight, which is basically insane. I wanted to set the calorie limit to 1500. Instead, the app gave it to 2875. That doesn't help me at all

Excellent app too lose weight. Setting a weight loss goal in the app based upon your individual stats and activity level easy. I especially like the create your own food button. With this you can accurately input calorie and macro nutrient values on the foods you regularly eat. Bottom line. I lost all of the weight I was looking to lose within the time line that I set for myself.

I like the app because I can just add the foods I eat most in the create section. I don't have to put up with thousands of things I don't eat and imput I don't want. No wasting time scrolling through what others eat or many brand names. I like the calorie bank also. I love the raw calorie feature!!!

Great app so far, I really enjoy the feature that allows for you to enter coustom food macros your eating. Great way to not overwhelm the developers with endless food options and track what applies to you.

Easy to follow ,could do with using saturated fat instead of total fat .i would like to be able to key in cals as well food weight.I would have used the step counter but am already using one.I like this app.

Great as starting point! I've never counted calories before but now as I want to lose just a little bit of weight (which is always the hardest), I've decided to try this app. I check the packiging of food I buy now and the preinstalled PCF counting is quite close to reality, so I guess the app can really be trusted. I love the fitness tracker option too; it gives me a rough idea of which exercises to do more of over the week. I will definitely continue using the app in the future! 😍
Overall quite good and easy to use. Database could be a little bit more broad and the calorie database isn't always correct. Other than that, I'm very happy with the app.

The food database isn't extensive enough to warrant making it so difficult to add foods that are not included, which somehow happen to be almost everything I eat. UI could be more intuitive /user friendly. I'll try again after a couple updates because everything else is great.

I find this app to be helpful in my journey towards achieving the perfect weight. It helps me to monitor what I eat. Whatever is not represented in the form of a picture I try not to eat because I want to be able to have accurate readings everytime. I like this app and see myself using it for a very long time.

I have used this app off and on for a few years whenever trying to lose weight. I find it very useful. Although it can be time consuming to add custom food, it keeps you conscientious about what you eat. I do wish there were multiple options for unit measure (grams, tablespoon etc) since I always need to do conversion. I also wish it kept track of fiber I eat daily. I did do some research a few yrs ago and this one I liked best.

Pretty good, great for what I need, which is just simply counting calories. Nothing super crazy, which is great. May not be what all are looking for however, as its very simple. There are ads, but most you can skip right away, or only wait for a couple seconds before skipping, which doesnt bother me.
Easy to use, very functional. Lacks search option in food section. Adding GI besides calories would make it almost perfect.

So far so good. I'm having fun using the app. I love being able to add ethnic dishes and other foods that's not on the app. A few adds now and again but so far I love it. It would be a fantastic app once I start losing the weight 😁

Adds pop-up all the time. There should be a search button to search and add foods that are not listed, together with their calories and other contents, directly from Internet. For the sport activities, it should include short explanation what they are.

The app is mostly useful but some inteface change would be beneficial, for exemple, when you want to add a meal, you cannot directly search for it, you have to go to the correct category and scroll to find it, also you cannot add workout to previous week if you forgot. Also, a home button would be nice and custom workout, like home workout.

I keep coming back to this app. It tremendously helped me lose weight and maintain an active lifestyle before. Now that I'm working on going back to my old lifestyle, I'm relying on it again. I like the new features added too. The interface is very intuitive.

This app is Awesome!!!!! I've tried numerous apps and just didn't prefer an app that required me to have an account. This was even better than I expected. The aesthetics are so smooth. The colors are relaxing. As well, I love the Macros part. Other apps don't really tell you and it wasn't until visually seeing my Macros of how imbalance my diet was . This app literally aligned me with a proper diet and I am grateful. I look forward to my health journey with this app! Much love!
Easy to use with trial and error. Calculates everything but food weight must be added. Love the visuals.

The application is very good, but the reason I gave only four stars is because a lot of stuff like simple ingredients you cannot gind inside,like for example brown sugar or cornstarch. So basically if I want to cook something with something that is not inside I'll be cheating simce I need the ingredients to make that food.

Like this app, using it for 3 days now, easy to use, like that does not transfer data to third parties, and like the pictures, additional feature of cultural dishes... Nice you can also mix ingredients that could easily calculate the nutritional value of your home made dishes... Down fall : no vegan alternatives to meat available.

I think it's amazing and everything so well planned out based on my current weight and how much I went to lose. However, with the search for food to log, I wish there were more options to explore like branded foods and vegetarian options as it seems to lack a tad

Really good, especially for noobs. I love the design and colours! Actually makes the process much less intimidating! Really happy to be able to tailor it to suit me, and see stats at a glance. Thanks so much!

I was looking for a free app to track my calories, workouts and water intake. I found a few that I needed to pay to use. It was like gold when I came across this app. The best by far. Absolutely love it!! Thanks team!
Still using the app. Wondering if there is a version with out adds. Would aslo like the food sections to be searchable. It would also be cool if you could use the app to track your sodium intake.
Great app. I love this. Has a water tracker, was able to add most of the foods I eat and weight loss graph. Easy to use with a lot of great features. Definitely the best app I've found for this.
Really good so far. I like the food icons and meal diary on the app. It has a tracker for how much water you drink too. Helps me stick to macros even when i want to snack on "not so healthy" snacks.

I had to learn how to work this app. This app is off the chain to be free. You can put all your info in. Even if the food not show. It keeps up with everything if u put the info in correct. It goes by week. So all a person have to do is put exercise in as a week and it reset every week that it set for you. Very easy. I love this app and I download all the other apps this one is best

I really would like more food choices that fit american normal food. All the weird food choices don't do any good. They are a waste of space. I get tired of having to make my own food calorie count. More selection would be great.
Decent app. Easy to use and I like that I can add my own foods and recipes to be more accurate. I do wish there was a larger list of foods already in the menu so it was faster to log though.
Latest version very poor, no longer shows value when you select, has some obscure cartoon of bicycle etc. Also adverts very annoying. Latest update is in my opinion a backward step. WHAT A SHAME.
replyContent: Dear Martin, You can still see the values of the current food by entering the weight of the food. Simply go to settings > Design and Features and choose the option to show current food values. If you need more help, please email me from inside the app so I can offer better support than in the review section. Best Regards Mario

content: Was tricky to navigate around the app to begin with. But after 5 minutes of exploring was straightforward to understand. Clear icons, quick to update and great that there is a section to add favorite food items.
replyContent: Dear Rhianon, glad to hear you are enjoying the app and thank you very much for your awesome support and detailed review. If you need assistance in the future, feel free email me directly from within the app. Have a great Weekend Mario

content: Lovely layout. Easy and fun to work with. You can program your own favourite food and even mix and match. Plus the exercise card is great. A fun way to keep track of your calories.

Love it, love it, love it. I can add in food that isn't on the app and I can create a whole meal, when I add the meal it will give me the calories I'm eating...awesome app...makes calorie counting so much easier...also adds in the calories lost with different exercises. It's an amazing app!
Good but not perfect 6 November 2020 Been using this app for over 2 years now, really not happy with the amount of adverts that come up, wasn't this bad !! Going to see what else there is!

This is a great app for keeping track of calories, creating custom foods and meals, tracking water intake every day and more. I have been using it over a year for recording my daily calories and weightloss, it is a fantastic app to have, highly recommend.

Currently using this app and it's very simple to use and not too many ads. It also records exercise and water intake. The only suggestion i can give is that pls allow us to search for the food from a search bar or something.

Handy app. There alot of british foods on it but if you put in your own it is even more pleasant to use. If you are just starting with a diet you will be surprised how much you actually eat to much. All in all a good app.

I am new and I'm having problems with this app already. It's difficult to find my own information I have previously entered. I did not knowingly choose to download the Armour App. I wanted, only, the My Fitness Pal App and I don't know if I got it!

I have only had this app installed for one day so I can't speak to the long term, but so far so good. I particularly like how you can create your own custom food/meal list which makes it quick and easy for meals I make and eat on a regular basis.
The app is really good but a search option for the food items would be very useful & user friendly. Try to add the search option in the food list.

I love this great app. The best app to creat cuatom recipes. It's super easy to use and has a great user interface. The database supports a lot of food and gets bigger and bigger. Personally, I am a friend of having a simple and therefore a more reduced selection compared to a database where you need to much time to find the right food. The only thing what I am missing is a bar code scanner or similar which can create my custom food and auromatically fill in my macro nutrition.

Simple to use, the interface is beautiful - love the wave function and the colour options. Calories burned from exercise are recorded separately from calories ingested (in other apps the burned calories are deducted from ingested calories, making it difficult to know how many calories one has eaten overall). My only quibble is that on inputting food, the search functionality sometimes brings up random food items instead of the one you actually clicked on, accidentally inputting the wrong food.

I like this app and has been easy for me to use. I also have the ability to create my own meals since most of my meals I make it home, it is hard to find an app that has exactly what I need. Whereas this app I can actually build the foods and then save them as my custom foods. This app is also great for tracking exercising and water intake.

I saw good efforts have been put in the app , but still too complicated for busy people like me who can't spend more than few minutes to enter data and see results. The app is great for those who can spend long time scrolling through the food and exercise lists. Thanks for the developers but can't use their app.
The user interface is very easy to understand! :) It has a lot of options (even games!) The colors and animation are also very attractive. Love this app so far!

Sometimes when I add a product and press the picture it appears that an app mistakenly adds the last used product not selected by me. I'm upset, otherwise it was a good app. Developer, where are you, do you still maintain it??? I would love to buy a pro version if it wouldn't have such ugly bugs!

Love this app! Easy to use and keep track of my calories with a large amount of foods to pick from. This has been so helpful as I document foods while I've been working out as well as schedule foods that have affected other health issues.

I use the app daily and it still a great app but the app glitches out at times and then produces the wrong calorie count which throw a monkey wrench in your progress----wow such a good concept but when the app does the wrong count on the calories the app becomes pointless....emailed the makers but they did not respond yet.

Only app that's helped me count calories longer than a few days. I'm 6 weeks in now (counting daily) and it's got everything I need, including statistics for calories and macros. Only thing that could be improved would be the possibility to add quantity variations for the same recipe, as I might cook the same recipe with different ingredient quantities, changing the calorie count appropriately. Doesn't deserve to have only 4 stars for this though. Great app overall.

Really simplifies the process of tracking calories and keeping a check on the macros. Having water consumption, exercise time,calories,weight all in one app is so convenient. Will definitely recommend this app.
Very useful. You can do a follow up on calories, water, exercise and weight. It has graphs on carbs, fat and protein. A particular food database and themes!

So much easier to use than other highly rated calorie counters. Others say they are free, but all the best features are only available by purchasing the upgrade. This app delivers what it said it would.

I love this app, it's easy to use, and has helped a lot staying on track with your goals. I don't find a lot of the pre-defined foods, to be that useful, cause i don't really know what the lasagna they used, was like; maybe more cheese, maybe less, etc, but at least it's generic estimate, if you eat out, and can't count calories. But for stuff like bananas, well a banana is a banana. So i mostly just make custom foods, from label of stuff i buy.
I love this app, you can track your cal, macros, water intake, measurements and it has statistics for all of the above. I just love it!

Works well for tracking progress and counting calories. The ads are annoying, almost every time you enter raw calories, BUT I'm not paying to get rid of them. 5 stars because it does what I need, for free.
Best calorie counting app I've used by far. It's simple, easy to use, and has everything I want without making everything over complicated. I love this app and would highly recommend.
I'm very excited. This app has all the tools to help me loss my weight and get healthier. Considering the Corvid-19 pandemic with ones being without work. This free app is just what I needed.

Overall this is a really good and helpful (free!) app for tracking exercise, calories, water intake etc. I really appreciate being able to add custom food! I hope that different foods and types of exercise keep getting added! For example I'd like to see HIIT and run/walk intervals and barre (I don't think these are in the app but i could be mistaken) There does seem to be a little glitch where i'll go to add a food to my wave and it will add a different food instead! But overall I'm really happy
it's good but the list of foods/ingredients could be extended. It could have an option for changing one's preferred target balance of protein/carbs/fat.

Really colorful and customizable. Helps suggest portion sizes when logging food and exercise intensity when logging workouts. I love it! Some ads show up after a week of use but they aren't annoying like many other apps :) would definitely recommend using 👌

Extremely glitchy. The pedometer app does not sync with this app even though this app suggest using. This app also has advertisements after just about every other click, and most recently opened an ad that wouldn't let me exit out of the screen.

I would recommend it since it is a free app. There are a lot of foods that food servings and their calorie value not listed properly. For example, a cup of cooked rice listed as 7.07 oz, but after a simple search online I found that there are only 4 oz of cooked rice fits in a cup. So, if something doesn't look right, check it additionally. The calorie value in this case went from 555 to 395. This app has an ability to frustrate you and make you give up on calorie counting. So, be careful.
replyContent: Dear Natalia, a cup of cooked rice contains 6.5 - 7.2 oz, depending on type/cup/water. Its always best to weigh the food to get the most accurate calorie calculation. The options in the app like "cup", "serving" are great assistance but they don't replace the accuracy of weighing the food. Contact me from within app if you need more help. Cheers

content: Would be great to add more basic foods in the mix for people who cook from scratch. Having said that, I'm finding it really useful and it's easy to add your own foods to mix into recipes.
I love it. Guides me from A to Z, and has a variety of options. Easier to navigate through the search option where you simply type the food you want to input. 10 🌟

It is working for 7-8 months, then crashed... I have played this game twice. Even the backup cannot recover the data for your "custom foods" and daily kcall statistic. Otherwise, it is easy to work with, simple and clear for all you have to track.

Really like this app, especially compared to others out there. So easy to use, cool interface, has most food items(only critism is that they have not been categorised well) and can add missing foods in "create food". Quite accurate, plans your calorie consumption and length of diet, tracks progress towards goals, water consumption and even has a cute memory game to curb cravings. Quite addictive . Vegan/vegetarian friendly
For a fre app it's ok. Could have more food options to count the calories. Unable to view previous days food eaten. It's helpful to get started but will require a more in-depth app eventually.
Its great, the only thing better would be a link to food they dont have on the app so I dont have to search for it on my own. BUT they allow you to add food once you do find it.

I love that it sets your weight loss goal, water intake and exercise tracking, but it has several flaws. Some calories are wrong they are showing more than what they really are. Some foods are hard to find because the pictures are weird. Maybe if they could add a bar to type in the food so it would pop up faster instead of having to scroll through a bunch of pictures till you find what you're looking for. Sometimes I eat half of a fruit but it doesnt give you the option. It starts at 1

I love being able to customize the color theme in this app. I also like that it works offline/no Internet connection needed. I plan on trying the companion app to track my steps. I am glad I do not need to subscribe to anything to use this app. I wish it had a support group of some kind but I can find such a group on Facebook. I plan on telling all my friends about this helpful app. I am grateful for it. I will upgrade from Free to Premium version to give credit to the developer. 👏💜

I love it so much! Perfect apk *But when i add new food , it would be better if i can add more options when i use it next time like ( half cup , 1 cup .. ) or ( 1tsp , 1 tbsp .. ) *Also when i don't have much calories to use , it would be much better if there's suggested food .. like if i have ( 200 ) what can i eat ? Then i can get list for food which has ( 200 ) calories or less .. THANK YOU!!♥️
Just downloaded. So far, amazing. Love the pictures to enter food. Very easy to add custom foods / protein shakes as well. As I use it more will provide additional feedback. Thanks!

Couldnt Start. During the initial setup process, I was asked if I wanted metric or imperial units. I chose imperial but was then asked how many cm I am tall. There was an imperial option but it wouldnt switch. When I tried to back out the app refused to let me. I hqve to forcr quit the app. Back in the junk drawer with this app.
Easy usable. Few times experienced a bug when you're adding a product to daily meal, app added last viewed product instead of one which is open right now. Needs to check what is added.

One of the best app I have ever used and I would like to recommend to all those ppl who are working hard for their dream body. This app gives complete stats about ur daily calorie intake, tracks ur progress and ensures that u get ur dream body. These app developers are so generous(the app is completely free)(O_O)

I love this app. It's very intuitive, easy to use and absolutely beautiful. The only reason I don't give it 5 stars is because it would be helpful if there was a search bar for food instead of just categories to browse through, and also sometimes when adding a new food to the day it will duplicate whatever was added previously instead. Otherwise this app is perfect. I just got a Fitbit and I'm keeping this for tracking and just transferring the numbers because I love it so much.

It is my first time using a calorie counter. This one is easy enough but it is a bit finicky - has to be if say you need to put in a meal that is traditional, but once you get used to it, it is great.
It is free. Little to no advertising. A lot of good information. Reminders are helpful and not too annoying. Easy inputs and data.
Great app, best I've ever used! The negative, seems very American regarding certain foods and drinks, you can manually put your own in though. No cup of tea option 😊
Great app, some times it adds a different food than the one i pressed which is annoying but just have to look carefully at my food list and double check its correct. Other than that i love this app
I'd give it five stars if not for the advertisments. They do not appear very often though. I like the ability to create your own meals and the basic calorie numbers for foid on the app seem legit.

I like the app. It gave me an opportunity to track (not in scientific detail-too much work!) my calorie intake; which was over what I needed to shed some weight. Simple and effective for me...could be for you as well. Stay well.

Really wanted to give 5 star,but couldn’t. The whole process of this app really awesome, but some important food items are not here.As example -jackfruit. It is a very important fruit. I think more food items should be add.Otherwise, the whole thing is just👍

Sooooo good. You can find almost every food item and even make up your own dish and calculate calories and nutrients. Though i hope you guys add more items to the list for eg. i can't find Brown Sugar, Brown Bread (though a lot of other breads are present in the list so kudos for that) . Keep up the good work !!!
So far I like this app. It allows me to track my calories, and exercise. Plus manage calories based on macros. User friendly and free app!
Great app. User friendly. Accurate. Downside is no iCloud for your data so you'd have to start afresh when you switch devices.

I've only used it for a week, but even though there are no physical changes yet I have felt great from knowing that I'm eating healthier. I often don't stick to exercises or diets for more than 2-3 days. However, this app has me going on through this week and I have no signs of slowing down.

I really like this app, it has helped me keep tracking of what I eat and drink and exercise. I'm still on my first week but I can already see that I'll use it for a very long time and I feel it is working already! My only problem is thats I can't find some food easily, there is not a search bar I have to go through all the food to find what I want. But there is the most used food category which helps since I pretty much eat the same stuff all the time.

Still getting used to this - it has been less than a week. I think it is very good. I will be extactic if it helps me get fit and healthy. It keeps an eye on me, so as long as I enter the information (foods and water etc) the rest is easy - done for me. Could you put a link to specific foods - until I get used to where items are (ie I know coffee is in drinks, but if I didn't, it would be good to type 'coffee' and go to it.) I like the adding foods section and that new added items stay.

I like the app, especially the graphics and the custom feature. The custom food has fat-carb-calorie-protien count -so any type of food plan can be tracked from keto to plant protein. I am counting calories. I was suprised how many calories were in an avacado. A guacamole salad with 3 avacados will cost 1000 calories. The carrot button has way more cals than a carrot though. The prefabs are higher than other sources. I double check online and customize for more accuracy.

I have been only using the app for a day it.is pretty good fully free it gives me reminders I can log my meals my daily exercise and my weight goals. I definitely recommend. Mend this app the only thing tat should change is that there are so many different features and some are a bit confusing but really good app. Super happy😀😀😀😄😄

I wish if you had more cake options. like sponge cake, vanilla cake, red velvet, cupcakes etc cause I like sweats and I find it difficult to manually add everything I don't find in the app despite it being a common food. I really love the application ❤ I like that it has cultural dishes. I recommended it to my friends thanks for your effort.

New to app. Frustrating. Food selection small. Hard to find items even close to what I am trying to find. Measurements are not accurate. When I put in 185 pounds I don't want to see 183.... Something. This makes me question the accuracy of the whole app.

The calorie count seems way off. I said I had a large bowl of cereal and it said that would be around 2,000 kcals. I find that hard to believe that a large bowl of cereal could be all your calories for the day!?! I also couldn't find any food search feature and therefore had to poke around categories for something like Guacamole that I couldn't find. I don't know if I'm doing something wrong, but it doesn't seem to work well.
Really love this app. Helps to keep track with a calorie deficit. Some food is limited but if you want to be more specific you can create your own.

I have seen such great results using this app. The macros, for the most part, are on point. It's a little cumbersome to begin with because you have to edit all your own stuff and I'm unsure why they can't just take the grams entered for fat, carbs, and protein and calculate the calories for you, but you get used to it. I think one way to improve the app even more would be to have a scanner button that scans the nutrition label and automatically adds the serving size to your custom food.
Easy to use, great graphics. Tested a few similar apps and this one is hassle free no need to deal with creating an account that will send you tons of pestering emails. This one is Zen clean and fun.

Have been using for about 35 days. Leeks instead of spring onions, cabbage as a whole rather than a portion, you do have to be a bit careful before pressing add to wave regarding the portions. The search option appears to be removed? That was useful rather than searching through all the categories, but otherwise its workable and is OK.
So far so good like the many food sources and built in calories count. Easy to use. Author needs to learn the difference between a kCal and a calorie though.

Seems to work very well. I really like the mix ingredients part because all you have to do is click the icon and the ingredients are listed so you can repeat the same recipe everytime. Lost 4.3 pounds in 2.5 weeks. Slow and steady!
Good, wish you could adjust items already programmed in. Most of items I have inputted myself,which is fine. Overall good app, keeps you on track.

I rarely make reviews but this is a really well thought out, simple, and nice looking app to track calories but unfortunatly Its glitchy at this moment and doesnt calculate food properly. I keep tried to add 1 egg and it's doubling the calories for a quantity of 1. There appears to be a glitch with the exercise graph tracker, the first time I used the app and it is showing me data from week 25 ? Wouldn't I be on week 1 if I jut started using it? This app has a lot of potential though.

Great app. It's hard to make new foods cause ya Neeed to find out how much calories n grams n all. Another reason is that can you add more indian food. Cause here we don't eat much of what's in there so we just have to add rice instead of some. Would rate it 5 stars if you do that. Keep it up👍

[Day 1 - Five Stars]: Good looking app. Easy to use. Lots of food options. "Create your own food" option integrates really well with the rest. [Day 2 - Three Stars]: Pretty damn glitchy. Continuously recategorizes, reidentifies, and miscalculates my selections and/or macros hours after I put them in. Will adjust my rating if they fix the glitch, because otherwise I really liked this one.

Great looking. Like the way you can customise. Only just started to use but would I imagine once added all foods you usually eat it will be a great way to track calorie intake and exercise. Plus it's free! Win win

Quite good one for a free app, I would just enjoy if ingredients would be searchable and if there would be a description for some of the meals as some are to general (e.g.:fruit smoothie). Otherwise lovely and customisable design!
The themes are pretty, the food list is extensive, the app is very customizable. I have lost 10kg in 6 months using the app to help me keep a diversified and enjoyable diet.
The best calorie counter app that I've ever used. Definitely a 5 star rating! Simple to use, very discreet ads, and straight to the point. It's also highly customizable. Very satisfied!
replyContent:
Very happy to hear that dear Ishak and than you for the awesome support and detailed 5 star review :)
If you need any help in the future or have ideas and feedback, contact me any time from within the app (Settings > Contact). 
Wish you further success on your journey.

Best Regards
Mario

content: Great option for calorie counting. Like how you can add you own calories (written on back of packaging) instead of having to look up everything you ate each time. Was using a different app before this is much better for monitoring my intake of calories and water.

Hey Mario, good job on the app. All apps I have tried had pros and cons, including yours. At first, I wanted to give you 4- 4 1/2, but as people like to complain, even on free apps, I decided this app deserved a 5. Your app is user friendly, comes with extra free features such as the water tracker and the streak which you don't get in other apps. The only thing I've seen in other apps that was not in yours is the ability to search brands or even scan bar codes. Small detail... Good job 👍

Easy, smooth interface. All the features are accessible for free. I can create customised food. Bonus points for cultural food category. Love their data & privacy sensitivity. Wholeheartedly recommend this app for health & well being w/o sacrificing online safety. No data mining or unnecessary permissions. There are ad intervals but I'm ok with that as devs & artists gotta get paid and they sure did a stellar job with this app. Request: daily energy input/output tracker.
Really easy to use and follow. Great for keeping track of my eating habits! Only criticism is the food list. A lot of UK popular foods aren't listed so you have to try and find a close alternative.

I won't give it only 1 star because it's not buggy and can work well if you are dedicated to typing in your own food. The design is visually appealing and easy to understand. The problem is the built-in food list. If you get lucky and find the food you want, the values are all wrong! For example, 30% cream is not 800 calories per 100g. Searching "milk" I never even found normal 3.2% full fat milk. You're better off just keeping track with a pencil. It's easier.

I tried a bunch of different free apps to track my eating, and this was the one I liked the best. UI takes some getting used to, but it was really easy to add in the meals I am eating regularly. It would be nice though if you could change the unit of measurement for each meal from oz to serving, or something similar
The app is very nice and easy to use for those that are lazy , like me, to check labels. Although being more diverse in the meals included. I am not a dietician but i highly recommend it
So far so good. Easy to use. Maybe add functionality of being able to add accurate calorie loss for exercising.

This is just the app I needed. It lists how many calories you can burn with almost every fitness activity you can think of, and tracks the number of calories you've gained with all foods and meals. As you go on through your day, it also lets you know how many calories you have left to consume. It's also free!!! Thank you Calorie Counter!!!! :D

So far I haven't had issues with the app. It's pretty cool in keeping track of daily caloric, carb, protein and fat intake. Most common food are available. The custom option may be inaccurate, especially if the food is homemade but it's not really an issue. Pretty easy to use and good enough for beginners in the calorie control journey.

this app is actually amazing. it has all these customizable features and is really easy to use. no glitches or anything. It gives you a variety of foods to choose from to count calories, has workouts, and gives you a plan on basically how many calories to eat and how much you need to burn... it even has a game in case you're thinking of eating junk food. PLEASE (and I cannot stress enough) PLEASE get this app it is so worth it
User friendly and intuitive application. Rich content, variety of customizing features and nice graphical presentation make it easy to use an very helpful. Thanks

Hey guys. What's up!!! Hope things get better as soon as days have been pasted. I wanna thanks for the great app which I eventually found on Google ▶ 🏬 😃. This app is really good and useful for those who may need to count on how much calorie wanna take and how to make the journey of your losing weight get easier, it definetly makes your lifestyle is getting better and in better progression than ever.
Been using the app for a week and I really like it. Some foods aren't on there but it allows you to add the foods on with they're nutrition content👍.

Very nice useful app, easy to program and manage our meals, specially in busy days where the time to think about meals is less. This application can give an idea about our intake, carbs, proteins, fats etc any time we want. If we cross the limit, we can manage day after 💪 🌟 🌟 🌟 🌟 🌟

This is a great app. There is no need to enter personal info or create yet another account. It is easy to use you track caloric intake, protein, carbs and fat intake to help you make better choices. It also tracks exercise and water intake. It keeps a history to see your progress and keep you accountable to yourself. It has a nice interface. It is free due to ads, but they are not too intrusive in my opinion. I highly recommend this app if you need to lose weight or improve your diet.

Just started using. Quite a good app. I like picking the food from the pics. Although I think it overestimates the calories in some fruit and veg. Need to use it a bit longer to give a clearer picture.
Love this app! I love the search button for foods, and that you can add your own in if you want. It's been really helpful with keeping me on track!
Love it. Really useful. Could have the option of customizing existing choises a bit more, especially with the exercise, as things are sometimes different around the world.

I have honestly downloaded 3-4 such apps n deleted, I am from the people who get demotivated easily with thr complication but this one is quite easy and understandable. Though there is an option where you can add the fruit or vegetable or anything that isint in the option and add the calorie breakdown I would still suggest to add the options of seeds like flax n chia seeds etc. Overall I love it so far.

I think this app is great! There are so many aspects of the app that can help you track yourself in both food and activity. Plus, you can put in your own food it's not on there to choose (but they have so many that are).

Things can be hard to find however there is a handy search tab. The aims created by the app itself are easily manageable and so far working for me. Its always difficult to make something so personal as a diet and fitness plan but this app seems a great aid to start with. And I enjoy the sence of achievement one gains in getting it all balanced right.

It has been very useful and helpful on my weightloss journey! I love that you can add your own mix of foods and keep them on hand, so if you always have a certain breakfast you can just add it instead of finding ingredient by ingredient everyday.
It's actually a decent application. Because majority of the features that the other application are giving on a paid membership, this one provides for free. I like the UI aswell and its easy to use.

Simple and easy to use with a beautiful, customizable interface. Much faster, less bloated and more enjoyable to use compared to similar apps such as MyFitnessPal. I really appreciate not having to sign up for an account, and I love how easy it is to add custom foods. Great app!
The app works perfectly fine, and it's completely free. Learn to use it's basic features before giving it a low score, just because y'alls can't read.
Love it. You can create your own meals with optional nutrition facts, it tracks water intake, exersise, and weight. It makes dieting so much easier. Satisfactory automation also.

This app has been brilliant. Very easy to use, clear interface. I don't spend hours navigating it. I like the exercise function is based in time and effort rather then KMS/reps (which gets messy). The app has kept me on track for 4 weeks and I've lost 6.5 kgs. Very happy! Thank you!
Pretty good and easy to use. Very easy for beginners to get started. I wish there was options to enter food amount in as cups and table spoons instead of ounces.

OK but ads became really intrusive. Edited to add that developer contacted me but issue remains so have stopped using. Found another that's also organised more logically for me and that includes UK foods.

I downloaded this app few days ago, and it's been awesome. It has made life really easy. Now I am able to make healthy choices and know exactly my calorie intake. I also like that there are cultural dishes that apply to other nationalities, even though they are few. I believe you guys can do better. That being said, it's a really good app.

Tldr: Had no issues at all. This is my first time tracking calories and so far I'm loving the app. You have search button there, so every ingredient is nice and easy to find and if I could not find an item, there is an option to create your own from scratch and add it to the list (uptil now had to do it only once). Very noice.

I give it 5 stars cos it is the best I have come across with. In the meals section,it has foods stuffs I never imagined it would have.it even has some cultural dishes which I have been seartfor and it facilitates me inputting my meals. I recommend adding more cultural and African related food stuffs though,just to make things more easier for us. But all thesame I love it. Great job

Seriving sizes of almost all foods are astronomically high. For example this app considers a 1/2 cup of dry cheerios to weigh 125g when a 1 cup actually weighs about 27g. Calories are almost always double or triple what they should be if you don't customize serving sizes. This app also encouraged me to eat 700 cals less than my doctor has confirmed is safe for weight loss. Would not recommend this app to anyone.

This app is amazing, there are all types of food and you can add your own, there is also all types of exercise, it is just perfect. there is also water quantity, and people from 14 years old can do it, even pregnant women...

You can add custom foods and nutrition facts so you can learn to balance your caloric intake without making drastic changes to how you eat (within reason of course), narrowing the margin for frustrating guesswork. Overall, seems a good choice for people trying to take weight loss seriously!
Functional and useful for my needs. Tracking exercise and calories. I tend to just do raw calories rather than finding the food in the app though.

This app has been so easy to use, and after just a few days I'm already noticing my habits and being healthier. The interface is great, the whole experience is just very positive and I appreciate the thoughtful nature of the app. Where lots of fitness apps are aggressive about their goals, this one is just very health positive and doesn't want to lecture you on what's best for you, but rather support the attainment of healthy habits.

This app is amazing and olso free. Not only that it counts the daily calories but olso it makes me more aware of what I eat. It olso helps me see how many calories I've burned daily. I only wish there would be olso exercises included which I know there are, I mean more complex Still I am very happy with this app.

So far it is working well. There are a few things I would like to be able to do. I would like more options to customize the exercise feature. It has helped me lose 6 lbs in the first week. I like that you track your water consumption it really makes a diffrence in how I feel.

Not a bad app. Counting calories in general is quite a complex thing to do, and it means always having a scale around. But this app "averages" the weights of each food/drink for you, which is nice. For a first timer, I think it's cool. Helps me keep track of my meals.

This app actually good. I can keep tracking my calories everyday. But unfortunately the reason why i gave 4 stars for this app is there is no variety of foods such as "stim fish", "Lime juices" and others. But ITS OKAY. I still can search it from google and i added the calories from google to this app. It just took time to check my calories everyday with many kind of food in my country. So overall this app still usefull BUT STILL NEED MORE UPDATES FOR FOODS AND EXERCISES .
It's a good app that's easy to use but the list of food is small which makes it more tedious cause I need to google and create food first. Other than that it's very helpful.
First app that actually helped me lose weight. The control menu and trackers are a bit hard to understand, but it's easy to get used to.

Piece of $#*! I could NEVER get the stupid thing to go back to the main screen!!! No swiping left swiping right tapping the screen up down no back button nothing I could never get back to the main screen once I touched an icon!!! I really wanted this app but totally frustrated! Please somebody tell me how to navigate this stupid app. I actually really want it still 😠
This is a really good app, it helps so much with keeping track of my calorie and water intake as well as my daily exercise schedule..

Loveley display. I spend a lot of time calculating or inputting the macro breakdown of certain recipes, to make it as exact as possible but once that's done and I get a feel for it, it'll become a lot easier. It's fun to use and I just figured out I can adjust my personal makro breakdown to start following a lower carb diet. Love it!

This App has really helped me in controlling my calorie intake. In the space of a week, I have already lost close to 2kg. I competed the health info with other sources and it is all comparable. Obviously, there are numerous foods that aren't pre-loaded. All I do is read & input the info on any packaging. It is then there forever. Whilst my diet is varied, it's not too much work. The benefit being that it is there for all time. Highly recommended 👍👍

I think the App is great if you can't find some type of food there is a create your own and you only don't once and its saved!! There is a water monitor part and a fitness part. It holds on to your goals and show stats! For a free app I couldn't imagine any better!

Great look and super easy to use. Love that I can track calories in, out and water. Nice it has a huge inventory of activities /exercises. Wish the food inventory was a little more extensive, but nice I can add my own...when I can remember too 04-05-20 Still love this app and ease of use. Tracking everyday and helping me keep honest with myself.

I was looking for a new app to keep track of what I eat to lose weight. It looks like a great app I love the way it is set up however the way you put in food you eat I feel should be improved a lot. Most apps have a scanner on food to scan and even if not you can find something like a peanut butter and jelly sandwich very easy on here I had a heck of a time figuring it out and wound up uninstalling simply because I still don't understand.
Lost a lot of weight as a college student, now I'm using this app to get back up to a healthy weight, awesome experience. Really helps make sure I'm eating enough throughout the day.

I tried several calorie counters. This one is the best. No registration, no need to go create profile, no ads(!), minimalistic and intuitive interface, very fast, good for battery and for weak devices. This application has huge database of products and it's very easy to add your own products and even complex dishes. It is even possible to scan a product bar code with phone camera. I used this application for a couple of days and bought a pro version without hesitation.
When searching online products, it will only show the ones that start with the search term, instead of displaying all the products that contain it
While I have found this app to be very good and does exactly what I need, I am removing it as I do not wish to have a Russian app on my cell phone.
Best calorie counter ever. Lost 6 kg already. 💪
I have lost 44kg. And this app helped Me a lot.
Diabetic not helpful
It made me weigh my egg.
It has everything I wanted
-19 kg after 4 month of using
The best app
Where did statistics export disappear?
The best!!! I gonna pass to iphone and I'm afraid, because Applestore doesn't have it.
LIMITED use in free version. only discovered after some time
It's a fantastic app. But. -1 star, because everyone can add their own dishes to "free to use/free to found". Maybe all food should be checked.
Without paying you can only view the last seven days of information you put in, and won't let you put in foods that are not already in their database (and there are a lot of foods missing).
Does a lot more than the other apps
Great app! BTW is there some privacy poly and list of data collected and transmitted by Hiki counter app?
Just want calorie counter! Can't find it anywhere
Frustrating
To hard to use. Not in english. Must weigh food. Dosnt lable increments, example oz. I can look up "baked potato" faster in Google and get the information. Sad really bad!

I love how much info this gives and how much I can keep track of all for free! However, as an American my foods are not labeled in grams. If this app ever adds support for cups, ounces, tablespoons, teaspoons, etc. It will become the best calorie tracker by far!! Currently I have to convert every single thing I add to grams which just isn't worth it since other apps exist.

Great, except won't let you add your own foods correctly to the database. It tries to calculate PFC per food serving, whatever that means, but it won't allow you to enter your own numbers and doesn't recognize my protein powder. I eat that every day, and an app that won't count my protein powder is not going to count my calorie intake accurately. Very disappointing, because everything else is great. Will tell you exactly how much you need to eat each day to gain the right amount of weight.
Works but not easy to use

Most food items are in Chinese. When adding an egg to my menu, it can only calculate calories and protein if I add in the weight of the egg in grams. I don't have time to weight all my foods in grams.

This app is just incredible ! Finally i can see what was wrong in my nutrition before . Extremely easy to use, huge food data base in different languages , and yeah I'm loosing weight easily without suffering . Thank you guys for creating of a such great app
Probably a great app in Russia, not USA
No data to add food. Not enough English Base. Hard to use.
Love this app!I have been used Hiki calculator for two years everyday. I have diabetes and for me it is the most convinient app to calculate carbs and fat. Thank you.
Would have liked to try this but food log was presented in cyrillic alphabet. No place to convert to English. Loser app.
It is an amazing app , I am using it's free version since years. Excellent work by developer.
Can't get it to describe it in inches , feet,or ounces , don't want an extra step to convert kilos and mm ,,,
It's ok. Unfortunately there's a limit to the different kinds of food you can enter in the free version so it becomes useless in about two days unless you want to buy pro.
Just what you need to control your weight
Went to put in food that i ate in the search and it's in a different language other than English.
Awesome app. So handy and does all the work for you. You just put food you take. Great. Thank you guys
Brilliant, very user friendly, easy to navigate & helpful.
What a blackmail. It is wonderful at first, until it will not let you add any foods unless you pay!!!! 🤦🏻‍♀️

I don't usually leave reviews, but here I want to thank the entire team for this app. I feel motivated, the app helps me a lot. It's my first week of usage, and it feels good. I'm also grateful for the database containing most of foods I can imagine, and I also can search for them in three languages I use, finding foods from different countries. Thank you!
This is an AMAZING App I love this It helped me a lot!
Top app, just what I needed in an app. Will be good to add glycemic load.
Easy and useful
Great and simple app
Just amazing. It's so simple to log your meals

Superb app: very customizable and easy to use! Many competitors overcomplicate their products' functionality or struggle to implement even basic features in a user-friendly way, while this one just does what it should do, and does it well.
Super app! Easy to use.
it will be awesome if you have this app also for iPhone, I loved it when I had an Android phone.
Love this app, will recommend to my friends
Cool app
Well done. It's really good.
Easy to use. Great help with weight loose.
Jumps straight into premium to force us to spend money.. Rubbish App.
replyContent: Если вы не готовы тратить деньги можно пользоваться бесплатной версией. В ней достаточно продуктов для контроля за питанием.

content: It is a good app but most of the products that I consume is not on it.
This app does work and I like it. It's very useful for counting calories and pro version isn't expensive
Great and easy to use, thanks
Everything is fine, but the design could be a bit better. Thank you for the app😊
Best way to lose weight is to count calories
