I find this app helpful, on my Keto wellness plan, Virta. Being able to sync to my Fitbit to eat more if I'm active and less calories if less active. Have lost 16 lbs in 60 days while capturing all the sodium, fats, carbs, and protein in all my meals and snacks.

Good app, Fair enough if you not willing to pay for pro u get basic service but still ok. If u willing to pay u get more benefits from nutrition, doctor and meal plan etc. Suggestions 1. please add various meals from the country that we lived by Indenticate with input our contry. 2. Please add calories for recipes from other users so when we recook the recipe we know the calories in that menu, make it easy for us to input in our Diary. Overall i am enjoy using this app
Lovin this app! I can keep track of calories, macros, and sodium intake! The app is easy to use and there are a variety of diet preferences to choose from. Highly recommend!

would rate it 5 stars if i could actually logged in 😅 i have tried several times. entering my desired weight, current, height etc. but when i put my gmail, it always says "unable to save. please try again later" i even deleted and installed it again but it still didnt work! please give a solution
I love this app so much. it has helped me to exactly know how much calories that I have taken everytime I eat my meals or snacks. Thanks so much.
Good app, but water tracking should be included in the free version. Also maby foods are not in the database.
Enjoy using the app to track my meals. Wide variety available and bar code scanner very useful.
Very clear information No need to worry about weight. It tells about complete diet and calories. Easy to identify energy consumption and expenditure.

I have used this app since 2013 on and off. The first time I used it to track my food and lost 50 lbs. I also use it to track me weight through the years. I don't actually use the social part of it. Although some times I will read through the comments and look at the pictures if I am looking for inspiration.
Excellent. Been using PC version. First time on Mobile today. So far, it's great! Wish I could load the premium edition on my laptop
Love the app. SA'n foods are easy to track. I have a question, could you guys perhaps build in an fasting tracker as well? That would be great.

I've been using this app on and off for a few years, steadily since about March. Seems some of the old bugs have been worked out since my last review. This app has definitely helped me lose weight. I do my best to stick with 1400 calories a day. Then my fitness tracker lets me know when I've burned the 1900 calories that allows me to lose a pound a week. If I fudge on my calories, I make sure I still burn 500 calories over what I took in 🙂 More to say, but out of space 😅

Been using for a couple of weeks. Worked great for the first little while but now the reports feature (which was the best feature) isn't coming up. I've contacted for help via the app. They replied the 1st time but it's been almost a week since they said to uninstall & re-install ( I even restarted my phone), told them so...& I'm still waiting for a reply. Getting frustrated this isn't working - I liked seeing what I'm tracking -seeing as there's so much effort in putting all that data in.

Please add the following features: - Adding the time when logging food you've eaten. - Seeing the calories burned in the daily / weekly reports. - More activity types for the calories burned section. - Being able to add calories without creating recipes.

This app has so many features on it. It is so easy to use and I am finally loosing weight. I didn't realize how many calories were in some of the foods that I ate. I will be using this app for a long time. I love it.
Great app. But can't get anyone to respond to a "contact us" request. Complete radio silence. Used this app before, can't reset password and there is zero assistance.

Very clunky UI, no way to enter calories directly. Didn't have even the most basic features I need, which is simply entering food, calculating calories or entering them directly for the food. I couldn't even do that.
Really such a great app to keep track! Amazing how many items it has in the scanning sections so trusting its all accurate

This app has helped me to see my pattern of eating. Very user friendly and forgiving to editing any profile goal (weight, calorie intake, diary). Would recommend to beginner life change person needing an easy app to navigate dieting journey.
This app is really so good for calories counting. I wish I'd had it's full subscription so i could be more happy with this

Easy to use, clear dashboard, huge library of foods, products relevant to my country (RSA), free if you want the basic package, no invasive advertising, community board to post your comments or get support, working really well so far thank you!

I don't have much experience with these kinds of apps, but I do not miss anything, and it's extremely intuitive to use. I just started my personal mission but already what shocked me the most is some hidden calories in little snacks or drinks. It's actually crazy, this is free and very low ad-impact.
Brilliant app! So simple to use.....and it works! Ive tried every diet in the book apart from Calorie Counting.... wish I had done it years ago!

I'm type 1 diabetic. It helps me figure out how many carbs I'm eating, so I know how much insulin to give. Before I started using it I was all over the charts. Now my sugars are under control and I've even lost 11lbs, in the last 2 weeks. It also help you watch what you eat since your keeping track of how bad or how much eat.

Effective and comprehensive. A few hiccups: for instance, if you are inputting your food for the day and need to add one that isn't already there, you have to finalize (check mark) what you already added or it disappears and you have to input it again. Also, an optional "final weight" input for recipes (that anyone could input on any recipe after making it) would be a great add-on as it would allow for easier portioning by weight instead of eyeballing it (or keeping that info in my notes app).
So easy to use and so exciting to see that you had a good day of healthy choices. Encourages you to exercise more!!! Love this app !!! Best app ever!!!
Great helps me keep my with my food journal and calories consumed. Inspiration from other folks and receipe ideas. I really appreciate all the help.

Free Macro counter! Love a good calorie counter where I can track weight and my macros!! Sometimes some food aren't listed so I have to add them, but a fairly good selection. I wish the water tracking was free, but otherwise, I'm happy to use this app daily. Ads are there.

Amazing app for counting calories. You can choose from the large database of foods. It even has most foods specific to my country. You can also edit any of the foods if they are outdated or incorrect. Amazing.
Best tool I have ever used to keep me on my 1200 cal/day diet. Have plateaued at -50 lb +/- 3lb and holding. Maintains my focus and is easy to use.
So many useful tools on this app to aid weight loss and really easy to use. Lots of good meal ideas too.
Update: this app is my favorite tracker. I suggested somethings in 2019, and they have actually improved.. I have since recommended this app to friends, family, and patients alike. Strong work
replyContent:
Hey X,

Thanks for the updated review and appreciate the feedback. If there's anything else that you see that could do with improvement please reach out.

Kind regards,
Lenny

content: Love, love, love. I love how all I need to do is take a picture or scan a barcode and instant the calories I consume are counter and tells me how much I need to consume for the day. Plus has meal plans. Tracks the calories you burn as well. I love this app but I don't understand why I need pay a premium price to track the water I consumed.

The free part is ok but needs a bar code scanner to make it easier to provide nutritional values. I would expect it has all these features when you buy the premium. I also don' t see the sync with google fit, that must be on the premium package as well. Not sure thought.
Great app for tracking your daily calories intake, food macro info for each meal, weekly weigh loss progress and super easy to use.
Food tracking is easy, app gets better and better. I can input nutrition now too if Bar code can't be found. I lost 10 kilos in 3 months.

Quite decent app, but make sure products macros are okay, because people post inaccurate macros. I would give 5 stars if I could make a list of my favourite products, so I wouldn't have to look them up each time.

This is such an interactive app. From the chat room, to the weight tracking, to the calorie tracker, which, by the way is phenomenal. The size of the data base on types of food, restaurants, and home delivery companys is the largest that I have seen. I am highly recommending this app for assistance in your weight loss efforts.

Being free, this app has been very helpful in my return-to-health journey. I'm actually enjoying weighing and measuring my food, and recording on the app. I'm a 69 years old grandmother and for the first time in many years, I am finally seeing a weight loss. I'm also walking between 3 to 4 km a few times each week. Thanks FatSecret!. You have a weird name.
Wow! I've used this app for years. Using the diary to plan meals and reports to track the most important nutrients. This is great! Thanks 5*

The user experience overall is nice, encouraging me to stay fit; however, there’s a little problem I am now facing, that the nutrition data synced with Google Fit isn’t accurate and appears to be counted repeatedly, which is quite frustrating. Hope the tiny flaw can be fixed.

Easy to use and very functional. I could track everything I needed to track right here. I found out where I was taking in the largest amount of calories and now I pay attention to those foods and make sure not to go overboard. I lost 20lbs a year ago, kept it off, and I'm planning another 10-15 this spring. So much easier with this app.

Needed a calorie counter after my recent type 2 diabetes diagnosis, and the app made it readily apparent that I was eating too much, so it helped me adjust my intake. It's also valuable in sorting my macronutrients, and tracking sugar and fibre. Minor irritants: incorrect or duplicate nutrition labels in the database, not being able to switch from volume to mass measurement for some items. Units also don't indicate Imperial/Metric variations. But otherwise I'm happy with the experience.
So easy and quick to use. Easy to find and input new foods. Gives you great incentive to really calorie count and lose pounds 👍

Great app with nutritional information about a very extensive list of food items. I am on a calorie controlled diet and the app is invaluable in keeping track of what I consume. I've been using the app for 3 months now and have not encountered any problems. I'd like to see two improvements: 1) Always having the option of selecting grams or millilitres when entering the serving size (often there is no choice of ml even if the item is a liquid); 2) Include saturated fat in the daily summary.
Very helpful for us to realise by how much we had been overeating, and to control our portion sizes. I've just over 2 stone in the last 6 months.
This application is not at all user friendly. I have many things to share but those won't fit in less than 500 words. Also the customer service is very very bad. Uninstalling the app right now!
The best food diary and weight diary app out there! Keeps me motivated and easy to see your calories and macros! Thank you to the developers!
I absolutely love this app. It's really helping with meal prep and tracking my progress. I do wish I could connect it to my Garmin watch tho.
Realy quick and easy to use. Finding the right foods, meals, and quantities is made simple. It has kept me on track effortlesly.
I'm happy that I'm able to find most information about various foods, organize and plan meals that I can save and use later.
Loved this app but disappointed to see that the Data from Google fit no longer syncs with the app. It's harder to track my fitness
Very helpful for tracking foods and kearning what is going in my body. Wish it would also help track sugars.

A few small issues like cals rather than kj here and there. I'd like to have my own complete list of foods (favourites) that I can manually enter. You'll find it helpful to toggle between app and website sign in. I'm only using the free basic version which serves my needs for my own personal record keeping. For those that like the community aspect, it appears there is lots of support.
Using the app more then 2 months. Easy to track calories, protein, carbs, fats, fibres. I would like to monitor calcium and other elements as well.
Excellent tool for tracking every part of your diet. Only gave it two stars because the app does not count the salt intake correctly.
Good, useful tool. Just wish I could search the recent food list and go back farther in time.
This is a great app to track your diet and eating habits. It's there to remind me what I ate and also do better at planning my meals.
Easy to use, kept pretty well updated, and most importantly, very helpful. I've lost almost 40 pounds using it.
Easy to use and intuitive too. Great free app that works well and has a pro version for more content and recipes. Love it.

Impressed with this program. Logging weight & food is a + for weight loss. But there is so much more. Exercise/activities logging shows how many calories consumed vs expended. Highly recommend! Try it, you'll like it.
This app it very easy and precise to use for Lose weight and everything else ,But I would like to add exercises and schedules to follow the exercises and to record the weights you lift

I love this app! So many features, it's hard to list. Great food database. Easy to add food, weight and exercise. I have lost 27 pounds using this app, and it takes just a few minutes a day. Love-love-love it!!!!

I am just a new user. Before going premium I did try the free app. I found that it was very easy to post meals, add foods, and monitor nutrients. Right now, I am on the 3 month premium program. If I continue to be satisfied I will go to yearly membership.

I love this app. Scanning food items by bar code is genius. Counting calories makes you hyper aware of what you are putting into your body. There are people from all over the world using this thing. If the premium version had a better user interface and translation API that would be wild. The community behind the simple tracking is what makes this app magic. That is where the value-added skyrockets. Make connecting with others easier and more fluid and if you go public, I'll buy.

I'm not happy with the latest update of Fat Secret. It used to flawlessly integrate with my Diabetes-M app and made it easy to mark things as "favorite" that I ate all the time. I don't have a need for calorie counting etc in FS because I already have that in the Diabetes-M app which I pay for every year. Now, I can't so much as "star" my favorite almond milk in my other app. It says it has to access my FS account (where my favorites are stored), no problem, I say yes. Goes back to the same screen and I click yes again and it closes out what I've entered and pops back to the main entry screen. I realize this problem is an integration problem but I suspect it has something to do with the new premium feature which allows menu building... and "favorites" must count as part of that. If someone has a fix for this, I'd love to hear it because as it stands now, while I appreciate the use of the calorie etc database, Fat Secret is pretty useless in making my life easier as an adjunct app for controlling my diabetes.

Easy to use, large data on food groups and super helpful in disciplining calorie intake. Highly recommended to understand your eating habits and making ammendments to achieve any weight loss, healthy eating goals.

Easy to understand and keep track. First app I've had the patience to stick with, helped me keep track super well, lost roughly 60 lbs in just under a yr. I haven't tried the premium personally because you already get so much on the free version.
It would be nice to have suggestive foods to even out the macros and micros inputed throughout the day so we can balance out and hit the goal at the end of the day.

This app makes it EXTREMELY EASY to record EVERYTHING you eat on a daily basis. Since I'm counting calories to lose weight, it makes it fun to track, that is unless you keep going over your recommended suggested calorie count! I've used this on numerous occasions.
Settings show you can connect with your Fitbit. I have that selected and nothing happens. No sync whatsoever.

I love this FatSecret App. I really learned a lot about what worked for me and what didn't by having a space and place to self-analyze my life-style habits. On occasion, it might remind me once to log at least my dinner but that was it then nothing the next day. If I got too busy, NO pushy constant bombarding of messages. Also, this app helped me become aware of my caloric intake and portions.
Very intuitive, app has just about all the features I need even though I am only using the free version. (Out of work for 9 months so I can't afford to pay attention lol)
This is an amazing app with so many amazing features!!!! You can even share your content with your dietician is a HUGE bonus feature. FatSecret team you are all ROCKSTARS!!!!
Works well. I'd like to see a delete feature on items eaten. Easier to use than the app I was using.
Love this app. It's easy to use. It's actually a pleasure to use. The calorie counter is very comprehensive. It's hard to see how they could improve it.

I love this app!!! It has made it so very easy for me to count my calories for each meal and snacks! I've lost 10lbs. in 2.5 weeks - this app is keeping me on track! It is incredibly user friendly and intuitive to use - and even allows for you to enter foods that may not be in the database - but that is rare a thousands of foods are in database. I am following the DASH diet and this app also keeps track of fat, sodium, carbs, protein, sugar, etc. Thank you for this wonderful app!!
Easy to use. It has almost everything in the food database to track your diet. And it's free to use the basics. Great app.
Quite easy, fancy and useful. You can add any information and people will benefit.

Very user-friendly app. Easy to use and easy to add your own foods that aren't already on the list. I enjoy being able to see the percentages of protein, etc. I'm eating and adjust my meals accordingly.

Incredible and comprehesive application. I've lost 10kgs in the 2 months I've started using it. Love the micros and the fact that it empowers me to know what exactly I'm consuming. Can't out-train a bad diet, and the app takes the guessing out of food for one. I'm also pretty sure that I have not discovered the application's full functionality ito is utility on my war on weight yet, but I'm looking forward to the continued journey of discovery. ADDING massage roller methods might b good 2.

Excellent, EXCELLENT resource to track calories & progress. It helps one make better choices & even choose the brands that suit us best for our weightloss goals. You can even enter brands & product categories -along with their nutritional info- that may no be on the incredibly VAST list of products. You'll not only be helping yourself, but also countless others by showing them even more healthy food options.
Very good. Helping me lose weight and cholesterol by monitoring my intake. Only hick is not always synchronizing with Fitbit. Often have to unlink then link again.

I love this app! It's so easy to use and the nutrition content search is the best part! There's so many brand name and pre-existing entries...Also, being able to share my progress (or not) with a community of other people with the same struggles is just awesome.

This is the best app! Keeps track of calories but also nutritional value, exercise, and water. The best part is once you enter your food, and the things mentioned above, ther next day youcan see it again in "recent" and you can just choose it again without having to input everything. Works everytime. This is how I maintain. Once I stop inputting what I eat everyday is when weight is gained. As long as you keep track you can see what how much you've eaten, calories, carbs, cholesterol, etc.

I couldn't lose weight before, it turns out it was because I didn't calculate calories. This app is very useful for calculating calories. Now, I can lose weight and I'm very happy. Thanks for this app. 🥺❤

Love that I can choose to keep my information offline. Easy to track foods. Great to scan packages. Got a message saying they will be making changes, NOT happy about that. App is good as is and they should quit messing with things that work well. Really hoping they don't ruin it.

I only have the free version, but it is user-friendly and links with my Samsung health so I don't have to manually record my walks if I wear my Samsung watch! The easy barcode reader feature is great for accurate calorie counting also.
I was trying to lose weight, when I entered my weight in the app forced me to change my goal, pissed me off.
Great app - easy to use, helpful tips and a wide range of recipes available.
It's better than some but doesn't have the information that others have. Unless you pay for an upgrade. Pay here or watch tons of ads with others. Depends on what you are willing to do.
Just What I Wanted It's simple and easy to use. I just wanted a way to record what I eat and that's what the free app does. I can also save all the foods I use the most.

I am still new to this app, so I'm still in the investigation process. What I have found so far is cool. The basic app, before you buy into the paid app, seems to be easy to operate. It has a great food selection with sku identification, making my tracking easier. I really appreciate the quick fill as I tend to have the same breakfast or lunch a couple of days in a row. I can customize my dietary needs for the Mediterranean vs. Keto diets which is key.
Free version doesn't let you change or adjust the daily calories number despite stating so on the setup. Instantly uninstalled.
It could use a dark mode, but besides that I wouldn't change a thing. It's made tracking my habits easier for me.

Really good app I lost 28 pounds so far and the cool thing is I'm losing weight slowly which is good and it's changed my eating habits, also it synchronises with Google fit for exercise progress. I'm using the free version so give it a go got nothing to lose. 🙂

Just paid for the 3 month subscription. Not what I was looking for. Wish there was more here for people who are looking to follow expert meal plans especially for body building. Manually clicking on recepies and not being able to build a grocery list is cumbersome.
I've used this app for years and years. Suddenly you have to pay to change your calorie allowance. How ridiculous.

Not the fun of new update. I can't change proportion of macros in making my kcal goal. I could only do that if I pay for it. I don't mean to be percice about it, but at least to put % as I could do that before. Thanks!

I used Lifesum for approx. 2 years and I was very happy with it. For getting the most accurate result, Lifesum can be synchronised with your Step Tracker. In addition to counting calories, you could fill in your weight and body measurements and it will show you a graph with your progress. Unfortunately after the newest update, the only thing you can do is literally just counting calories. All the features that made Lifesum better than the other apps, are now only for premium members. A pity.
After the latest update..., can no longer adjust calories. It's ridiculous that it's part of the "premium" plan. Please fix
replyContent:
We deeply apologize for the issue. 

The responsible teams have worked hard on a solution and the app is now back to normal. We are working on preventative measures to avoid further incidents of this kind.

If you should still experience any issue, please contact us through Settings/Support in the app with more details. 

Thank you!

content: Works well for tracking everything, no problems so far. Minus one star for the constant popups in premium.

10 out of 10 app. Easy to use, great recipes and only 5$ for premium to unlock other things. The lite version is still good though. I recommend this app if you want to track your calorie intake, carbs, protein etc. So much you can do on this app. Very satisfied and glad I found it.

Only started using this app a few days ago but find it extremely user-friendly - which makes it easier for me to stay on track. Definitely recommend to anyone looking for an easy way to track calories. I'm only using the (free) basic program but Lifesum's premier program is actually reasonably priced, too. Great app!
It's pitiful to see that even Setting the calorie goal has become a premium Feature. Have been using it for years now, but have to change due to their poor premium policy.
Love the scanner. Quick and easy I can set up my meals for the next day and can edit and add food very easy !
I used to love this app, but now I wanted to up my calorie content because I exercise more and I can't. Instead, it took 300 calories off. That's insane

I love this app! Super user friendly, so effortless to track macros and keep my nutritional goals on track. I was looking for an app that I could put in my own daily caloric goal and macros. I had paid for a professional to calculate my calories and macros based on my body and fitness goals. Most apps don't let you adjust their calculated/ recommended calories and macros so I was thrilled to have found Lifesum!
It's a good app but I just really wish I could choose my target calories for the day. I used to be able to but they changed it and made many of the features premium

This app is very similar to many free apps however they push you to trying 1 month(that is actually a subscription that I am still figuring out how to canel) If yoy want to track calories, exercise, get recipes and waste $12 a month, this is the app for you.

The main reason I paid for the subscription is the life score. The first time you use it, you're asked questions like how many times a week you eat brown bread, to get a baseline score. Then, based on what food you've logged and what habits you've tracked (e.g. water intake) the score is supposed to update on a Monday. For two Mondays in a row now, I'm being asked to take the test again (no special diet or food plan), very dissatisfied.
Great app but its expensive, specially if like me wanted to gain weight; id rather buy foods than subscribe. I hope they also offer a one time premium purchase instead of subscription based. Thanks

It's great. Tracking and adding custom meals and recipes is amazing. Love that it can track my smart watch for easy tracking when I'm active. The only thing I would like to see expanded in the future is the snack tracker with different times of the day.
Very helpful in awareness, quick and user friendly! Losing weight quicker than ever before. Making healthier food choices.
Great app. The only suggestion I would make would be to add a +Drink category. They can be added into other categories, but it would be helpful to have them as an independent option.
The app is amazing! There was barely an ad shown and the app is quite easy to use. It's really helping me when I'm trying to be more healthy and lose weight.

Easy to use but the database is poorly managed (if managed at all) and extremely inaccurate. Scanning in items is right 80% of the time. Much of what you get for the premium price is free with MyFitnessPal. Good first effort but it's not there yet.
I'd like to be able to control the exact caloric goals. Other than that it's really helpful

the thing that truly irritates me is the "add exercise" section being buggy af. it ALWAYS stops working when I try to edit the minutes of each of my exercises. I got premium hoping it'd be fixed, but nope. 😭 otherwise, I like it. it's become somewhat of a game for me and keeps me perfectly in check.
This app is so easy to use. Helps me keep track of calories in as well as calories burned. Love it.

Rubbish. While your scanning the food it, the app closes on you. Also when you do the health test, half way it states error, states to press cancel or ok. No matter how many times you try it shut thr app on you. There was a 1month subscription that has gone. The £4.99 subscription charges £9.99 not £4.99. If you go out the app it wont let you start where you left off from. I will be looking for another app. Personally I used to like this one. Too many issues now from day 1 sadly.
Upgrade to access 16:8 intermittent fasting you said. I did that, but can I find it? NOPE. Please fix that asap No contact about this. No way to track I F. I wish I hadn't upgraded.
Nice UI but you should be able to share meals with friends, ie for couples cooking together, will stick with MFP for now hopefully this will be added in the future

Ive used this app on and off for a few years now, i havent used it recently but have gone to today, i went to change my calorie intake target for the day, and now that cant be done unless ive got a premium account!! I used to be able to do that before without having to pay.. well i wont be paying, i will just work it out as i go along.. bit annoying!!

Love it... This is absolutely worth the subscription which isn't very costly int he first place. The only thing I wish it would have is the ability to sync my fitbit but other than that this is excellent!!!
It really helps me to gain weight i really love all rhe features with the food the work out its a really nice app i am very happy with my progres

I tried the free version for a few days but decided i need to try moor so i subscribe for 3 months to try it out until now its soo good very user friendly and easy to use but it would be nice if you added some more workouts types.
Great app. Can you add health tracking, like blood pressure, pulse, and blood sugar.
It's fairly easy to use and keep up with. Helps you keep motivated to keep going. Keeping track of my calorie intake is helping me a lot.
Love it, so user friendly, gives me all the information I look for. Try it, I recommend it!!!
This app is really great. I love keeping myself accountable. Even if I have a bad eating day, I still make it a point to log my intake.
Super comprehensive food database. I live in the Netherlands and I can use the barcode scanner on pretty much every food I buy. Similar apps only have foods from the USA and UK.

Great app. I love how you can scan products and it automatically puts in the nutritional values. I bought a scale as well so I can better keep track of how much I'm eating. It's been a great experience thus far. I should mention that I have the paid version. (It's worth it)
Pretty good but some things could function better when logging meals and saving your own meals

I have tried to unsubscribe from this app. Apparently once you subscribe they have you trapped forever! It is not listed in my Google Play subscriptions, but they charge me every month! Don't use this app!
Very easy to use. Very helpful while trying to loose or maintain your weight. Would recommend to all.
It's pretty good but you can't delete the recipes you make, so it gets pretty cluttered.

There is a very frustrating process you have to do sometimes to get your exercise from other apps to sync properly because it glitches out so often. Otherwise I love the app but please fix this! Edit: they have fixed the glitch so my review is now 5 stars. I really love the app and have been using it for years now. Thanks for fixing it!

The only complaint i have work the app is I would love to input the macros and product info for something you may not have in the database so that i can accurately track because i love overseas and whole most things are in the like 85% even here in Italy, i would love to be able to make my food tracking even more complete, even if i have to do a bit of the leg work
Easy way to count calories. Has made me think twice now about eating things I don't really need..

Pros: connects to Samsung health. Cons: constantly having to submit corrections for macros bc of incorrect info. Ive received error messages that foods can't be found in database and I'll have to manually enter. Users can't add friends or follow others. Inability to customize daily meals. Ex. Adding snack 1 and snack 2, etc. Doesnt have copy and paste options to easily add foods to another day or meal. Inability to customize water settings without using app presets. Wish I could get refund.
Great app, my partner has diabetes and this app has helped us both keep track of our food intake. Large library of food brands and nutrition info. Love it
I love that keeps everything in check in one app. It helps me be a little more responsible for what I eat and how much water I take in.
Why change the manual calories setting into a premium setting? Try fixing the constant crashing of the application instead of Making previously free functions paid.....

Honestly, this is the best wellness application I have downloaded. It measured my calorie and fluid intake plus it displayed the calories that I've burnt after exercising. It truly served its purpose in monitoring your well-being. I will continue using this app for it helped me in my weight loss journey. Thank you Lifesum!
Used to be so much better, but now everything is on premium! You need premium to adjust your calories! Ridiculous. The only thing going is that the food diary is still the best.

Fantastic app. Even better I now have premium. Unfortunately my only complaint is some items I scan the macros and calories are out. Also some barcodes once scanned show a completely different item. All that aside I love the smiley faces it shows me for my food choices. This is the main reason I choose this over any other calorie tracking app.

It's helped me loss weight and gain weight that best part is the tracking with steps and exercise I honestly use dumb bell for almost every entry then minus about 30 mins for resting in-between,also being able to adjust macronutrients is amazing especially adjusting your carbs to fat when gaining weight. I really wish there was dark mode though please add that thank you

I used to love Lifesum. Now it is trying to squeeze money out of anything. Before you didn't have to PAY(!?) to adjust your daily calorie intake. My calorie intake is set so low from when I was younger, now I'm using the app again I adjust my current weight and I get a health warning that I "need to set a higher calorie intake". The "reset to default" button only resets it to my teenage weight. How broken. What was a health tool is now just a daily reminder of my weight gain.

Good app.. would have given 5 stars if the app would allow me to use my own bbq recipe.. in another recipe instead of breaking down all the ingredients myself and adding them in. Seems like an easy thing for them to do.

Used to be good, but over time the greedy devs are moving even basic features like setting your own calorie goals or combining food to preset meals behind premium subscriptions. Avoid and look for better alternatives unless you're ready to be milked to hell and back.

Super intuitive interface. I was having trouble figuring out MyFitnessPal. This app is such wow! Thanks for making it! *Update: After using this app for a couple months, I'd like to point some flaws that I've noticed. First, the app will often randomly add/remove bottles of water when opening/closing the app. Second, the scan feature isn't always accurate. Third the calories seem incorrect at times. I.e. what is listed in the app doesn't match the nutrition facts on the item.
the free version is about useless. can't do much with the app. I understand some features must be payed, but this is ridiculous. don't even bother if you're not willing to pay 👎
Basic features which used to be free are being moved behind a paywall. Scanning foods often brings up the wrong item or macros.
It was good on the start when setting calorie goals, until they made it where you have to pay for every little thing with a subscription.
Very easy to use. This is my first time tracking my calories and this app has made it super easy.

I've been using it for a few days now and it's been good. It's simple enough to use and gives you a general idea of calories you're taking in. Some ethnic foods are hard to find but I'm not surprised, that's usually the case. Anyhow, I'm not a big app person so if an app has coming back everyday, then I know it's good. I'm gonna see how long I can use the free version until I feel like the paid version is worth it.
Easy to use, lots of great recipes and a variety of recommended diet plans to suit all.
Lifesum is easy to use and has a large and accurate database of foods. Love that my workouts sync from my Samsung Health app and automatically adjusts my daily calories.

My only complaint is that it doesn't show as many micro nutrients and weekly nutrition info like similar apps, i.e. MyFitnessPal. The comparative cost of a premium membership definitely makes it worth it, though.

Disappointing. Lacks diet plans for specific health needs/conditions like type 2 diabetes, low fibre (IBS), low fat (fatty liver disease), low cholesterol, and more. No mixing of diets like (vegetarian) keto. Uninstalled.
Really easy to use app with everything you could need even just on the basic app but premium also looks really good and helpful and such a cheap price also.
I love how you can scan foods it's so easy. Already rated it. Could the app stop asking me to rate it. I love it. The end haha can't get any better than 5stars ❤️
Great app. Would love to have a feature of custom counters beyond the existing daily water, veggies and weekly fish.
pretty great, a shame that most of the features are for a paid subscription, but the free version gets the job done!
"Healthy eating and diet", yeah that's only if you pay for premium. Otherwise this is only a log book basically. I can do that with the health app that automatically comes with my phone.

I have always had trouble with portion control. When I tried to use a journal I was usually guessing as to how many calories I had eaten. LifeSum takes the guess work out and I love that I can add my own recipes

Good app, needs more food options. Insensitives always help to stay on track. Maybe a option to take photos of progress 🤔. Just something more to keep it interesting would help. Also I upgraded to premium, it was the one that I really connected to.

Great app! The only thing I would like to be improved is the variety of the database. I'm a foreign user, so there are many foods from my country that do not even exist in Lifesum (for the most part). Other than that, the app is easy and appealing to use, offers a ton of useful info and does it's job peefectly!

This app is great for keeping track of what you consume on the regular. It has allowed me to see just how much junk food i consume, and find the patterns in my diet over the day that i need to change. My Only problem is the way the wster intake is measured in cups or bottles with weird amounts but whatever.
Good, but except for tracking food literally everything is premium now, can't even see my caloric intake overview of the past week.
It's alright, but like all other calorie apps it mostly has the calorie info on branded foods and that's just inconvinient for foreigners like me

I like it for the design and feel when tracking meals, it's really nice to use. The pricing is great compared to its competitors. The recipes are nice, but sometimes make no sense (a snack recipe that gives 15 servings of 150kcal each, a dinner recipe marked as 19,000 kcal). What would be useful is if I could choose a set of recipes and plan for myself. Say, pick just 3 dinners and 1 snack (same snack for 3 days), choose how many portions for each, and get a plan and shopping list for that.

Very useful. The fact that you can scan a barcode en the item is recognized is pretty cool. Imagine if the meal library could become so comprehensive that it could include foods and meal names from different cultures that are not so popular. The exercise tab is kind of strange. It does not confirm that an exercise has been added to the log for me.

Its very hard to find a diet or meal tracking app that helps when you're trying to gain weight rather than lose, but I was excited when I found this app. Its database is extensive and it's also easy to quick add calories when you have a snack. Very user friendly and a blessing no matter which side of the weight spectrum you are. Being underweight, overweight, or just trying to stay a healthy weight, I recommend this app for everyone. I'd give it 10 stars if I could, it's amazing.

It's a handy app with many recipes. Mainly enjoying the Vegan week feature with shopping list. Although sometimes it doesn't register meals correctly. Like twice the calories instead of once. Also would be nice if the other plans had the shopping list and pre-listed meals so you don't have to search. Or month planning instead of only a week. Option needed to convert veggie recipes to vegan. But so far really liking the recipes and they're easy to stick to.

A friend recommended this program so I foolishly jumped in with both feet. Too many negatives to list. Adding a food near impossible and otherwise problematic. The quick add feature allows you to add calories but no descriptor. You cannot export your data unless you email them to do it for you. Cancelling the program doesn't refund any portion of your subscription fee (which, to be fair, you are warned about but it is still bad business).
Very "needy", annoying and unprofessional notifications all the time. Haven't found a way to directly let it pick recipes or foods *for me*. Otherwise pretty ok.
Helps me better understand my goals and keeps me on track on my food. I love the overall design of the app and watching the water bottles fill up is satisfying 😌

Barcode scanner calories are consistently wrong. Most of the time the calorie and macros would be off for any food I scanned in. I like the app a lot but I have now switched to another app that has the correct foods in their database.

I would have once given this app 5 stars but after a recent update basic features have become locked behind a costly subscription. Features such as manually adjusting overall calories and including burned calories. Bit of a shame the developers got greedy since I did enjoy using this app :(

I downloaded and installed this app in two day. The nutrition facts are a mix of incorrect and partially incorrect. I tried to input the correct information for the nutrition facts but it is telling me it is inaccurate. This app caused me more stress on this healthy eating journey. And I will not have it distract me from my goals because of it's lack of proper information. I'm done with this app, I will stick to pen and paper.
I like it so far. One thing I have issue with is the fact that my fitbit app doesn't connect to it. However, I have a feeling that it might be an issue on Fitbit's side.

It's fairly good app. I have paid version. It could have percentages of cards, protein and fats for the diet. The app is good start for getting into dieting. However, it is based upon the belief that burning more calories and eating less, losses more weight. For most people, gaining muscle will lose fat better thus the approach is all wrong. The app misleads you to think that cycling and walking burns more calories thus allows you to eat more. This approach made me put on weight.

This app is not worth it. Find an alternative. Food database has a lot of errors and customer service is not very responsive. Attempt made to correct errors and app would accept corrections. I think there are better apps out there for less money. As a premium subscriber, I am very disappointed.

Nice interface but not a functional app 1. Adding your own meals doesn't work. I keep getting an error saying that the macro distribution is inaccurate for literally everything I input. Validated this against online calculators 2. Doesn't connect with Garmin. like??? One of the largest fitness tracking brands, if not the largest 3. Poor experience with customer service - dismissive and condescending 4. Claims to partner with Gympass, I've been trying to pair the account for weeks. See #3

I'm really satisfied with this app and this is just with the basic version. Will consider paying soon because I really like the clean UI, simple illustrations and easy tracking. It syncs well with my Samsung Health app. Unlocking meal plans is hidden behind paywall but I'm good with the free features. Like that I can track how many calories burnt in a day and how many more I need to eat. The tips and notifications are very useful too. Most importantly, no ads. I would recommend this!

Lifesum is simply an awesome app that helps me to live a more health way of life. Since using it I feel a million times better. I'm on chemotherapy and even the side affects of the treatment seems less burdensome. Thank you lifesum.

Easy, Accurate, Fun and Motivational. I was sceptical about the benefit of a tracking app. Glad I pushed through and made Lifesum part of my life, it's made a real difference and helped me achieve a number of my goals. With better linking to my other apps, laptop syncronisation and a possible lifetime membership option it would be a must have app.

Recent update ruined it. used to love lifesum for tracking, as it has nicest UI. the premium seemed to focus on meal plans and recipes which was fine, I'm not about that. I did really love the feature to save my own custom meals though, super useful. now that's gated that create meal feature behind a paywall now so I have to track each individual ingredient. sad, I really enjoyed lifesum, but I will be switching away
Easy to use, lots of nutrition information on all types of foods, easy calorie tracker, water intake tracker, lots of food recipes. Overall i really enjoy this app.
Great app. I like to add my own meals and food, that way I have the accuracy I need for tracking all my calories and nutrients.
Good app even without the premium features, I like that it remembers the foods I've eaten making it easier to plug in my information as the app becomes more familiar with my diet.
I love this app it really helps me keep track of what I'm eating. Iv lost 9 pound in 4 weeks.

The app itself is great. Very easy to use, cute interface. HOWEVER I don't really like how it's been evolving since when I first started using it. More and more features are becoming accessible to paying users only, and honestly, now that you can't edit the calorie intake anymore, I'm likely to stop using it. I understand taking away body measurements but when it comes to essential things...nope, I don't really like where this is going.

Im easily able to stick to the program. It shows all the calories one eats or drinks and tells you how much you can eat till you reach your daily calorie intake. It also adds your exercise and amount of burnt calories, so you always know where you re at! Alreadyost 2 kilos of my 5 kg goal, in a week! Really live this app

App is realy helping me in tracking my calories. Just one thing I feel is missing: the option to automatically carry carlories over to the next day, for example: 200 extra calories allowed on Friday if you were 200 calories under on Thursday.

Love the app. Used to use myfittness pal. It was a little bit of a change and took some time to get used too (not as many people use the app so the information available is less than my fitness pal). But the price for the premium version is SO much better and I could not recommend more.

I ended up getting premium, which has been helpful to transfer my exercise from the Fitbit app directly to this app. My biggest complaint, which makes the app useless really, is that the nutrition information is not accurate. I'm doing keto and will scan something that has 2 carbs, but then the percentage will say "85% carbs" and the stats are then wayyy off, making it look like I'm failing at my diet. It's just not accurate.

Like....OMGZ!!! To quote the LifeSum rep: "Oh.......NOs!?!" So yeah, Tried this "free" app to test & after latest update, stupid app crashes when opened. Glad I never sunk any funds into this glitterturd.

It wont let me buy Premium Ive tried for days to get it, but it only gives error, right now the last paynent look like it registered in my bank account but is pending( Only when i chose the 12 month plan go figure) but it has not updated in app yet. Its a good app I've used it before but its not really that good without the Premium. I know its not on my side the issue is because ive purchased things in other apps with the same paynent method recently.

Great app, I really like. Really easy to use and is great at helping me track my calories and exercise. Lots of recipes to choose from and there is an extensive bank of food items. I have never had trouble scanning or searching for an item when I'm making up my own recipes.
Really good app. Makes me aware of my calorie intake, therefore I know when my daily limit is getting close. As a result, this has been the most successful weight loss I've managed for some time!

Just started my weight loss journey after over a 4 year hiatus. It took some determination to stay on track but once I made my mind up it became enjoyable. This app had assisted me in this process. It's extras to help inform you on diet and nutrition. Very informative. I know nothing about this stuff. I'm just determined to lose weight.

The app is quite good. The experience is satisfactory, and it deliveries what it was initially proposal. The only negative point so far is that there's no way of adding extra meal to the diary, forcing you distribute everything in four main meals, which is kind of disappointing
Update: so disappointed that you now have to pay to adjust the calories. The count they have given me is way too high.
I like that the paid app has lots of customization and that it is aesthetically pleasing. I think it's still too expensive though.

I used this app for years and loved it. They have changed so that the abilities to change calories intake is locked unless you buy the premium version. That is really frustrating and I am now looking for a different app to use. Also the calorie intake they give me is too high. I don't know how they calculate it.

This has been okay for me. I've always struggled losing weight. I struggle with an eating disorder I always overeat or not eat at all. I don't recommend if you are like this aswell as it took a low turn for me
So far so good.This app works for me.Easy to use. Good info and options,plans.See the results in a year.

So far so good. I figured let me try the premium and I'm making sure to log everything I eat, I also leave a margin for error as sometimes it's hard to know exactly what size or portions you are eating, but other than that I'm giving 5 🌟
It's got a nice calorie tracking but when I try to track my exercise it's a bit tricky not very accurate.
I don't understand how it works. What does it mean "track" a meal? It seems like I cannot make a list of recipes and have a list of ingredients for shopping.

Great Interface - Inconsistent Data After a few days tracking my strick post-op diet with the free version, I was very happy with how easy it was to use. Then I paid for access to the nutritional details to see how I was doing and compare it to my own pencil -and-paper tally. Wow, were they off by a mile! * Carbs were counted as fiber * Serving sizes were way off * Protine was hit or miss. Worsenyet, I can't edit existing records nor make.ky own.
The app works well, however there are too many incorrect entries for some food items, so I end up needing to report incorrect information quite often.

Does the basic job but too many things now locked behind a pay wall, including the basic option to change your daily calorie goal. Having used the paid subscription in the past I just don't feel it's worth the cost, especially when other apps offer more for free. Will return to previously used apps.
replyContent: Thank you very much for your feedback! Please feel free to leave suggestions for improvement on UserVoice: https://lifesum.uservoice.com - our team is regularly browsing through the information there to make sure we are aware of the different demands. Best regards!

content: Not a bad app but I just did an update and the app kept crashing. I tried reinstalling my phone several times and finally had to unistall to use it again.
Have always loved this app, keep coming back to it. But more and more features are becoming premium. And now I cant even change my daily calories....

I dislike the newest update with one of the main problems is changing the Calorie count. For one, I can't change the goal to what I believe fits my lifestyle without paying.... Secondly, the deficiets the app is giving now is what was on quote "too low" or unhealthy. Which is it? I used to like this app, even with amount of foods where the scan results and macros being Way Off/Inaccurate.
Calorie counting made easy. The only improvement I would suggest is a desktop site to make planning ahead more efficient.
App is easy to use and very direct with what you can do to help weight loss progress easier. Very simple yet very informative
Easy to use, functions well. I can track everything I want in one place, very useful app.

Love how it tracks nutrients. Would love to see more exercises added, like aqua walking by distance and time. Also--some way to visually mark which entries in the database are official calorie/ nutrient counts for foods. There are way too many erroneous entries that come up in a food search, and it isn't immediately clear that these entries were added by users.

Used to be incredible but has recently changed so you need to pay for most basic features, including adjusting your daily calorie goal, which was the main reason for using this app as part of ED recovery. Won't be using anymore, they clearly care more for the cashgrab than the users.
I love this app but needs some improvements 1 an easy fasting button and 2 a shopping list with pictures because I haven't heard of half the stuff that's on there
Its pretty good fot tracking caloric intake day by day but could include a long term plan like how to come off the diet succesfull and keep your results
It's okay 😂🤣 offers a lot of content and help without having to make purchases, which is nice I just wish it was more with out the need to subscribe 😔😂

I've been using the app for a few months now and it's been helpful to me as someone trying to gain weight. I find the weight tracker pretty useful and the same goes for the calorie tracker. Unfortunately the latter has now been locked behind a paywall which seems unfair to those of us who can't afford premium. I can understand the recipe section and other bits that give more detailed insight into nutrition and health being locked but this takes it a bit too far.

won't connect to any apps or my fitbit to automatically track exercise. all of my logins are correct, the app just will not connect automatically so I have to do everything manually. loved that feature the most but it doesn't work anymore I guess lmao

So far, it's been a great tool for losing weight. What I'd love to see: When creating my own meals it would be great if I could track how many grams a portion is, instead of having to guess if I'm eating 1 whole portion, or a half. I don't always cook from a recipe so I'm having to guess how many portions my meals make. Edited 2 June I accidentally deleted my first weight entry under body measurements and found out there is no option to add it back. Body measurements are now useless to me.
Lost 10 pounds in one week if you don't have to put alot of effort and you are getting results because this app keeps you on track with a goal weight. Looking forward to reach my goal.

I use the free version and still I can track almost all my calories. It has a huge food library and scanning mode works perfectly. My only problem is water tracking option. Sometimes it shows different amount of water than I entered.
Very good and handy. However, could improve by having more foods already on the app rather than having to input them but that's me being picky.
A good app. Bar codes scanning is not always accurate. Database is also a bit out in some cases. Could do with diabetic recepies and plans.
Best app to track daily water intake and food. UI design looks great and relevant. Easy to use. no issue at all
I've been a paying member for a while and I love this app. I really wish they would bring back the little "perfect" when you hit within a calorie goal but that's my only small nitpick.

There are a lot of recipes to choose from with clear instructions on how to make them. The app is intuitive and has many options. It allows you to measure claorie intake and it also splits the recipes up into breakfast, lunch, dinner, and snacks for you. It measures your water intake too! Perfect for bother beginner vegetarians (like me) and experts alike! 5 stars.
One of the more useful tracking apps I've tried. Covers meals/food, water intake, and exersize. Gives a weekly update on your progress (or lack thereof).
Simple clean design. Easy to use. Doesn't have ads all over like some food trackers.

At first, I had the free version b/c I just wanted the basics; track my calories & exercise. And it was adequate. But I wasn't truly committed to changing my habits. When I went to the full version, it really made more of a difference than I thought it would. It offers so many more tools and options. It is worth the price. I caught a sale, but even at full price, it's worth the value. There's something there for everyone.

Still functional but incredibly frustrating that the ability to change the calorie limit is now locked behind premium. That was one of the key features of this app, and as someone who is currently trying to REPAIR their relationship with food, its incredibly DISAPPOINTING and DISTRESSING to see. I fail to see why this feature needs to be locked and inaccessible to those who're unable to afford it.
This app has helped me so much, with a program to track what i'm eating and clearly see where i fall short. There's lots of foods already in the app and the barcode scan is really useful.
The indicated nutritional value of products is subpar at times (i.e. doesn't match), but otherwise, the app is great.

Decent app, integrates into the smart watch via Samsung health, but you're getting a 2 star rating based on your recent decision to hide the ability to manually change your daily calories behind a pay wall.... like really!! Back to FatSecret for me!!!
Great app, ticks alla the boxes for me. Just the exercises part they overestimate the calories burn so i put half or 2/3 of the training time to get right calories burned

I would like to see a weekly average of calories consumed. When creating a meal, I'd like to be able to rearrange the order of the foods I'd like to be able to choose times to get breakfast lunch and dinner notifications
I actually really enjoy this app. I used the free version then upgraded because it was 50% off. The ability to take a photo of the barcode to enter food is a time saver!
Not worth it, you are extremely limited to their "set macros" unless you pay for premium. Luckily there are other apps that let you do it without paying
Very impressed with the usefulness of this app to track calories, fat, carbs and fibre. Wish it could collect data from Huawei Health.

Ability to sync with Fitbit exceeds that of MyFitnessPal, bit the crowdsourced food items are suspect, the ability to add recipes isn't intuitive, and editing recipes you have added is, as far as I can tell, impossible. I have paid for a premium account as well.
It's ok to track your meals. When you pay for it you get recepies which is nice .
They make you PAY for premium to set your own calorie target...so many apps do this for free. Ridiculous, uninstalled.
Good tracker, would like the option of marking or tagging days with names and comments in addition to just logging intake and activities.

Very pushy with buying a subscription. Would be nice if there were cheaper options just for seeing sugar intake and other nutrition stats - I have no need for the recipes at all. You used to be able to see your all-time progress (daily calorie intake) with a nice graph but they paywalled it within the last few weeks. Removing features that were free before is a gross move. 👎

The recipes are simple and delicious! I absolutely love the shopping list feature. The interface is fun, friendly, clean, and intuitive. If more of the diet programs had an option for pre-planned menu and shopping list, this app would be full-on perfect.
Great use for tracking your daily intake: even for those who are not trying to burn or gain weight.

Easy interface, huge food databank for logging, you can even scan the Ean code very reliably. Never had a code so far it didn't register! The free version has all the features you need. The paid version seems to be at a reasonable price and has a lot of fancy features. Definitely one of the better apps for dieting, beats fitness pal imo.

Overall Lifesum is great. However, there are a couple of things that would be nice to have in the app. Firstly, it doesn't let you set the goal weight if it's lower than the one that's considered healthy for you. That's the problem all of my friends who use Lifesum have. I believe, that this is your life and you are free to set any goal you want to. Secondly, it would be really nice if I could add a photo of the meal. Not when I create it or look for it, but on a daily basis with every meal.

Ive been enjoying this app so far. It has been a couple of weeks since I got this and Ive seen signicficant results! I do wish to see more of the nutrient facts of certain meals (fiber, iron, etc.) Regardless, I recommend this app to anyone who wants to lose that weight!
I love that they have calories for almost every restaurant I just wish the whole menu existed but other than that love it been helping me with this weight lose

Useful app to track macros. Most items I've scanned are correct. Some are a little off, but that could be that the product has changed a little and the connected barcode hasn't been updated. Maybe simplify the settings and personal information sections. The fewer clicks to find something the better. Great overall though!

I really enjoy this app a lot. it's helping count calories and follow my diet. However once I upgraded to premium I now have this bug. When I open the app it sends me to a website every time and it's annoying. It sends me to a website I read from your nutrition value information. Not sure why it keeps sending to this page. I've already read it and I tried to force stop the app and re open. But every time I open the app it goes to the nutrition value info web site.*Update it works now. Random bug
replyContent: We deeply apologise for this! Please contact support directly at https://lifesum.com/deep/settings?page=support and they will help you sort this out quickly. Thank you!

content: Ouch. Too aggressive paywalls nowadays, losing previous features and limiting isn't cool. Subscription services should add extra value, not the other way

Good app but some things could be better (imo): 1. I set my goal to maintain weight although I want to lose some fat and gain muscle, seems to be the only way.. which leads to 2. the burned calories are added to the daily amount. I know, with my goal it seems logical but it's mostly distracting. Oh and every time I want to track something the app glitches and the keyboard disappears 3 times in a row (as everything you could tip in 2 seconds) Everything else is great and I use it every day

Not a bad app, seen better. Its a bit complicated adding your own recipes, long winded. Also I subscribed to an offer of 3 months at a discount rate, I checked on Google pay, after 1 month its full price although the offer doesn't make that clear. Have cancelled all future payments. Also took them days to answer my query about price difference. They say there is 1000 recipes, they do have some very nice meals, also you can save your own recipes or dishes which gives them an extra star.
replyContent: Thank you very much for your feedback! We will make sure that it reaches the responsible teams. The recipes shown in the app under the Recipe tab is based on what diet/meal plan you are on, what food preferences you have entered and what allergies you have.

content: I really like the opportunity to put what I eat on my own that's not a menu item. Thank you lifesum.

It's the best app of this kind I've used up to date. That said, I think it promotes diet culture which can be problematic. Also, I would love if it could integrate with a Bellabeat wearable and if I could set a calorie range rather than a calorie limit. Finally, some of the food entries aren't representative of the actual nutrition of the item entered and it's hard to correct them.
replyContent: Thank you very much for your feedback! We will make sure that it reaches the responsible teams.

content: Easy to use and to find the food you want and easy to create your own food and meals, it has everything i need...track my meals, my sport, my weight. For me it has everything i need Still love it I understand that they need to make money, but to close the features of waist tracking and that i even can't see the chart from my weight anymore if i don't pay. That are no big features i am not sure if it necessary and helps. But i still use the app
replyContent: We are happy to hear you have a positive experience using Lifesum! We value your input and encourage you to let us know more details about your experience with us: https://lifesum.com/deep/settings?page=support Thanks in advance!

content: Do not sign up or enter any pay details, will keep charging you, even though you've cancelled. I cannot unsbscribe or cancel again!! I've been charged 2yrs running. Not happy.
replyContent: We deeply apologise for this, if you cancel your subscription this should not be the case! Please contact support directly at https://lifesum.com/deep/settings?page=support and they will help you sort this out quickly. Thank you!

content: It's an impressive app to use for calculating calories. The interface is decorated with soft colors, easy to use. No ads! I like this. There is a lot of data of food for you to choose. If the data haven't recorded, you absolutely can add more. It's good to try.
1st timer, beginner to the diet life. I would like to see the foods scanned that are bad or not helpful to hitting your goals, by suggesting a better food option!
Good but hard to find a lot of different foods that their scan code does not register.

Lifesum is an amazing way to keep track of your diet and how much you are eating and how much you should eat. I learnt about it because of my friends and I am sooo happy they showed me. Now we all compare results at the end of each day and encourage each other to do a bit better or congratulate them for hitting their goal. I highly recommend this app.

Don't waste your money! The app was easy to use and great for tracking steps and water consumption. The app sucks at getting calories and nutritional information correct. I would scan the barcode on my food and it would bring up the item but the fact were not accurate, they were close but never right and having to adjust portions was a pain to try and get it accurate from a calorie standpoint.
replyContent: Thank you very much for your review! We will inform the responsible team regarding your feedback.

content: This app is really great, but I am giving it 4 stars because you won't be able to access many features until u don't buy premium, although u do get food, calorie and exercise tracking but to get some of the recipes u need to unlock premium and not just that but many other things need premium, but the main features are available for free which makes the app really efficient and quick to use.

Awesome! Accurate results, low restrictions and motivates you a lot, although some people may have to edit their calorie count into a different limit because a doctor told them to eat a specific amount, it wasn't a problem for me because it gave me the amount I actually should be eating. I also like how there is so much food in the browser because unlike other apps if I eat something traditional or unusual in some places, this app has it! Excellent app.

Good, not great. I wanted to figure out where my daily calories are coming from, but this app, like all food trackers, suffers from one tedious issue - having to figure out portion sizes when making home cooked meals. Making one pot meals for 10-12 servings with lots of ingredients is hard to track. And the issue with this app is calories per serving/ounce/Tbsp/etc... are often wrong. content: "Lose it" for Free! or if you choose you can get the upgraded version. And Fabulous! An excellent app that is so helpful to get you to do what we already know how to do but don't. If you cheat, the only one you cheat is yourself. LOSE IT is helping me do exactly what I need to do by tracking my exercise and intake of foods. Losing it and loving it. ❤️ Thank you LOSE IT!

I love how easy it is to find item's that I'm consuming, even specific brands. Just knowing what's in the food I eat has helped me eat better food. Also being aware of my eating has helped me curb my 'grazing' habit, instead of just opening a bag of chips and hoping for the best, I get a snack sized bowl, put my chips in it and know how much salt and carbs I'm getting. It makes chips so much more enjoyable because I savor them and when I'm done there is no guilt.

This app is absolutely perfect for me. easy to setup [even without reading instructions], use and it costs a fraction of what I spent on another weight loss program. its so individually created. content: a little clunk finding foods sometimes but overall great and easy to use.

the ads for your subscription are annoying. It block a day that I can't add anything to it.
