content: Simple interface, large database of foods and ease of use are my top most important things when using a calorie counting app, this one has all of that! The free version is more than enough for your calorie counting needs, I have enjoyed it a lot so I decided to pay the premium version and I am very happy with it. This became my favorite calorie counting app!
As always. Advertised as a free helper app, throws a massive price at you towards the end.

Great app for tracking. Most things are easy, the database of foods is quite large and scanning bar codes finds most things. But when I realized I needed to move to a Keto diet, I found that it did not support that as well. I wanted to see less emphasis on calorie totals and more tracking of carb totals, so I switched to a different app. And why Keto? Keto allows me to address my feelings of hunger and stay on track. Oh well. Thanks for getting me back to tracking, LoseIt!

Exactly What I Was Looking For. This app has set me up a plan based on my height and weight and my goals for losing the weight. Additionally the app has given me control over how fast I chose to lose the weight to create realistic expectations. I loved how the app allows you to scan barcodes from food items to get accurate calorie counting. I'm on Day and I feel much better than when I started! You'll be amazed of how many mindless calories we consume on a daily basis.

Subscription makes this worthless. Id pay a one time fee for the app. But subscriptions are just an anxiety inducing horror mess. Google has calorie info for every food product on earth. I can add. Subscription models for games or any other apps are a total dealbreaker.
Good for counting calories and keeping track of what you eat, but no way you'll lose the weight it says without exercise.
I wish it was free. For the sake of me I don't think a subscription model fit this category of apps. maybe a one time payment could be great. oh well, c'est la vie!
I once I get familiar with logging my food ill be set. I love the app. its worth investing the mere 20.00yrly for premium membership.

Guess it's fine. I didnt really lose weight even though I was under my calories for days so it makes me think the calories are off on the app? I did have to change the calories on one item because it was wrong in the system, but I don't know how common that is. I'll be trying something else.
Well i havent stopped telling people how aaesome this app is...losing weight easily is a nice change of pace. biggest thing for me is the accountability partner it provides..

The app has an expansive food database and easy input methods with the bar code reader. Connecting to fitbit was unfortunately not available on the free version but the first year offer of 50% off on premium was not too high price to pay for my future healt and well being. Setting everything to my liking was a bit of fiddly work so if you are not technology orientated or have a short temper, ask help and prepare for at least 30min set up proses.

This app is brilliant! I absolutely love it. I've used several different calorie tacking apps and this is by far the best. So far everything I have scanned has been recognised and the calories have been correct according to the packets listing. This is not always the case with other apps. I love the little pictures that appear next to the food too. Plus you are able to see at a glance exactly what you have logged without having to navigate too far. No glitches either. Highly recommend, thank you
I'm really enjoying this app. It helps stay focused and motivates me to stay on track for a more healthy lifestyle.

I love that it has a Fasting tracker built-in so that I don't have to use multiple apps. They are addressing a bug with it and I look forward to the update. Otherwise this is the best, comprehensive food/fitness app I've used, to-date.

I'd always strayed away from this app before because I personally wanted to focus more on nutrition value rather than calories, but the alternatives always charged a premium for, well, their premium services. Lose It! is not only more affordable, but it's also better in my opinion. It supports all my other fitness apps to sync my weight and workouts, and it's a lot easier to use with a setup process that's well thought-out and delightfully supportive in anyone's health goals.

This really helped me lose 2.2kg in a month in a healthy and easy way. One thing I would say is that, although it does connect to Google Health, it doesn't connect to Huawei Health, which I use but that's just me nit-picking.
Not easy to scan something that has more than one serving, it only wants to log the single serving
honestly it's great, this app has a function where you can post your own story, and it warns you if your calorie budget is too low. Even tho the exercises may not be accurate in calorie burn

Overall fits my needs well. I'm using the free version so far, not the pro and it's doing exactly what I'd hoped. The recipe option is a nice touch! My only real complaint, some of the foods in the library have inaccurate values. However you can add your own and avoid the library altogether. I would love to have a widget that I could add to my home screen that would show my daily stats at a glance!

App hangs when searching for food. I have to restart the phone whenever I search for a good that isn't in the library. A helpful improvement would be adding weight training to the exercise section of the app because not everyone is focused solely on cardiovascular exercises like the ones listed. Overall, I think this is a pretty good app for tracking macros.

The best and most intuitive food tracker that I've used. I've used 3 others in the past and none compare to Macro's ease of use, easily understandable graphical displays, and convenient customization.

I loved this app while preparing for bariatric surgery, but life got in the way and surgery has been delayed so removed spp. Back on track and wanted to track my diet again but now have to pay for features that really helped,,, unfortunately I will can not afford to pay for apps... I have found another app that is free now and almost just as good,,
It's OK. Has alot of incorrect nutrition info I have to correct
Finally a simple calorie and macro tracker! No need for an account, no adds, no hard push for a premium subscription. Just a simple app for a simple task. THANK YOU!

I wanted to make a suggestion to have a widget that allows the user to add 250ml of water and see the water intake but the Contact support navigation item does not work. LE. Contact support and Report problem links don't work. I wanted to report another issue. With the dark mode, Android thinks the app is in light mode, and it paints a white background behind the keyboard which appears for a fraction of second when the keyboard expands or collapses. It's annoying to my eyes.

New to keto and having a hard time with macros... this is my solution. It's easy to use and very helpful with tracking. Really enjoy scanning feature (not even plus member!) And library of foods makes it easy to either find your food or something comparable.

I've tried so many apps before finding this one. It's definitely not so cluttered like most. I like how clean and simple it is to use. It's not confusing and doesn't have a ton of things but it's exactly what I was looking for. I like you can choose the type of plan you'd like to do and it's adjusts your calorie, carbs, fat & protein intake. I also love it's not too expensive if you want to upgrade. My fitness pal is so confusing overloaded with things plus $80 a year! This you can use free!
By far the best app I've used for keeping track of macros. Super easy

Best app. I think much better than MyFitnesspal, here you can monitor your carbohydrates, fats and proteins constantly seeing all the information in front of you, and you can very easily decide what food to add. For me, this has been a problem with all the apps I've tested before. This is the best app in the industry

Colorful, but missing core features. You can't change units of measurement of foods (cups to grams etc.) And the food library is buggy. Might be good one day. For now use Fatsecret as it's still the best in the market.

2nd time I upgraded to plus for a year subscription and has so much more to offer then the free version. Hands down the best macro application especially for keto and intermittent fasting and has been very useful for accomplishing my health goals.
Don't waste your money to update. What a rip off! It gives you nothing more than free version. Sorry to say they seen me coming.......

I like this app. It has a clean and uncluttered interface and the cost to upgrade to the pro version is reasonable. However, I can't stick with it because it's missing a couple of things which I hope get added in the future. There's no weight tracking, which is odd in an app of this nature. I would like to see weight tracking with a time to goal predictor as these can be very motivating. I would also like to see a widget added, which would be a good visual reminder and make meal logging faster.
It's not counting my macros correctly. It shows I haven't hit my daily carb-protein-fat intakes, yet my daily calories over my daily limit.
Addendum: Forgot to add that it allows you to arrange your meals as you like, which is great for people that do OMAD or IF.
best I have seen. it's designed to be unobtrusive yet has all the features one needs.

ABSOLUTELY the BEST app I have used not only for tracking but also just in general. So thankful I found this. I have already LOST 4 pounds in less than two weeks from being able to have an easier way to keep track. (Haven't seen the scale move in so long *sad face*) It lets you choose what type of "diet" you want to follow. I chose high protein and then it tells you how many grams of carbs, proteins, and fats you need to eat to achieve your goal.

Nice app, simple to use, recipe feature is nice and saves time. Fact check all things you add because lots of foods are wrong in the public library. A little glitch makes you restart the app occasionally but it always saves what you have added. Using the free version.

I cannot say how great this app is compared to all others I've tried. I can make 1-10 custom-labeled meals. I can make templates to set different goals for different days! ALSO, when I scan food I can edit the nutrition facts right then! (SO IMPORTANT!) Some items say they are 0 carbs (in ALL other apps) because they are <1 carb ... But I like to set them to 0.5 carbs when I see sugar somewhere in the ingredients. In other apps, you can't do that. Love it so far!

Has searchable online food nutrient data and stores your copies and edits local. Contributed data is not always correct. Simple to use. Does this weird thing where if you add excercise it increases the daily value targets for some reason. Don't like that but otherwise mostly clean concise app. Would allow a person to export and reimport a spreadsheet of nutrient data to make mining the web easier. Barcode scanner doesn't work but I think it's my camera.

The app is very good but the only problem is that it doesn't work offline and i can't access any data related to food and recipes offline so, please fix this problem and make localbackup possible I am afraid that in the future any problem could happen to the app servers and all my data would be inaccessible so, please make it accessible offline
I really love this app, but it doesn't seem to work offline. There's no good reason why I should need a network connection to see the food that I've already entered for the day.
It's actually really simple and easy to use. And no, I am not a bot. Could a bot do this ajshhwhshaha, didn't think so 😌💅🏼
Great app and layout, it's just frustrating that every time I want to type a quantity when inputting food, it autofills my cell phone number.
Great app! Simple and easy to use and they keep adding new updates that are making it ever better.
Very happy with the app! I have T1 Diabetes and accurate monitoring of my carbohydrate intake is key for the control of the condition. Thanks to this app it is possible.
Just what I was looking for; no frills, good database, no judgement - just the facts.
Three days in and I see a future of better eating habits developing.
Amazing app! Setup can be slightly confusing but besides that it's amazing and has everything you could need!

This app is perfect for tracking meals and their nutritional content. It gives you full control over your meal plan with a gammit of customization options. Would recommend to anyone trying to stick to a diet.

Started using it to manage my GERD a couple years ago, once I got that under control my usage fell off. now using it to lift. Great app, does what it needs to, stays out of your way. Just asked the dev if he can implement other micronutrients or custom fields, but ultimately a small complaint.
Good app but just really wish it could connect and share data with more external apps
Seems pretty good, but no weight tracker? That and /or a body fat tracker /graph would be great. Seems there isn't one app that has all features!

It does exactly what I was hoping to get out of a free macro calculator I've downloaded several others and deleted all of them because there are too many add walls or you have to pay to use it. This is simple and effective

I love this app, definitely the best that I've tried so far to calculate calories and macros. I like that is kept simple but at the same time very detailed and personalizable. The ads shown are absolutely not in the way and that really improves the experience. Absolutely recommended!
Awesome app. It provides everything I need. Just It would be awesome if there was a web version.
The app is amazing but the payment model is terrible. $33 CAD per year on a recurring subscription is just unnecessary and unrealistic. Needs a one time payment option.
I activated the plus version which is quite expensive for what the app is worth and there is no option to deactivate it on the app!

Easy to use. Simple straight forward. Thought i saw somewhere it linked to google fit, but i can't seem to figure that out. Must be wrong, unless someone knows how. Would love to have that ability to sync nutrient info from here to google fit.
Easy to use and works better than I imagined any macros app to work. I wish I started using it sooner

This app is very easy to use and pretty simple no extra fancy stuff. If youre here your most likely trying to find a better alternative to MyFitnessApp and it is, as far as i can tell there is no overpriced premium and has all the essentials for nutrients and macros. Thumbs up.

Overall clean and simple app compared to my fitness pal. Wish I could do a one time payment of like 5 bucks for at least some of the pro features even if they still want to keep the subscription model for other things. (Overall sub looks inexpensive) Some bugs and improvements can be made like text being too small and colors overly complex. But generally works on quickly finding food and reading my days totals

Generally Well done including a barcode scanner to easily include refined good you eat otherwise a pretty extensive database of foods from a quick search. The only thing is that most items I've added with the barcode don't match the nutritional info on the packages, or they're just partially filled. Also other nice features are create ur own quick foods and recipes and u can activate the net carbs option, good if ur in keto!

I used the free version for awhile with success so I upgraded and paid. I was hoping to include two additional meal set ups and as of yet I find no additional benefit or additional uses to paying except no advertising and the app freezes up now. I've tried contacting support through the app and it does not open and goes nowhere.
There's a problem with the calories calculator. It add extra calories from meals. Additionally, when i registered with wrong email then signed out all my information was lost.
Finally found this app as I was looking for something matches level of MyFitnessPal. Also, very affordable and easy user interface. Might be better than MyFitnessPal in future.
A simple app. Simple to use to track macros. I love the scan option. It allows me to scan my favorites w/o having to look up each time.

Just starting a keto lifestyle. Honestly I tried 10+ apps before this. Though I admit it can be a little tough to get the hang of it. Once you do its amazing. The barcode scanner is a godsend and 80% of the items it finds saving me tons of time. I can group items as recipes so I don't need to add every item each day, for something like bulletproof coffee. Ads are very minimal and don't hinder functionality. I will likely pay for premium just to support the devs. Thank you for an amazing app!

Much more intuitive than other apps I've tried. I use a portion container system for meal guidance, input them, and watch to be sure I hit my goals. I haven't used it for long, but the fact that I haven't groaned every time I've looked at the app says a lot!

My chosen unit is g I search for beef liver, and one option is measured in oz. I expect the app to recalc from oz to gram and present it to me as such. The point of the app is to do the calc for me. Also, there is only a subscription based option, no once off ; unfortunately I've made a decision to avoid such products.

Awesome app, works amazing. Only reason why it didn't get that last star is cause of the exercise feature. It would be nice to see more sports or calisthenics being an option too. Otherwise it's awesome.
Interface seems okay, every food I've tried to log has weird portions (ie 150g when the actual serving is 128g and it's a single serving item)

Simple to use and clean interface. The ads are not very intrusive and pro is not to expensive if you want the extra options. When I contacted support the response was very quick, helpful and friendly.
Easy to use and I absolutely love how fast I can make custom entries. Best macro app I've ever used.

24 hours convinced me how great this app is. I'm personally a fan of apps that stay put of your way, and Macros excells here. I'd like to see some third party integration so I don't have to enter my hydration or exercise twice - but that's my biggest gripe, and I had to think to find it. Do yourself a favor and get this app.
Perfect app. Simple, intuitive. Has just the right amount of bells and whistles without distracting from the main job of tracking macros over time. Nice job!
Been using this for probably 5 months now. It's just about everything I wanted, the only thing I wish it did is sync with my Samsung health app. Other than that I love it
Just downloaded it, and I can already see it's better than fitness pal! Simple and efficient. No $20 monthly fee to see macros.

Absolutely love it! It makes you one hundred percent accountable for the things you put in your mouth! Even though I was on a carnivore diet, I was eating way too much food! This helped me stay at a reasonable level. A little finicky in the beginning but once you get your food inputted and get the hang of it, it is super easy!

So far this app has been awesome. It's been quite helpful with keeping track of my intake. I've never used an app of this sort before so I have nothing to compare it with but in my case, it's doing the job and with ease. I enjoy using it.
App itself makes tracking macros simple. Lost a star as it doesn't integrate with Garmin or Google fit

Excellent, highly recommended. Have been using for a few years, very easy to use, customisable for your goals, add your own recipes, best app for tracking calories and macros. Thank you for developing this application.

I'm updating my review from 2 stars to 5. I sent an email to the developer JosmanTek as I couldn't track water, or even change the date, thus my chart was stuck on the same day & I couldn't use it at all. I received 2 emails with instructions & advice, which I implemented, & now everything is working! Looking forward to using it

Simple and easy to use. Doesn't ask any questions before it lets you into the main app. Allows you to put in items manually without requiring a bunch of unnecessary details. Exactly what I was looking for!

Basic UI, but all the essential features - insert your own recipes, divide them up by servings, barcode scanner to add new items automatically, calorie counter, unit conversions (g -> oz). I wish you could toggle the unit conversion with a drop down, without going into "edit" mode, but really, the app is pretty much perfect. One non-invasive ad at the bottom of the screen, no spamming with invitations to try the premium version :)
Great app. I love how you can edit the distribution of the macros. It never gives enough protein to begin with. I've made plenty of meal plans using this as a baseline

Great help managing my macros. App easy to learn and navigate. I hadn't counted macros because it was a pain, but this app lets me tweak meals by adding/ subtracting foods to get my target amounts. Calculates your goal by weight, etc. Lets you add your own favorite foods, scan bar codes, search a library of foods, track water, calc what is remaining and enter other nutritional values. What I would like to see is sorting foods by fat, carbs or protein and keep other measurements I have added.
Love this app. Easy, straightforward and clear. It would be nice to have also weekly summaries.
It's a good app for what it is, but it doesn't connect to anything like Samsung Health or Google Fit. That limits its overall usefulness.
Simple. Tracks net carbs. Tracks sugar alcohol. Definitely a go-to! Wish it were more esthetically pleasing, but wouldn't trade that for functionality.

As a newbie to counting macros, this app is brilliant. Very easy to use, has all the foods you can imagine and you can set your day as you want (I just deleted meals and put everything together in one, because lazy), the BEST part is that you can adjust the 3 macros percentages as per the diet/lifestyle you want to have. Spot on with everything, and free ♡♡♡♡♡
It does exactly what it advertises and I don't think I've encountered a bug after about 6 months of daily use. It's really similar to My Fitness Pal except it's free

It may be premature as I've only just downloaded it, but the app is perfect! Easy to use, no personal info, no gimmicks, let's you adjust your pre-calculated goals and calculates macros, you can make your own list of foods, add excercises etc. exactly what I needed!

best app for track calories. does not require log in (thank god) and it goes straight to the point. this is how a great user experience should look like. I will buy the premium just to suport the devs.
Good but it doesn't have a list of foods,you need to add every single one manually, I recommend track from nutritionix instead

Slimmed down version of mfp, without the forums and social aspect. The only issue is some of the barcodes are not accurate but acceptable. Developers need to allow modifying barcodes for the label values.
Perfect app that has many useful features to help track with exercise, water, and much more.

Useless. Too basic and even then, full of bugs and glitches all over. For example, when you want to enter a number to specify how much of a food you had, you have to do it twice because as soon as you delete the default number, the macros show 0.00 even though you have entered a new number. Uninstalling. It's worthless.

Amazing. This App is so simple and it works! Its science! It takes some time to add in your food in the beginning but once it's in, you input your food in with one click and you're done! It makes you accountable for what you're stuffing in your mouth! We eat WAY MORE than we think we do. This app makes you aware. Love it!

Finally an application that turns out to be useful because of the parameters and the level of information the user can provide. If you want to keep track what you are eating and improve your eating habits you will love it. Thank you sir.
Better than the other myFP. Allows for percentages of macros in 1% increments like normal counting goes, rather than in increments of 5% like MyFPal does it . Thanks!

I just came across this app a few minutes ago after looking at numerous otherapps along with reading each of their specs and reviews! I feel this app is what I am looking for Because I am just wanting an app to tell me what my calorie intake is after putting everything in my List that I have eaten for each part of the Day! Its Great and So far is Easy to Operate! With Great Pleasure to say Im Glad I kept searching and Came across this wonderful App that is meeting all my needs thus far!

It's ok. Used carb manager for years and loved it but they updated and screwed it.The dark mode is nice. The database leaves a lot to be desired. Its not as expansive as other apps. I have to correct barcode scans because people put in wrong numbers, names , right down to not even being able to spell brands. That's not the apps fault but they need to put a report function in for idiot entries messing up database accuracy. It doesn't multiply correctly either when you increase serving size
Its as good to use as it is tedious to start. The only reason it doesn't get 5 stars is I would like to see a per serving price tracking system to see the price of 3ach serving or the whole meal

Extremely easy to use, very informative, no BS interface, ads blend in nicely and aren't distracting at all, there are options to add custom recipes and even exercises. Very satisfyed with this calorie counter. Recommended for any fitness person, be they amateur or pro.

Easy to use, clean and intuitive interface, and very helpful for keeping track of food intake and fitness goals. The barcode reader feature works really well and makes it even easier to use. I can't recommend this app enough to anyone trying to maintain focused on their diet.

Best free macro tracking app I've found, provides all the features necessary to accurately and painlessly track your macro and micro nutrients throughout the day, without locking you behind a monthly pay-wall to access essential features. Enough said
hands down the easiest nutrition tracking app. no issues. been using for 2 years. love it. works great at free level. I love the features that come with paying. nice work. here. thank you.
Lost 20% body fat and 40 lbs total in a full body recomp. Mostly from dedicated use of this app and regular activities/workouts. Don't slack off, give it 3 months and it will change your life!

Edit after update: the daily calories bar now doesnt look red after you exceed your daily target. The calories number of each meal looked way better next to the name of the meal instead of being placed next to the macros Thanks in advance

I used mfp for almost 6 years and would get frustrated with the cumbersome food log. I've tried almost 12 other food diary apps and am so glad to have found this one! It is perfect for my needs. Free version is easy to use and ads are not intrusive. App is straight forward, foods can be added, edited or deleted easily. I agree with reviewer that said it takes the anxiety out of keeping a journal. I also appreciate being able to customize the number of meals I eat in a day. The latest update made this great app even better! Well worth paying for if you choose to do so, this app is one of the best.

Reliable layout and love that you can customize things I just wish there was a way to keep multiple cal & macro goals so that you could have different goals for each day. I carb cycle so I have different macro distributions every day and I think those who eat differently for rest days, etc would benefit from it. Otherwise great app

Perfect for PSFM and Keto tracking. Adjustable for individual macros/diet specific goals, has an extensive food library for easy plug in food tracking and also allows you to create recipes using ingredients (most of which are already in the database/ library) but if you don't find a food or ingredient, it's very easy to add it in. Love the simplicity of the app and have switched over to this from MyFitnessPal..much better

Just downloaded it. Seems easy enough. But how do I sync my phone and my tablet so I don't have to add each food individually? 12/14/20 getting tedious rewriting entries from phone to tablet or tablet to phone.
Amazing. Best app for tracking , also allows you to copy meals all whole days and paste on the next day. Very practical

Love it! Easy to use and simple. I can just add, and/or edit foods for the day, I can also track my water intake, and I can also add my own recipe and can save it for another day I make it and just edit if there's any changes. The ads are bearable, it doesn't take much space on the screen.👌👌👌

What a great app. I love the interface. Ads are not intrusive and are in a small banner at the bottom of the page. SO much better than my fitness pal. I can easily count macros and make sure I'm getting enough protein to put on some muscle. So easy to add new food/recipe information and most of the time foods are already there from where other people have inputted. Sometimes they are not quite up to date as brands change things so I always check up on foods I add from the library.

I've been using this app for 4 years. It's spot on and easy to use. I made loads of recipes and used the app the accurately count my macros. Made real gains. Then i go to use it today and ALL my recipes and saved food have vanished! Pretty gutted. Hoping it can be sorted

Great for my needs! Counts the macros, foods can be edited, recipes can be created, individual items can be created if its not in the library, and has basic calculations for weight loss/gain. The only thing I want different is a left/right button for the days at the bottom.
So far it's been good. Never tracked food this way, so it's a learning curve. But it's been pretty easy to create, search by title, or scan everything I need.

Annoyed that you have stupid limitations like you can only set it in grams for the paid version. I have no idea yet if this is the app for me and I'm not going to pay until I do know as I've downloaded several that have not been what I needed. Now I won't get the chance to see if it's the appropriate app for my needs because of dumb restrictions like that. Why on earth can you have the free version only if you want to set it in percentages but have to pay to set in grams!! Stupid and now deleted

I use it to both meal plan and record meals. So I plan the meals are nd the caloric goals and macros goals I've set. The I eat exactly what I've planned. I like the bar code scanner and the ability to edit foods. Some people do not accurately record information. Also, the app seems to accurately figure net carbs. I have the paid version. Very useful.

Absolutely love the app. I noticed it doesn't update my recipes when I update my foods, and I don't understand why I need an internet connection to see my log, but other than that I have no further wishes.

It's good, I like it. Better than fitness pal. Better user interface. Love the simplicity. Love the database of foods that you can search through and edit. Wonderful. Only additions I would like: custom in-app reminders to log food/weight. And a graph showing how much weight you've gained or lost. If you had those two functions, it would be the perfect app to me.
As a father of 3 small children, I personally find it near impossible to track macros, this app changed that. I have literally thanked the person that recommend this app, 5 times.

Manually set calories doesn't work. When you manually set the calories it doesn't show up as the target on the journal tab. The journal tab targets are based on goals and activity level regardless of manual calorie goal.
This app is very simple to use. Calculates your calories and macros at the same time, as well as a percentage of fats carbs and protein.

Really pleased to find this excellent app; much better functionality than MFP, really like the ability to track grams protein, carbs, fat (hence the Macro name); option to automatically calculate Net Carbs.VERY helpful.

This is hands down the best macro tracking app I have ever used. And I have tried about six or seven. Creating recipes is so easy. Another feature I absolutely love is when you go to add foods for breakfast, it will show recent foods that you have logged for previous breakfasts first. Same goes for a lunch and dinner. They're seriously was so much thought put into this app. I tell all of my macro tracking friends about it.
Basic. Only one macro option unless you upgrade. Logging is a awkward UX with extra taps to add foods.
I love this app. Simple and easy to use. Love being able to adjust my calories and macros and distribute them how I like across my meals.

Great!!. You can use a barcode scanner to enter you meals and is highly customisable. It tells you how many carbs, fat, and protein you should eat and how many calories you should eat. I love this app. I've personally lost 50 pounds using this app

Lovely app, very straightforward with a lot of customization in the right spots and minimal distracting graphics. Only issues I have are that you can't set your own water targets and the recipe builder crashes without saving your data if you click outside the app. Weight tracking over time and the *ability to swap macro percent without changing them on prior days would also be useful* (this has since been added)

Personally I'm giving it a 5 star bc it does everything I downloaded it for. You can customized it and add anything you need, super easy to open, swipe, click, add, whatever then get on with your day, all while keeping your macros counted. I prefer this app over others I've tried. And I'm pretty picky haha

Totally disappointed 😥😥😥 I thought that myfitness pal is bad but this one is way more disappointing. 1. Way too much colors to distract the eye 2. No option to make my costume meal,adding pictures and so on 3. No option to follow my killos 4. Every single time I have to change my diet, always give me CUSTOM but I want Keto. Thank you, but no.

Does about everything I needed to do! I can add my own food or choose from the data base, detailed recipes, and choose grams or percentages, among some of the features. You need to use the app for a little while before leaving a review. It does more than you would think. Helped me enter ketosis!
I needed an easy, user friendly app to keep track of calories and macros. This app is perfect and exactly what I was looking for.

Really like this app and find it a lot more stream lined & straight forward than mfp. The food data base has so many things & it is a breeze to add your own recipes which I appreciate since I cook so much. My only complaint is that it seems to "round up" my counts. For instance , something that is 1.5g fat per serving, it will round to 2 & does that for all items like that. By the end of the day that really adds up & makes my counts both inaccurate & higher which is highly inconvenient.
Best free macro tracking app. No annoying ads if any, so good I can't remember, easy to use and has everything and you can edit so many things

Great app for counting calories without anxiety! Amount of overall calories is well calculated, values can be edited and interface is really simple to use. I like to check my daily intake but other apps led me to anxiety issues on food (warning about too much fat introduced, calories intake too big on the font)
Great app.. simple yet very useful, most of the foods you want to track are avalible even for someone who lives in the third world.. helps alot with tracking what you put in my body
So helpful and user friendly I liked it so much. The ads are a small bar at the bottom of the screen which is okay.
Simple, just what I needed & highly customisable to the days and macro splits. Minus all the social distractions. Pay extra for premium, but reasonably priced. Great job!
Inaccurate when you need to change the measurement units. It doesnt change the calories or macros when you do.
Pretty good, some bugs. Good at tracking macros, but constantly deletes the recipes I create. Very frustrating Otherwise, I enjoy using it.

Better than most, and pro features are reasonably priced. Unfortunately like almost every other diet tracker, this app does not allow to to list anything other than the default cal/carb/protein/fat on the home screen. You have to tap "details" and scroll down a big list to see vitamins or minerals that are important to you (example: low sodium diet for kidney/heart health).

Reviewed yesterday and only gave it 4 stars because, well it was just one day. Well, now it is 2 days and this app does everything I need. Easy to track food and water, add new food, manage calories and macros, even edit food if I make a mistake in creating. Been using Spark People but it is changing and don't like My Fitness Pal (too cumbersome). A reviewer at MFP recommended Macros. It is everything I need and want in a simple, flawless execution (so far). Love this app!
Simple, yet effective design. Not bogged down by unnecessary features. Ads aren't very invasive and don't ruin the user experience.

This is the winner from among 6 different apps. I had 'Carb Manager' for over a year. Their update causes a Full Screen Ad with every page change. Uninstalled. ~ MACROS lets you use their app without EVER creating an account if desired. Create your own recipes. Good library w/ barcodes. EASIEST water tracking ever. And I like that it defaults to searching MY FOODS. ~ NEEDED: ability to add foods in GRAM msmts; more accurate than cups. And not sure where to track weight. I emailed the developer.

This is the best app that fit my needs ie to monitor and track my micro nutrients. So easy to use. Very friendly and its food data base are surprisingly so gd. I'll not be changing apps anymore. So happy with this app.

App has a good range of functionality for free. The range of foods already in there is great. It's easy to use and easy to see where you are up to each day. Do need to be careful to double check the stats of foods before selecting as it appears some people add a food with no stats. There isn't an edit function to correct any typos in a food after saving.

This app is great for meal and macro tracking. I love that it connects to my FitBit so I don't have to double up my data input. I love how customizable it is. My only bone of contention is the fact that the app only tracks sugar instead of added sugars, which almost all labels specify. Added sugars matter way more for nutrition than sugar, and most sugar recommendations are about added sugar intake.
My favorite calorie and nutrition tracker. Helpful graphs and visualizations. Simple layout for for easy and quick readability.
Some of the foods are incorrect, but I love that you can adjust the macros on the fly, nothing is static. Also hooks up to FitBit app that my coach can see (but this is much more user friendly)
Good app to track your dietary journey but could you add it so we can add a custom amount of water cause it's just annoying with only the 4 options
Love this app! I've been using it daily for the past month and it's great for gauging where you stand with your daily caloric intake and macros.
This app is truly life changing Alhamdulillah. It keeps me so disciplined in terms of sticking to a healthy diet in order to stay within my caloric limit as well as meet my macros goal.
I lost 40 pounds using this app. You can change your macros, correct nutritional values, add your own food. I just wish it had a weight tracker with it. I had to down load an app for that.
The app is amazing. Does everything you would want make your own recipes easy input for any food you could buy.

Great app, been using it to track daily intake for specific goals for about 6 months now. Very good features and the Macro Plus purchase is definitely worth it! Nice to have features if the Devs are willing 😊 : Custom Reminders for tracking meals (custom in terms of timing of reminders) Supplements tracking as an option (e.g. Whey, Fish oil, etc.)

I use the free version and the majority of features work flawlessly. The recipe feature is very frustrating tho. After meticulously scanning and converting each ingredient to grams the tracker itself defaults the recipe to serving size, and does not automatically calculate the total weight. This leads me to do all of my math, twice. Please change it so if I choose a mass measurement the field automatically sums the mass of my ingredients.

I just started this app and I'm already so impressed with the set up and ability to customize. The free version has so much to offer (more than other popular apps) but if you still want to upgrade, their premium service is super affordable.
Very simple to use! 👌🏻 i just bought the Plus version for 12 mos. Would be better if i can add excercises and calories burned based on reps and sets rather than just in minutes.

Stop looking. Simple, not obtrusive apps, tons of ways to find your foods, very simple and usable UI. Not sure if there are better apps, but if there are they'd likely just be similar versions of this. Brilliant A+ work

I've tried several macro trackers and calorie counters, this is by far the best, simplest, and easiest to use. The free version has everything i need, but i love the app so much i got the plus version to help support the future development of this. At $13/yr why not? And customer support is great! I emailed with a Austin and was responded to quickly!

good enough but the inability to adjust BMI and other measurements is annoying. The bigger issue is why the app always forgets what foods and meals I added in. Everything from the barcode to the name and macros, once written in, disappear from the app in a week or so. Unless it can actually save them without losing them I can't recommend this.

Love. Love. Love. 😍 Some other apps may have some 10 million downloads... It doesn't mean the ones with less downloads are not but as good. I have used My Fitness Pal, Fitbit... Loads of others.. and yes it's early days but I already see why this is a popular app. A lot of thought put into it and meaningful features. Love it.
Best one so far... The free version counts calories and macros, makes you scan and edit the food you want to log on, create recipes and meal plans and so on... It's just perfect

Far and above better than my fitness pal! This is what My Fitness Pal used to be! I'm so glad I found you! No long user creation, immediate set up, super easy and comprehensive ui, bonus features and all for free! I'm in love and excited to get back on track!

It is, plain and simple, plain and simple. No frills, nothing unnecessary. It's beautiful in its minimalism. Easy to adjust what you want, easy to input, easy to see your overalls. This is the only app I use now, and it's perfect.

Thanks to the intuitiveness and available customization of this app, I'm finally tracking my macros consistently. (Never had the patience with any others I've tried.) Thank you!! Definitely an integral tool on this journey. 🌿
It's had every food I've scanned so far, and it makes keeping track of my meals really really easy.
Easy to use, the only free app I could find that does macros well and simply in addition to calories.

This app is exactly what I have been looking for. More flexible than the other apps I've tried. Able to set your own macros, enter and edit your own foods, and clearly see your goal vs where you are at currently. Ads do not interfere. Well designed. I would love to be able to share info/results with a friend, or have a short editable summary page that could be shared or viewed.

Great app to keep a record of all your meals. It is very useful if you want to work out, lose weight, want to see what are you eating if you have an illness or just for fun. I use eat every day in every meal. Thank you! (:
Simple and Easy. Been using this app for a few years for myself. I have the paid version, now I can make clients meal plans right from my phone. Love this app.

Really impressed with this app, it does everything I need it to! Very easy to build list of food choices, easy to adjust the amounts /nutrition data to accurately match what you ate. Really like the ability to copy & paste a whole meal from one day to next - breakfast is usually the same for me! You can tweak settings easily - eg I'm slowly lowering my carb:protein/fat ratio to get nearer to a keto type diet. Best of all - it even adds calories used in exercise onto allowances each day!
I am using this app since a very long time now about 1 year. I have lost 28 kgs in total till now. It has quite a vast list of food items. Loved it. It also measures calories quite accurate. Liked it
The app is great for tracking macros, the user interface is straight forward. I ended up switching though because it's not easy to see net carbs :/
Hey Keto lifers , This is the App to used for tarcking your macros. Ive used this app for 30min and im loving how easy it was to used. Thank you so much. I can keep track of my macros with ease.

Great app with a simple and intuitive interface. Interface tesponse time can be sluggish and export formatting needs improvement. Improvements to export formatting needed.

Almost Perfect For My Needs 1. I had to add my own entries since the pre-feeded entries had incorrect Macros. 2. It has Meal Planner. 3. It has Macros Ratio Goals. 4. I can make my own Recipes. 5. I am losing weight(fat).
Fantastic free app! Easy to use, can adjust macros and calories. Scans barcodes. Organised and user-friendly. Logs food, water, exercise. A game-changer!

I have downloaded (8) different apps. to track my macros and they all want a bunch of info before they either tell me I need the upgrade to do what I want or I find out that it doesn't track carbs accurately (if at all)! If you just want an app. with a simple way to track your carbs, proteins and fats, look no further and get this one! Very user friendly and customizable - and free!

I love this app, easy to figure out all of the macros. Only 1 thing I'd like to ask, is it possible to switch from duration to steps in regards to the walking exercise? If that was possible then it would be 5/5

I have moved from Carb Manager to Macros. After trying dozens of trackers I like the simple functionality of Macros. 1 major glitch.......scanned foods and library foods are often wrong. I end up going in and editing them. For example Fage 5% when scanned comes up with wrong portion size and wrong macro nutrient info. However, it's a small price to pay for a really good aop

I really like this app. It's very easy to navigate and very straight forward. Like other apps, I would need to buy a membership to import recipes, which I can't afford right now. But even creating recipes manually is so much easier than on other apps, I'm willing to go without that feature, as long as the basic features are user friendly. I also love how it figures out an estimated bmi. Now if the free app included community groups, I would definetily rate this app 5 stars 😊!
Overall great app. Very complete library of foods. Only complaint is that it has become quite glitchy of late. It hasn't been updated since Sept 2020.

Love app with exceptions If custom amount is put in some nutritional values don't get updated. Im on a low cholesterol diet and if I change the amount eaten it updates some nutrition but not cholesterol so daily values are skewed.UPDATE: Still love this app. Dev is really responsive to issues. Learning more about the app. Going premium today!

Very nice and organized app, gives you lots of info for your diet and weight planning, specially about carbs, calories.,etc. Good idea of what you get from it. I would give it a 5 star rating if it had a single price purchase. Monthly rates are easy to forget, and if you stop using the app for any reasons, those charges keep coming, and that is what all these apps are after. No sign in required which is refreshing, I would gladly pay a one time fee for removing addds alone.

Good app overall. My wife and I are trying to be more deliberate with our nutrition, I think this app can help us get there. The one shortcoming I see in the app is that there is no way to share recipies, meaning we have to manually input everything twice. Inputing recipies is a very time consuming task, specially at the beginning while you are setting yourself up. Not being able to share recipies doubles the time needed.
Exceptionally easy to use and the subscription based upgrade is worth it at a very low cost. Highly Recommend.
It's brilliant. Simple, no unnecessary frills like other nutrition tracking apps but still elegant and easy to use. Well done!

Wow this app is bad. I used the app for a week and found EVERY SINGLE entry is wrong, based on USDA nutrition facts and even comparing packaged food nutrition facts on the label to entries. It isn't trustworthy by any means and the developers show they lack even remedial dietary tracking skills, let alone competence by any stretch of the imagination. They need to give up apps and try grocery bagging to see how food works as they clearly have no clue. Just quit team, try finger painting.

Beautiful UI, non-intrusive ads, and lacks the bloat of other nutrition tracking apps. I love the large food database and the barcode scanner. Entering in individual foods, recipes, macro, and micro-nutrients is simple and intuitive.

PSA for keto: go into your settings (cogwheel in upper right) go to "Advanced," and turn on "Calculate net carbs." It would be a great feature if when selecting keto/atkins, this would automatically turned on. *Winks at the devs* I love this app. It's easy to use and has basically everything I need on my weight loss journey. Highly recommended!

For some strange reason this app does not track magnesium. No matter what food I put in the tracker, the magnesium will not register. It does not register my magnesium supplements either. This is a disappointment since the reason for purchasing the app was to keep track of my electrolyte intake.

Incredible app. Non-intrusive ads, seamless interface, everything has been thought of. Even lets you scan the barcode of food items and compares them to the database of what everyone else has scanned, so you don't have to enter in the macros half the time.

I love this app! It's super easy and I appreciate all the displays. My ONE wish is that you could "lock" in a meal and transfer macros around - if I have a low fat breakfast, I want those fats "moved" to dinner or lunch, or redistributed once I know I'm not eating any more for breakfast. The daily tracker sort of does this but it would be nice if that could be customizable per meal. Otherwise it does exactly what I need!
Wanna get into this app, having an issue with Magnesium, it just says zero no matter what... I did write an email to you guys regarding the issue and didn't get a response. I want it to work!!

Huge data base. Easy to log and track macros!!!..... way easier than writing it all. Plus, you can calculate your own recipies accurately, and use them. Best food diary app I've tried. You'll love it too.
Really like the app. Simple and uncluttered interface. Does exactly what I want with no pointless extras I'll never use.

Great for meal tracking, easy to use, minimal ads, easy to find or add foods... barcode scanner actually works! Easy to add workouts & edit anything (goals, nutrient labels, calories burned per workout etc...) Definitely recommend!
Love this app, the colour coding and UI are incredibly helpful to get info from a quick glance. Would have bought premium if it was a flat fee and not a monthly/yearly subscription...
Best app to track macros and store recipes. The extensive food inventory, edit features and barcode option make it very easy for tracking.
This is a great app if looking for macros and evercise log. Is not loaded down with a lot of filler junk. and the pro cost is very affordable.
I've been using it for quite a while and I like it a lot more than the other apps I've tried. I just wish it was easier to track a recomp diet using this app, but besides that it's been perfect.

Easy to use and track calories and macros much easier then other apps I've tried. It's all in the one view with tracking at the top so as you enter you can easily see where you are at. Customer services is very responsive and usually get back to you by the next day. I have been using the free version for 4 months but will up upgrade to paid version as I would like to start tracking other micronutrients.
Scanned two items and the information was inaccurate. Tried creating a new listing and editing the info and it was an absolute nightmare. Wouldn't suggest this app if you want accurate info.

Great app. I can manually set the macros to what I want and adjust as I go. The food which is already in the database is quite good. Creating a food and/or recipe is relatively fast and easy. I would prefer an extra section of the app to be able to insert your weight so as to see a graph of your progress.

Helps to stay accountable of your diet, the food you eat, can search find and insert, above all, it's good for weightloss, weight gain and best thing about it is it's free.. would recommend to anyone serious about learning how to manage their diet

Any app that demands you to sign up = going to sell your personal data to their affiliates. Plain and simple. And watch, if they respond to this, they won't deny that they sell or give away your information that they collect- if you type it in or if they grab it from your phone storage.

I love this simple-to-navigate app to track macros and calories. There is an immense number of items already in the database and everything can be edited for accuracy. The copy-and-paste meal feature is a great time saver too. What I would like to see is a spot to log/track daily weight changes. Then this app would be perfect!
Since downloading this app, I have received a daily text from different numbers trying to sell me on weight loss supplements. Do not download this app!!!

I used MFP before but Macros is way simpler to use. I love the minimalist design, dark mode and clear informations. It's very quick to add entries to your food journal. It runs great on my phone as well (I have a Huawei P20 lite which can be slow with other apps).

This app has been instrumental in fine tuning my already great eating habits to help develop my physique goals. Erin Stern, fitness professional, advised tracking macros, and this app has far exceeded my expectations for getting the results I want from proper diet and weight training. I would recommend this app to anyone
This app is easy to use and helped me lose 25lbs since I purchased it. As I use a scale to measure what I eat a nice feature would be a uom conversion when adding a food.

Easy to use, really well designed interface. To start you need to double check the nutritional information for added food against the info on the actual food packaging ( or website if it doesn't have it i.e loose fruit/veg) to get the most accurate results. Worth the effort though

Recently they added an enormous banner ad on top of the diary tab that takes up essentially a quarter of the screen telling you to get premium. Makes it impossible to see the whole day's diary. Tempted to just switch to another app because of how irritating that obstruction of screen space is.

content: Be careful!!! Im 2018 they had a data breach and I just found out! During the MyFitnessPal data breach, hackers accessed usernames, passwords, and email addresses. Uninstalled. I wanted to like it, but this app is horribly inaccurate! The numbers are completely different from what is on the packaging for my sausage. This app should allow you to make adjustments to correct the amount of calories, or at least allow you to put in a gram measurement so that it can be more accurate.

Was using lose it but decided to switch over to My Fitness Pal. It is great but one thing that might make me go back to lose it is the fact you can't change the oz or grams of things. (although the searching could use more filtering.) only issues for me are 1. that the numbers turn red when you're even just the slightest bit over, which is very aggressive, and there isn't anything to warn away a starvation diet. and 2. i feel like the community is very toxicly positive and old.
replyContent: Hi there! Thank you for your review and feedback. User comments help us shape the app for the future.

content: I appreciate this app- makes it easy to log food and find approximations for calories and macros even when I'm too lazy to do the exact amounts. I don't need to spend more than a minute to input a meal, but even when I'm thorough it doesn't make more than 3min!

content: Needs more options for food tracking such as weight instead of serving size. Otherwise pretty good. Way better interface than MyFitnessPal.
replyContent: Hi Kyle! Thank you for your review and feedback. We have passed your comments to our product team. If you would like to provide additional feedback, feel free to reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

replyContent: Hi Aaron! Thanks for the review and feedback. If you'd like to provide additional feedback, feel free to reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

replyContent: Hi Stephanie! Thanks for the review and feedback. Lack of phone storage is a frequent cause of crashes. We'd be happy to take a look at this and the other issues you are seeing. Please reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: Frustratingly glitchy. Inputted meals frequently disappear and many other issues. Good UI, but unfortunately doesnt work well at all.
replyContent: Hi Nick! Thanks for the review and feedback. We'd be happy to look into the issue you are experiencing. Please reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: Great app works well. Only negative is the database is a bit limited but that can be built over time. I never seem to get ads with free version and free version has everything I need. Happy.
replyContent: Hi Adrian! Thanks for the review and feedback. We're pleased to hear you like MyPlate.

replyContent: Hi William! Thanks for the review and feedback. If you have additional feedback you would like to provide, please reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

replyContent: Hi Ramanidharan! Thanks for the review and feedback. The MyPlate app tracks macros. If you are unsure of where to find this, please reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: As far as keeping track of your meals and macros, it's ok. Needs more weighing options for certain foods. On the exercise portion of the app, It seems very limited on the exercises available. Would be great if their was a wider selection aswell as able to input how many sets, weight etc instead of just duration
replyContent: Hi Ty! Thank you for your review and feedback. We will pass your comments to our product team. If there is additional feedback you would like to provide, please reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

replyContent: Hi Eileen! Thanks for the review. I'm sorry to hear you have forgotten your password. If you would like assistance logging in, simply reach out to us at support@livestrong.com and we'll get you sorted right away.

content: Counting calories sucks because counting sucks. This app has helped me plan meals and keep conveninet and accurate records of the foods I actually eat. I really appreciate being able to scan barcodes, manually enter nutrition facts, or use generic nutrition facts (like for a steak). replyContent: Hi William! Thank you for providing a review. We're pleased to hear the app is helping you to achieve your goals.

content: I just started counting and this is a really nice app to do so. It's completely free with optional perks to buy, which is really cool. I also really like how it tells you how much protein/carbs/fats you've eaten because it's a good measurement to tell if I need to eat more protein based foods or to cut on fatty foods. Thanks for the neat app!
replyContent: Hi there! Thank you for your review. We're pleased to hear you are enjoying the app.

content: I like this app because it tells me my actual fiber content which is what I am tracking. Super happy because it does the one thing I wanted to do is track my fiber.
replyContent: Hi Kelli! Thanks for the review. We're pleased to hear you are enjoying MyPlate.

content: The food log allows me to track everything. Has a wide selection for me to choose from. That's helpful when constantly in motion. I don't have to dig far to find. It also pops up the food I habitually eat. Quick, informative and easy.
I needed something simple without much learning curve. It's been perfect to track my calories and exercise daily without any trouble whatsoever.
replyContent: Hi Zach! Thank you for the review. We're glad you are enjoying MyPlate.

content: Have now used app for some time and am pleased with the results. I Do recommend for folks looking to control their nutrition. Replacement for another app so, initial thought is very favorable. Only time will tell. More later. Very happy with the App over time and definitely recommend for anyone needing to track their daily nutrition.
replyContent: Hi K. Thanks for the review. If you have any questions, please reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: I've been using this app for almost 8 years now. It had always been a great resource and easy to navigate. It's so easy to use, especially with the barcode feature. replyContent: Hi Nichelle! Thanks for the review and feedback. We're pleased to hear MyPlate is helping you to achieve your goals.

content: Use to use this app all the time when i was working out and dieting then got away from that now that ive started wanting 2 track my stuff again i redownloaded the app and went 2 log in and said my password was no good i do the oassword reset and dont recieve a email to do it even checked the spam folder and no email so cant use the app.
replyContent: Hi Jeffrey! Thanks for the review and feedback. You can use the app. Simply reach out to us at support@livestrong.com and we'll get you sorted right away.

content: Looks nice but for the first item I tried adding there was only one size (3 oz.). I wanted to add 8 oz. EDIT 2: removed a star for not showing micronutrients (vitamins/minerals)
replyContent: Hi Ryan! Thanks for the review and feedback. If you have additional feedback you would like to provide please reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: At first use in giving this 5 bc it makes adding new foods simple, the teaching interface is simple and fun to use, and you have to love the verified database of foods that allows you to easily find anything you've eaten
replyContent: Hi Tyler! Thank you for your review. We're pleased to hear you are enjoying MyPlate.

content: Overall, it's adequate, but it's not so great for tracking a Keto diet. The search algorithm for general meals and/or food items is confusing. I can do a search for sugar free ice cream bars but get 20 listings for cucumbers and ribeye steaks first before any ice cream products comes up.
replyContent: Hi Charlie! Thanks for the review and feedback. If you have additional feedback you would like to provide please reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: Love it!! Has nice list of already entered items that you can modify and you can enter your own. User friendly, easy to navigate and easy to read data. I'm very pleased. Thanks!!
replyContent: Hi Island Butterfly! Thank you for providing a review. We're so happy to hear you are enjoying MyPlate.

content: This is a solid app I've used off and on over many years. Originally, from a web page, this app has evolved to be something streamlined and efficient. Most items not listed have something very close, enough to find an appropriate calorie count. I've never even bothered to buy the paid version. Free works great!
replyContent: Hi Alli! Thank you so much for your review and continued support. We're glad you like the app.

content: I've had this app for half a year now and it's help alot when it came to my fitness journey I also love all the different options it has when it come to tracking calories and nutrition, best app I've found so far when it comes to tracking calories plus there's an awesome online community that offers lots of support
replyContent: Hi Sammie! Thank you for your review. We're happy to hear you are enjoying MyPlate.

content: Would've given 5 stars but there's an error in the app. Whenever I received a mail about my weekly progress it's different from my calorie intake according to the app. Example on Thursday I ate like 4200 calories according to app but only 3100 according to mail. Please fix this issue. Over-all a really great app.
replyContent: Hi Vibhav! Thank you for your review and feedback. We'd like to look into why some of your items did not sync. Please reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: An alpha sort for foods needed. Also differentiation between foods for breakfasts, lunches and dinners would also be useful. One year later: no changes made. App remains difficult to use.
replyContent: Hi Paula! We've forwarded your feedback to our developers. Thank you for taking out the time to send us your suggestions!

content: I like that it's easy to use and unlike other apps you don't have to upgrade to use the food calorie tracker. I been having a hard time losing weight and now I know why. replyContent: Hi Lola! Thank you for your review. We're happy to hear you are enjoying the app.

content: Been using this app for around 2 years. replyContent: Hi Nathaniel! Thank you for your review and feedback. I understand your frustration and have passed your comments to our product team. If you have additional feedback please reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: Super pleased, I am already loving this app! Naturally I have connected it to my Google Fit account, and get my calories added for me by scanning barcodes of my food! replyContent: Hi Kell! Thank you for your great review. We're happy to hear you are benefitting from MyPlate.

replyContent: Hi Dawna! Thanks for the review and feedback. We're sorry to hear you have experienced an issue with the app. Please reach out to us at support@livestrong.com so we may look into this further.

content: Needs improvement. The previous app I use had no problem identifying all the food I input booth manually and thru bar code reader. This one knows only 3 out of ten I input. I hope they put more effort into adding more food items in their database. 3 stars for now.
replyContent: Hi Michael! MyPlate uses a third-party food database, which is a collection of listings from the USDA and food manufacturers. content: Brilliant app! Would definitely change a few things about the layout and add an option to browse my foods without being in the adding menu. This app is making my bulk a success.
replyContent: Hi John! Thank you so much for your review. We're happy to hear MyPlate is helping you to achieve your goals.

replyContent: Hi Alex! Thank you for your review and feedback. If you have any questions regarding the app, feel free to reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

replyContent: Hi Karen! Thanks for the review and feedback. We received your message, reset your password, and you confirmed that you are now able to login. Please let us know if we can assist with anything else.

content: Excellent App. Must be pretty accurate with the calories as has worked for losing weight. Scans more Barcodes than other couple of apps I've tried. content: I enjoy using this app to keep track of my calorie intake and progress. I keep min linked to my Google fit so I can also see my daily net calories. content: I used the app to lose 35 pounds. I learned a lot about food and what's in it. replyContent: Hi there! Thank you for your review. We're pleased to hear MyPlate has helped you to achieve your goals.

content: I like my plate because it allows you to keep track of your calories and all the things that you put into your mouth. replyContent: Hi Martha! Thanks for that awesome review. We're happy to hear MyPlate has been so helpful.

content: This app is great! Have been able to find all foods and food brands through the search feature...Tracks calories, water, and activity! Easy to use! Its been a great help.

content: Love this app. I've tried so many times to lose weight and get to a healthier BMI. Once I used the MyPlate app, I was able to lose 42 pounds with its user friendly interface and features.

content: Much better than myfitnesspal. The ads are minimal and uninvasive, the UI is uncluttered and responsive, AND you can count your macros without having to buy the premium version. Great app.

content: This is a great app for anyone looking to lose weight. Easy to extreme diet plans. I set extreme and allowed myself to go slightly over at times of desperation and still lost 40lbs. Almost to my goal weight and plan to keep using it to maintain a healthy lifestyle. A+ Thank you.

content: A bit clumsy in terms of food names (chobani oat milk is nutritionally correct, but labeled as yogurt). And recent foods don't save the quantity, so if you eat the same thing every day, you'll have to adjust the amount every day. Overall good and has all the food I typically eat.

content: This is a wonderful app. The only problem is, that the food database is a little lacking and the scanner function is weak. Otherwise the system is very easy to use and does a great job with tracking and nutrition.
replyContent: Hi BobJane! Thank you for your review and feedback. If you are unable to find the food you are looking for in the database we encourage you to create a custom food.

content: The overwhelming majority of tracking options are volumetric. Many options differ by a large degree from printed nutrition facts. replyContent: Hi Mitchell! We are aware of, and working to correct, the issue of some measurements not being available. To manually add a food tap on the blue plus sign. content: Please stop lying! As I said in my earlier review, I reached out to support for help and once their troubleshooting failed to fix the problem they DISAPPEARED without a trace and the problem was never resolved! It's bad that this app stopped working after years of me wasting my time with it, but now I'm getting smart @ss remarks from the developer over me letting people know I did not receive help from support. I don't recommend this app to anyone.
replyContent: Hi Peter! Thanks for the review and feedback. As you are aware, support replied to your requests within two business days and did not disappear. If you have additional questions, we are more than happy to help. For further assistance, please respond to any of our replies.

content: App has started to crash on me now. Also as others have said you need to add the weightloss common foods to favourites with a generic accepted calorie like ch breast, fish, salad, porridge, apple, banana, grapes.. content: It hardly has any of the food that I scan the barcodes of. The two redeeming features are: 1. The app looks great. 2. It syncs with my Google Fit app.
replyContent: Hi Teivel! MyPlate uses a comprehensive third-party food database, Nutritionix, which is a collection of listings from the USDA and food manufacturers. content: User added calories are so often obvious and verifiable lies. replyContent: Hi Keith! Thanks for the review. Our devs are working to resolve the issue of some measurements not being available on items. We use a comprehensive third-party database, Nutritionix, which is a collection of listings from the USDA and food manufacturers. Unfortunately, we're not able to add or remove items from this database.

content: Very limited food options to be able to effectively track caloric intake. It doesn't allow me to track water intake. If the app has a water tracking feature, then it's not user friendly as I couldn't locate it in the 3 days I had it.

content: Really loved this app but now it's not working at all. :( I was using it and it suddenly stopped showing search results. Tried uninstalling and reinstalling and it did not work still. Great community and great app. Just hope it gets fixed...
replyContent: Hi Lorraine! Thanks for the review and feedback. Because this is the only report we have received of this, the issue is most likely with your device. We'd be happy to help you troubleshoot this. Please reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: Honestly, the best diet tracker i could find out of all of them. Doesnt bombard you with premium ads, gives you the features necessary to complete your diet without nagging at you for premium, its easy to use, gives you useful information on your diet. I plan on using this for a while.
replyContent: Hi Kyle! Thank you for your review. We're pleased to hear you are enjoying MyPlate.

content: Most foods are available on app... or at least I can use something as a close option. Otherwise I'd give 5 stars. I like knowing the carb and protein content.
