replyContent: Hi there! Thank you for your review and feedback. If you are unable to find a food you are looking for, you can create a custom food in the app. If you have any questions feel free to reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: This app keeps closing randomly. That is the one flaw. I used this app years ago to track my food, water, & activity abs was happy that it is still available! It's very user friendly. I love the detail & breakdown of nutrients. It connects to my fitness app to help track calories burned, also.
replyContent: Hi Jennifer! Thanks for the review and feedback. We're sorry to hear you are experiencing issues with the app closing. Please try deleting and reinstalling the app. If you continue to experience this, please reach out to us at support@livestrong.com. We'd be happy to look into this.

content: This app works quite well as a basic tracker for calories and nutrition consumption. Helping me a lot with my fitness and weight loss goals, doesn't push in any way just acts as a tracker. Bar code scanner works great and finding foods isn't difficult at all.
replyContent: Hi Lolly! We appreciate you taking the time to provide a review. We're pleased to hear you are enjoying MyPlate.

content: Having to add foods was difficult. If I opened another window to obtain the nutrition info, MyPlate would make me start all over. Add the name, look up the calories and re-enter everything again. Nit sure why i havr to start over everytime I need to open a window . I'm a huge fan of Livestrong but this fell short of my expecations.
replyContent: Hi Theresa! Thank you for your review and feedback. We will be releasing a fix for this issue in the coming days. If you have any questions, please reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: Easy interface. Can set up my own foods. Has a surprisingly broad calorie search window. I simply use it to track my calorie so I can't say much about some other options.
replyContent: Hi Blong! Thanks for the review. We're glad you like the app.

content: It's been pretty great so far. It wasn't mostly free it would be a 1 star. I sometimes have difficulty finding a few foods but you can get around that with its features such as the barcode scanner and putting in the calories manually.
replyContent: Hi Nathan! Thank you for your review and feedback. We're glad you like the app. If there is any additional feedback you would like to provide, feel free to contact us at support@livestrong.com.

content: Looking for app that allows me to track vitamins for my deficiencies while loosing weight. This only allows proteins, carbs, fats. Doesnt fit my needs. This was easy to use, especially barcode scanner.
replyContent: Hi there! Thank you so much for your review and feedback. If you have any questions regarding the app or further feedback you'd like to provide, please reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: Google Fit Sync Issues, after an update the sync features aren't working on my Android based phone. It just appears to be loading indefinitely. Fix this and my review will go back up to 5 stars. Fixed!
replyContent: Hi Dotti! Our team is working on a fix for this issue right now! Google has made a change to their privacy policy. Our team is working to reconcile this as quickly as possible. Please reach out to us at support@livestrong.com so we can notify you as soon as it is resolved.

content: Using the android version of this app, I have the same problem as other users where the app loses all of the data I put into it whenever I change timezones. Seeing that I travel alot for work, this makes it difficult to track things during travel days. Hopefully they are able to fix this, because otherwise the app works pretty well.
replyContent: Hi Tim! Thank you for your review and feedback. Our team is aware of the issue and working to resolve it. We appreciate your patience as our devs diagnose and correct the issue.

content: App worked for a bit, then started randomly crashing. Even restarting my device and reloading the app didn't help. Lost almost a month of tracked meals and exercise.
replyContent: Hi Rae! Thanks for the review and feedback. Please delete the app and reinstall. If you continue to experience any issues, we're happy to help. You can always reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: Been using for years because it's easy to use but after phone system upgrade cannot get it to sync with Google Fit. Shouldn't have two spend 30+ minutes to get to get it to sync. Disappointed. Will consider other apps for food tracking.
replyContent: Hi Sherry! Thanks for the review. We appreciate your support. Our team is working on a fix for this issue right now! Google has made a change to their privacy policy. Our team is working to reconcile this as quickly as possible. Please reach out to us at support@livestrong.com so we can notify you as soon as it is resolved.

content: This app deletes my recorded data every time I change time zones, which happens often. I paid over $40, it is an absolute waste. I love that I can scan barcodes for food, but it is pointless if it deletes my data.
replyContent: Hi Kate! We're sorry to hear of the difficulties you have encountered. Please reach out to us at support@livestrong.com so we may assist you directly. Thank you.

content: Excellent app with a few issues. The pros are being able to combine diet and exercise data in an easy way to keep track of progress. The cons are the US-centric measures (converting from cups to grams is tedious), the occasional dodgy data (raw aubergines do not have 200 kcal!!) and most seriously the fact that when one adds exercises, thus increasing the food calories to eat, the number of grams of carbs/protein/fat do not also increase as they should. Please fix this, developers! 😊
replyContent: Hi Peter! Thanks for the review and feedback. I have passed your comments to our product team. If you have any questions or additional feedback, please reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: Its premium plans include diet recommendations and showing macros counts in percentages, which is the only function I was hoping to have in the free feature list. Since that's not the case, its just like any other app like healthify me.
replyContent: Hi Lakshmi! Thanks for the review and feedback. If you have any additional feedback you would like to provide, feel free to reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: I can find most foods but there are still a lot that have to be entered. An example is any Freshly Meal and Arbonne products missing or incorrect. Otherwise very helpful and easy to use.
replyContent: Hi there! Thanks for the review. MyPlate uses a third-party food database, Nutritionix, which is a collection of listings from the USDA and some food manufacturers. Unfortunately, we're not able to add or remove items from this database. If the item you'd like to track is not in our database, we recommend creating a custom food entry in the app.

content: Tried searching for several brands of food, no records found, just generic guesses for generic equivalents. It would be too much work to create new foods every meal every day. Other apps like My Fitness Pal and Lose It have even obscure brands most of the time, though there's way too many duplicates. I'll take my chances with the latter though, better too much than not enough.
replyContent: Hi ZaCloud! Thanks for the review and feedback. MyPlate uses a third-party food database, which is a collection of listings from the USDA and some food manufacturers. Unfortunately, we're not able to add or remove items from this database as it is managed by Nutritionix. If you have any questions reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: This is a great app. It has a pretty exhaustive list of foods that you can select and track, plus a place to create your own foods. It keeps track of things you eat regularly for easy tracking. One negative thing: the calorie counts of many foods listed are wrong (off just a bit from what the app has "verified" vs what it actually says on the food item for calories), but there is an "quick add calories" tab so you can easily adjust the calories for accurate tracking.
replyContent: Hi Kathy! Thank you for the review and feedback. MyPlate uses a third-party food database, which is a collection of listings from the USDA and some food manufacturers. Unfortunately, we're not able to add or remove items from this database as it is managed by Nutritionix. Your workaround is a smart way to correct this until the entry is updated.

content: Love this app! Very helpful...I have lost 7 lbs since using it, it's motivating me each time I log in. You can track your weight, carbs, proteins, fats, excercise, and water intake. If you like group accountability, this app provides that help too...you have a community of people are going through the same things as you! I was floundering for a long while, and this app has really helped me!
replyContent: Hi L M! Thank you for taking the time to leave a review. Congratulations on your progress. We're happy to hear that MyPlate's tools and Community have helped you on your way.

content: To the developer: with 13 trackers you are definitely HARVESTING data. You can lie about it the trackers tell the whole story. They are easy to look up and see what they do. 13 trackers. really.... You need to add that many to your app. You really need Facebook trackers. Unexceptable. This app is data HARVESTING on a while new scale
replyContent: Hi there! The MyPlate app does not harvest data. When you login to the app using Facebook, MyPlate needs to validate your account using your Facebook. You do not have to use Facebook login; simply create a username and password. I apologize for your confusion. If you have additional questions feel free to reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: There should also be an options to see our "Favourites" that the app knows we eat a lot of but doesn't allow us access to. Also the search engine is massively flawed. You can look up a product, have their engine pop up the exact item you're looking for then when you hit search, comes up with completely different foods. How do you get Cookies with Chewy bar?
replyContent: Hi Casey! Thank you for your review and feedback. I will pass your comments to our product team. If you have any questions or additional feedback, feel free to reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: Downloaded and deleted countless excercise apps, and this is one of the few that Ive actually bothered to keep around. The step tracker challenges are a great motivator to get up and keep trying for that extra mile. I am sore as can be but havent felt this good in a bit.
replyContent: Hi Constance! Thank you for providing a review. We're glad you are enjoying MyPlate.

content: Worth the Gold subscription. Got it for the whole year. Records total and per meal macros and calories, keeps history of food diary and water intake. Only feature that I'd like to see added is the option to add what time food was eaten and for a glucose and blood pressure log. Nice app, thanks!
replyContent: Hi Happy Feet! We truly appreciate you taking the time to leave a review. I have passed your comments on to our Product Team. If you have additional suggestions, feel free to reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: This app is great! Though I've found due to my weird dietary restrictions that it didn't have all the foods I eat in their food library. I have to enter them manually, and if you change tabs (to check the calculator I use to figure calories, fat, etc) it erases everything you've inputted and you have to start again. If that wasn't the case I'd use this app more.
replyContent: Hi Cara! Thank you for your review and feedback. I'm happy to say our team will soon be addressing the erasure issue you have described. If you have any questions or additional feedback, please reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: I love using this app for tracking my meals and exercise. The community is awesome! I'm thankful for all of the awesome members too. The Admins are so helpful, they keep a good watch on the posts for any unsafe suggestions, and offering helpful information on healthy eating habits for everyone, as well as keeping an eye out for the teens/young adults ensuring that they are following safe & healthy eating/exercise patterns for their still growing bodies.
replyContent: Hi Georgia! We appreciate you leaving a review. We're so glad you're enjoying utilizing the app and Community.

content: This app is the best one I've used for tracking food and I have tried them all. The free version tracks food really well with many options for food options and imperial and metric units and tracks fat/protien/carbs and the paid version tracks protien and sugars and other micronutrients. One of my favorites. Also it does sync up woth google fit and others.
replyContent: Hi Styx! We appreciate you leaving a review. We're happy to hear you like the app.

content: it's okay. sometimes there's problems with syncing the google fit exercise but other than that it's alright. until they made it so the custom calorie thing doesn't go below 1200. like i know what i'm doing bestie mind your business lmao. so that's annoying but other than that it works ig. there's better apps but there's also worse ones. easy to use and stuff
replyContent: Hi John! For safety reasons, 1200 calories per day is the minimum caloric goal allowed by the app. This is commonly considered the lowest number of calories a person can eat in a day without doctor supervision. Since most of our users do not check with a doctor before taking on such a goal we implemented this as a safety feature.

content: Great app, and run by people who seem to actually care, and who motivate without being patronising. Unfortunately the scanner doesn't work for me, which is disappointing. Otherwise it would be 5 stars.
replyContent: Hi Natascha! Thank you for your review and feedback. I have passed your comments to our product team. If have any additional feedback, feel free to reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: Great app for tracking my calories. I like that my google fit data feeds into the app. I also like how easy it is to input my meals. The weekly summary email is helpful as well!
replyContent: Hi Lisa! Thank you for leaving a review. We're glad the app has been able to help.

content: Works great. Scanner of items for nutrition info makes things quick, but the search function is easy to use as well. Tracks activity (steps) from GoogleFit too ,which is a plus, but not manually entered activity in Fit, so I have to do double entry. Wish it had a recipe nutritional calculator built in or could connect to a recipe calculator as I make many homemade recipes. Just by tracking calories for a month, I've lost 12 lbs.
replyContent: Hi Jarrod! We appreciate your review and feedback. We're happy to hear you like MyPlate. If you have any questions, please reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: Very basic, good, non gendered app. I used it to gain weight. It was hard to find an app not catered to only one gender and mainly aimed at losing weight. Could use more free features and cheaper pay options, but it's very good for the basics i needed
replyContent: Hi Jordan! We appreciate your review and feedback. We're glad to hear the app is working well for you.

content: U love it. Super easy to use, easy to navigate, track. You can track pretty much anything to uneed to from excercise to what you've eaten. It even has something that you can basically google what you've eaten within the app. Overall it's just very good. Can't find anything wrong with it. ALSO THERE ARE NO ADDS
replyContent: Hi Anna! Thank you so much for your review. We're pleased to hear you are enjoying the app.

content: Works well! Easy to use and has made me aware of how many calories I was eating from bad food choices. In a little over 2 months I have lost 9lbs and 1 inch from my waist by simply eating better. I recommend!
replyContent: Hi Travis! Thank you for the review and congratulations on your success. If you have any questions regarding the app, don't hesitate to reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: Sometimes the database data on nutrients is not matching the tag on the product. Wish there was a way to edit the nutrients data when and after adding. Also, wish there was a way to express the quantity in arbitrary units, as opposed to the proportion of the fixed serving sizes. Finally, wish there were a way to import burned calories directly from FitBit.
replyContent: Hi Bakhtiyar! We appreciate you leaving a review and feedback. Your comments have been passed to our Product Team. If you have additional feedback or questions, please reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: Very neutral language that doesn't guilt trip. Helps track a bunch of things, including water intake, exercise, weight, macros and micros. I do wish the water tracking was a little more expensive as it only lets you increase how much you drank in 8, 16, & 32 oz. Also has a community for support and questions. One of the best lifestyle trackers I've ever used, and I've been trying for a decade to stay healthy!
replyContent: Hi Louca! Thank you for your amazing review. We appreciate your feedback and are glad to be a part of your health journey.

content: Missed Potential - But Serves the Purpose... Lowering my rating from 4 to 3, as the developer/company really isn't adding much needed features, like editing meal names, etc. Such an easy addition, but the lack of it has really ruined the experience for me. A lot of other no-brainsers missing, as well, which come to light after usage. Still, it does what it sets out to do and usually well. That said, will likely start looking for a new tracker soon.
replyContent: Hi Andrew! Thanks for the review and feedback. I have passed your comments to our product team. If you have additional feedback you would like to provide, please reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: I like the interface but if you want to add food via the barcode, be aware that 80% of the time, though the right product will come up, most of the values are wrong. From serving size, calories and macros. I expect to manually enter some things but not things that are supposedly in the database.
replyContent: Hi Nick! Thank you for the review and feedback. MyPlate uses a comprehensive third-party food database, Nutritionix, which is a collection of listings from the USDA and some food manufacturers. Unfortunately, we're not able to add or remove items from this database. If you have any questions please contact us at support@livestrong.com.

content: It's a really great app but I would appreciate some options added to the community for gaining weight as well, not just losing it. Then it will be perfect and fit for everybody. Gaining weight isn't the only struggle people have. I am underweight and want more options and tips since it is harder to find them than it is for weight loss. If more weight gain people grouped together, we could give tips like everyone else does. It's really hard to reach my goals without this feature
replyContent: Hi there! We appreciate your review and feedback. I think a Community forum focused on weight gain is a great idea. I have passed your comments on to our product team. If you have additional feedback, please reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: Lacking a lot of features, lacking a lot of items in search. I can't manually add nutritional information which means it's not calculating my home made meals properly. I have to try and find what's closest :(
replyContent: Hi Meg! Thanks for the review and feedback. To create a Custom Food tap on the blue plus sign, tap the meal you'd like to track the custom food to tap "My Food", scroll to the bottom of the page and "Create A New Food". If you have any questions, please reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: The help I needed. I didn't realize how many calories I was consuming. I was WAY OFF! I wanted to get healthy the right way. I picked the extreme option on my calorie reduction but it honestly doesn't feel extream. One month in and I've lost 11lbs! I have not been able to use the community tab though. It crashes the app everytime.
replyContent: Hi there! Thanks for the review and feedback. Regarding the crash you experienced, please delete and reinstall the app. If this does not resolve the issue, please reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: Super handy tool. I love how you can add your own meals and foods. I can't figure out how to access the meals from my profile (vs only having access when actually adding a meal).
replyContent: Hi Leslie! Thanks for the review and feedback. Custom meals do need to be viewed within a meal period. If you have any questions, don't hesitate to reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: Looks nice but lacks features. Lacks simple things like calories for "a teaspoon of sugar" also the barcode scanner hasnt found a single barcode I have tried so far so I tediously have to enter every single food item. Lacks feature to edit a food once added leading to redundent data entry if you make a mistake.
replyContent: Hi Declan! Thank you for the review and feedback. We're sorry to hear you have experienced issues with the app. We'd be happy to troubleshoot this. Please reach out to us at support@livestrong.com so we can get more information.

content: This is very good for a free app. I've used my fitness pal for years and decided I didn't want to pay those rates anymore. The only thing that needs some improving is the search function. I wish there were more option in the library to choose from and that there were more accurate measuring for each food.
replyContent: Hi Devin! Thanks for the review and feedback. I've passed your comments to our product team. Our team is currently working on a fix for the missing measurement options. If you have any questions or additional feedback, please reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: The MyPlate app has been easy and straight forward for me to count calories for the past month. Access to the message boards are also great for finding meal inspiration, sharing your goals, and asking questions. I would definitely recommend this app to people just starting their journey into a healthier lifestyle. This is a great tool to supplement your research into finding what nutrition (such as types of food, macro nutrients, minimum/maximum daily calories to eat) works for you.
replyContent: Hi K Lane! Thank you for your great review. We happy to hear you are enjoying the MyPlate app.

content: Simplier than MyFitnessPal, nice interface. Not as robust with food library or barcode scanning, and occasionally forgots a meal that I enter into it, but overall not bad. Glad I made the switch.
replyContent: Hi Steve! Thank you for the review and feedback. We'd be happy to look into the logging issue you're seeing. Feel free to reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: Great experience so far. I can track how I want, which is awesome. And I must say...the amount of things to track under "walking" is so hilariously inclusive. Take a look!
replyContent: Hi Dennis! We appreciate you leaving a review. We're happy to hear you are enjoying the app.

content: This is great to count my calories after going off the nutrisystem diet, but the scanner is very sketchy and doesnt get the correct info most the time, but typing in the brand of food manually is the correct info, that would be my only complaint, fix scanner and get percise food nutrition contents, otherwise excellent app. Thank you guys
replyContent: Hi Joel! Thank you for your review and feedback. We've passed your comments to our development team. If you have any questions or would like to give additional feedback, feel free to reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: Hard to start with print too light to read. But stayed with it until memorized the titles. Use it all day. Infinitely valuable for my ratios and to lesser extent calorie count. Thank you.
replyContent: Hi there! Thank you for the review and feedback. I'm glad you are enjoying the app and will pass your comments on to our Product Team.

content: It does what it needs to do for me. Not too much clutter. I've lost 30 lbs with it in 6 months. There is an issue with syncing the data. I moved to a new phone and no matter what I try the progress only goes back about 3 months though the web site shows all 6 months.
replyContent: Hi there! Thank you for the review and feed back. Congratulations on your success.

content: The interface is simple, but their database is outdated, I can't find most of the foods I eat. This app is a bad imitation of Myfitnesspal. It doesn't have to option to creat a meal right from your foods.
replyContent: Hi Stan! MyPlate uses a third-party food database which is a collection of listings from the USDA and food manufacturers. We're unable to add or remove items from the database. To create a meal select Breakfast, Lunch, Dinner, or Snack, and then tap "My Meals". Select "Create a New Meal" and enter the foods you would like to group together.

content: It works well. But today it showed something that said "Add Breakfast from Yesterday" and I clicked on it. Which worked great. Only it's useless to me because I didn't eat that breakfast today. And I don't know how to edit that. So because I pushed something I'll have to calculate my protein and calories by hand today, which isn't convenient at all.
replyContent: Hi there! To delete an item navigate to the "Food Diary" on the main app page. Tap on the meal period you want to edit. On the next page select the item you wish to delete. Scroll to the bottom of the entry and tap "Delete This Entry". If you have any other questions, feel free to reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: App could be better. Does not have a cardio option when inputting exercise. No daily reminders. Cant put in much info about your workout schedule. And now there are so many unnecessary ads. It cant tell the good carbs from bad, or good fats from bad if your micro and macro counting. But I love that you can scan your foods; makes for easy entry for your food dairy. The community online is great as well. I wish it could synch to my phone to such with my calories burned from workouts
replyContent: Hi Jemmelia! You can search for cardio and other exercises to track by tapping "Exercise" from the Diary page of the app. Type the exercise you are looking for in the search bar. "Good" fats, carbs, etc., are subjective. As such we are not able to make such distinctions. If you have additional questions reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: MyPlate gets the job done. And the minimalist UI is nice (especially when compared to MFP's excessively cluttered one). But it's also lacking some of the things that make apps like MFP so nice to use, like the ability to create a meal with a serving count; the ability to add a meal to your day as a meal, and not just as a substitute for five+ other foods. So, as it is now, it's pretty good. But I'd like to see MyPlate improve in the future.
replyContent: Hi Peter! We appreciate your review and feedback. I have passed your feedback to our product team. If you have additional comments or recommendations, please let us know. You can reach us at support@livestrong.com.

content: This app helped me stay accountable for every single bit of food that I put into my mouth. Utilizing this app along with other things, I was able to lose 40+ pounds in about 6-7 months. I absolutely recommend it for anyone who is serious about getting healthy and wanting to lose weight.
replyContent: Hi Audrey! Congratulations on your success and thank you for the review. We appreciate your support.

content: I like the app, but for beginner not intuitive on how to add food. I finally found help and found how to scan package bar codes but not always correct and cannot edit values or add items without bar code. Weekly summary does not match in app calorie value. Will not sync with Google Fit even tough it is turned on in both apps. Crashed sometimes when going between functions.
replyContent: Hi Earl! Thanks for the review and feedback. This guide will show you how to add food without the barcode and more: https://www.livestrong.com/slideshow/1011365-use-livestrongs-myplate-calorie-tracker-app-android/ If you have questions regarding the summary, connecting Fit, or anything else please reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: The app is everything I need but I'm really really hoping for some bug fixes very soon. If you travel between time zones for work your entries won't show up on the app unless you sign out and sign back in, and when you do that, your Google fit exercises for the day will double and then double again if you try to delete them. The interface is simple and easy to use, but please, please, please fix the bugs soon.
replyContent: Hi Hunter! Thank you for your review and feedback. I have passed your comments to our Product Team. If you have any questions or additional feedback, please reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: This is a great app so far. Your food database surpassed my expectations in scale and variety. However, I can't give 5 stars because the search function is not intuitive. Entering "orange" populates foods that are flavored orange, rather than the fruit. Playing around with the wording got me what I was looking for, but perhaps you can improve your search results functionality to prioritize the most common searches.
replyContent: Hi Carissa! Thank you for the review and feedback. I've passed your comments to our Product Team. If you have additional suggestions feel free to share them with us at support@livestrong.com.

content: Good app, however, it's missing the functionality of automatically converting measurements. For example, if I scan a product, it will give the nutrition facts for 1 serving and then I need to enter the amounts of serving I am eating. It would be nice to tell the app that I'm using 50g or 1/2 cup of the product instead of figuring outside the app, for example, how much is 50g of a 30g serving (1.66 serving) or 1/2 cup of a 1/3 cup serving. This should all be done within the app.
replyContent: Hi Jean! Thank you for the review and feedback. This is something our developers are currently working to address. If you have any questions, please reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: Easy app to use. I am just returning from a few years off. I was able to use exercise and tracking foods eaten to lose 100 pounds and holding. Now another begining for the next goal.
replyContent: Hi Mae! Thank you for leaving a review. Congratulations on your amazing achievement.

content: Decent App. Good user interface, but the calorie total is off by about 200 calories if you're trying to keep track of Macros too. Food data entries seem inaccurate, so you may want to add your own.
replyContent: Hi Marcus! Thank you for your review and feedback. MyPlate uses a comprehensive third-party food database, which is a collection of listings from the USDA and some food manufacturers. Unfortunately, we're not able to add or remove items from this database as it is managed by Nutritionix.

content: I really am disappointed that I spent $ on this ap. There isn't much more available in the paid version than the free version. (It's basically a food and weight log.) I realized I made a mistake the minute I bought it.  I immediately searched to see where I could cancel it. (Not easy to do). I was surprised to find that I can not cancel it and get a refund. I purchased it for 1 year. I'm confused over whose policy doesn't offer the refund..  is it Googlepay or livestrong?
replyContent: Hi Angela. Thanks for the review. You can cancel your subscription in the Google Play Store. If you do not want to do this, please reach out to us at support@livestrong.com. We're happy to take care of it for you.

content: I liked the app until now. I scanned a barcode but the result was no food found. So I tried to add the food manually. No good. I know both options worked before but not anymore. Any ideas? Works great again. Thanks for the update.
replyContent: Hi Gary! Thanks for the review. Yesterday evening we encountered an issue that has since been resolved. We're sorry you were negatively impacted. If you experience any other issues, please reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: I've tried like 20 apps and this one suits me most. Nice easy front page to add stuff on the go. It's not all flashy and confusing. I'm using the basic version. Would be good if you can import Samsung health data.. I'd been using that for 2 years.. I cba manually updating. I guess food listings will improve over time. Also consider adding caffeine intake or protein shake intake. And sleep record.
replyContent: Hi Kashif! Thanks for the review and feedback. Currently the MyPlate app syncs with the Google Fit app and can import data from the devices you sync to Google Fit. If you have any questions feel free to reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: MyPlate has helped me keep a positive perspective on what I'm really putting in my body. I enjoy using the charts and getting my weekly updates on how well I've done. MyPlate app is easy-to-use and I would recommend it to anyone.
replyContent: Hi Jesica! Thanks for the review. We appreciate your support.

content: EDIT: Thank you so much for the update! The app is back up and running, haven't had any problems since my first review! [FIRST REVIEW] Great app, but it frequently stops working at the most inconvenient times. For example right now, the food data base is down. Any search will show no results, even something as generic as pizza or burgers. It's very frustrating... I still like the app and I do recommend it, but it has a lot of problems that have not been addressed for years.
replyContent: Hi Peter! Thanks for the review. Yesterday evening we encountered an issue that has since been resolved. We're sorry you were negatively impacted. If you experience any other issues, please reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: Has a very annoying bug where if you log a group of foods using a meal from the my meals tab, and then try to delete one of the ingredients, it looks like it's deleted at first but if you exit or delete another ingredient it comes back. Makes it impossible to delete food out of a meal because when one gets deleted another just pops back up. This happens randomly and there's no way of fixing it, force stopping the app, resetting phone, none of it works.
replyContent: Hi Austin! Thanks for the review and feedback. This is a unique issue. We'd like to look into what you are experiencing. You can contact us at support@livestrong.com.

content: This app started out really helpful and it was nice that it had an online counterpart so I could still access it without my phone. However, over the last few days it's been really slow to load, it won't let me add custom food, and it errors out frequently. I've decided to uninstall it, as I can't get the website to work either, so what's the point in keeping it if I can't use it to keep track of my food, exercise, etc. I've since moved back to the Fitbit app, where it's likely I'll stay.
replyContent: Hi Brittany! Thanks for the review. Yesterday evening we encountered an issue that has since been resolved. We're sorry you were negatively impacted. If you experience any other issues, please reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: Great app, once you get used to it. Runs smoothly, and offers flexibility with the quick calorie adder. I do wish there was entry modes to track caffeine, cigarettes, and prescriptions (a reminder function with a checklist would be stellar) would seal the deal
replyContent: Hi there! Thank you for the review and feedback. If you have any other great ideas, we're happy to hear them. Please contact us at support@livestrong.com.

content: The app was good at the beginning but now it seems to have gotten all buggy and when I try to add a meal it duplicates entries and calories and when I try to delete ingredients it seems to just bring ingredients back that I had just deleted. I now can't use it any more, which is frustrating...
replyContent: Hi Sara! Thanks for the review. This is a unique problem that we'd like to take a closer look at. Please reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: The best app for weight loss. I had a gastric sleeve last year so it's important for me to watch what I'm eating. Being able to see what nutrients I'm putting in my body, as well as what I'm burning, has been the biggest motivator for my weight loss. 63lbs down! This is the best app I have on my phone. Give it a shot! It's free! It's also from one of the most reputable brands online (in my opinion)! Thank you for this amazing app.
replyContent: Hi Angelica! Thank you for that amazing review. We're happy to be a part of your fitness journey.

content: I like it for tracking my food. Other than that it's not super user friendly on the free version. Perhaps it gets better if you subscribe. It is faster to load my food than in my Samsung health app.
replyContent: Hi Lyn! We appreciate your review and feedback. We'd like to know what you are having trouble with. You can contact us directly at support@livestrong.com. Thank you.

content: Overall the app is awesome, I really like that it shows the macros, that's why I use it over other apps. Pretty easy to navigate, has a decent amount of common foods already programmed in.
replyContent: Hi Morgan! Thanks for the review. We're glad you're enjoying the app.

content: July 2020 - I have the free version. I am so glad to finally find a tracker that calculates bmr and uses that, exercise and weight loss goals to calculate calorie budgets. This is the only method that has ever worked for me. Also, the food lists look good. You can find what you want without having to search through a bunch of crowdsourced debris. Edit Jan 2021 - I upgraded to the gold version and it didn't add much functionality or content, other than removing ads. Maybe do more challenges?
replyContent: Hi there! We appreciate you leaving a review and feedback. If you have any questions regarding the MyPlate app features, please reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: Great. Free, no intrusive ads. You can monitor exercises, calories, protein, fats and carbs. If you want more you can upgrade but you get a decent amount for free.
replyContent: Hi there! Thanks you for the review. We're pleased to hear you are enjoying the MyPlate app. If you have any questions regarding the app, feel free to reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: Great for tracking foods, calories, protein, carbs, and sugar. I wish more foods could be stored and available to recall, now you need to get te bar code and scan it versus recalling from prior foods scanned.
replyContent: Hi Brad! We appreciate your review and feedback. Recently eaten foods will appear under the Recent tab for the meal period in which they were previously tracked. If you have any questions, feel free to reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: Super easy to follow! Adjust daily calorie goals & percentages for protein, fat, and carbs. Scan option makes it easy to find most foods, can manually add foods in the portions you eat, and can create meals. I like to prep so I like that I can make a pot of anything, add all the ingredients in the app, then break out my portions since sometimes I might get 4 portions and other meals I get more. I suggest this app to literally ALL of my friends! Can add exercise, water, pair with devices, etc.
replyContent: Hi Autumn! Thank you so much for the review. We appreciate your support.

content: I love the tracker. My only complaints are that there's is no time stamp. I want to know when I ate, as I try to eat only every two or three hours. Also, I would like the opportunity to have ALL of the food I scanned remembered and in a list that could be sorted by date and/or alphabetically.
replyContent: Hi Shane! Thanks for the review and feedback. I've passed your comments on to our development team. If you have any additional suggestions, feel free to reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: been using myplate for more than a decade. app is mostly good. however, i have to constantly clear the data because it doesn't always track what i record. I'll track a meal, then when i check again later, parts of what i tracked are missing. a bit frustrating.
replyContent: Hi Daniel! Thanks for the review. We'd like to take a look at what you're experiencing. Please reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: I always lose when I use this app. I wish there was a better way to share my meal info. Roommate makes a meal, but can't share the final nutritional info after it is calculated from the recipe. Other than that I love this app.
replyContent: Hi there! Thanks for your review and feedback. I've passed your comments on to our devs. If you have any questions regarding the app, feel free to reach out at support@livestrong.com.

content: I was able to lose 30 lbs with the help of this app. It's really easy to track calories and learn portion control with MyPlate. It's definitely helpful for working towards a healthier lifestyle!
replyContent: Hi Wren! Thanks for the review and congratulations on your success. We're happy to be a part of your fitness journey.

content: Food searches are difficult and quantity sizes aren't flexible enough. For example, a search for raisins required scrolling through a long list of prepared products to get to the item. Then when I found it, the serving sizes didn't accommodate my need to add 1 teaspoon of raisins. I had to count the raisins in a tsp., then calculate the % for a 50 count serving size.
replyContent: Hi Trisha! Thanks for the review and feedback. Our team is aware of an issue with grams and other measurement units not being displayed as a serving size option. The team is working on a fix for this issue. If you have any questions, you can contact us at support@livestrong.com.

content: Excellent app. Huge help in controlling my eating habits and meeting my goals. Easy interface and readout. Only complaint is my My Food list isn't sortable so sometimes I have to scroll really far down to find a food item.
replyContent: Hi Mylurian! We appreciate your review and feedback. We have passed your comments on to our developers. Thank you.

content: Among all the fitness/diet tracking apps that I have tried, this one is the best as I can manually input the values from my local food. I hope you'll add more features in your future updates. Also fix some sync bugs in google fit app. It would be best also if you allow 3rd party app sync and external devices such as a smart watch to work in your app. Lastly, please lower your premium fee as I am still a student and can't afford the overpriced subscription.
replyContent: Hi Bonjuvy! Thanks for your review and feedback. If you have any questions regarding the app, please feel free to reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: A great free app which had made it easy for me to loose over 3 stone in weight. It focuses my mind on what I should be eating and how many wasted calories there are in some foods. By making simple changes, uping my protein and reducing my consumption of carbs and fat it has really helped me. I have had so many people ask how I've lost the weight and I always recommend this app. If I can anyone can if they are determined and have this handy, easy to use app downloaded.
replyContent: Hi Anne! Thank you for your amazing review. We appreciate your support.

content: It's good, but there is room for improvement. Not all barcodes scan with information. I like the fact that I can add my own food items, but I have to memorize or write down the nutritional information because if I leave the app to look at another screen, it resets. Not a good ux, there's really no reason other than poor development. All in all though, one of the better apps out there. They do have a simple interface that offers enough to be valuable without over doing it like others.
replyContent: Hi David! Thank you for the review and feedback. If you have additional suggestions, feel free to reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: Its good for a casual, daily log. However its hard to deacribe some home made meals. They do give the option to input whole meals and save them for later.
replyContent: Hi Valerie! Thank you for the review and feedback. If you have any questions, feel free to reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: Have been using it for a while now and faced no challenges. Perfectly suitable if you're willing to improve your health and reach your goals. However, do your own research on how many calories you should or meant to be consuming for your specific goals. This app may not provide recommended calories for every individual.
replyContent: Hi Labina! Thanks for the review. We're glad the app is working well for you.

content: Very useful. Lots (but not all) of foods in the database. This app lacks the weight tracking graph and calorie adjusting feature of the full computer one, but it makes up for it in convenience
replyContent: Hi Julie! We appreciate your review and feedback. We've passed your recommendations on to our product team. If you are unable to find the food you are looking for, we recommend creating a custom food. If you have questions, please reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: I use this app to keep track of my food that I eat and calorie count. It does not have all the calorie counts for some things. But it can easily be improvised with a close substitute.
replyContent: Hi Courtney! Thanks for the review and feedback. If you are unable to find the exact food you are looking for, we also recommend creating a custom food. If you have any questions, feel free to reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: love this tracking app have used it for more than a year ...on my weight journey...I would like to see to see tracking calories when using air fryer...nutrional calorie counts for restraunts menus...fast food... Thank you I rate u 100+ on a scale of 10 being the highest...☝🏽
replyContent: Hi Margaret! Thank you for your kind review and feedback. We are happy to hear you are enjoying the app.

content: A good app will get 5 stars if I can manually edit the amount of calories I burn. I don't excercise with my phone so google fit doesn't accurately track calories burnt. However I have a fit bit but the data can't be transferred to the app. Manually inputting the calories burnt would definitely make it a 5 star app
replyContent: Hi Warren! MyPlate can input data from devices you connect to Google Fit. Additionally, you can manually input calories by logging into your account on the desktop site. https://www.livestrong.com/myplate/dashboard/ For more information regarding how to do this, please reach out to us at support@livestrong.com. Thank you.

content: I had gastric bypass(5/2016) and i love this app for keeping track of my protein intake.Edit(12/2020) I have gained 30# over the last year. It wasnt the pandemic, it was ALL ME. During the holidays last year I ate things I knew I shouldn't have and I have just kept gaining and gaining. I'm gonna use this app to be diligent about what I put in my pie hole. I always think to myself, "I dont really eat that much", but once the calories start adding up I'm sure I will be surprised.
replyContent: Hi Samantha! We appreciate your review. We're glad we can be a part of your fitness journey.

content: Love the "my meals" feature as I eat the same thing for breakfast and lunch during the week. Only wish I could log in witj multiple devices (with my phone) as it is on my tablet. Update! I was able to log into the app and sync it with Google fitness. I updated my review to 5 stars!
replyContent: Hi Rick. Thanks for leaving a review. You can login on multiple devices using the same username and password. If you would like assistance with this, please reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: Good for tracking all aspects of nutrition, not just calories. Bar code scanner is useful but sometimes fails to scan. This feature makes it very easy for me to track items so I am more likely to be consistent.
replyContent: Hi Sophie! Thanks for the review and feedback. Our developers are aware of the point with the barcode scanner and are working on a fix for this. If you have any questions, feel free to reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: Awesome calorie tracker. 1 minor quibble is that the keyboard for adjusting the amount of a serving covers the "I ate this" button and having to close it before confirming the food is unnecessary annoying.
replyContent: Hi Tony! Thanks for the review and feedback. We have passed it along to our Product Team. If you have any other suggestions, feel free to reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: Needs some minor adjustments. I add a lot to the "My food" category, getting very lengthy. Why is this not organized in any sort of way? You'd think it would be by most recently added or even alpha order but there is not rhyme or reason to it. I also would like to be able to edit food items I've already entered. I have to re-enter a new item if I change a recipe.
replyContent: Katie! We appreciate your review and feedback. I have passed along your comments to our product development team. We are always adding new content and features to the app and love getting feedback as it helps guide our designs and tools moving forward. If you have additional ideas, we encourage you to reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: I don't know... I don't really trust the nutritional information I'm getting logging stuff... 1½ cup mixed greens: 110 calories? 280mg sodium? 11% of my daily fat intake? That doesn't sound right at all. Is that counting someone that drenched it with dressing or something? I want to add my tbsp oil/lemon seperate. I think the numbers should be specific, I don't want to guess what it is you're using to come up with what the app is putting back.
replyContent: Hi Josh! Thanks for the review and feedback. I believe that entry is referring to cooked greens but I agree, it is unclear. MyPlate uses a third-party food database, which is a collection of listings from the USDA and food manufacturers. Unfortunately, we're not able to edit this database as it is managed by Nutritionix.

content: Need updates. The myFoods section has no edit feature, so if you made a typo you must re-enter in the entire food nutrition. Also, the "add new food" button is at the bottom of the screen, I have to scroll through hundreds of items to add a new item. Same goes for deleting an entry, button is at the bottom and you have to scroll downwards. I believe our screens are large enough now, there is no reason for this. I feel this app hasn't made any useful updates to their app in a long time.
replyContent: Hi Melissa! We appreciate your honest review and feedback. I have passed your comments on to our development team. If you have any other suggestions, feel free to reach out to us at support@livestrong.com. Thank you.

content: EDIT** Thank you for fixing this issue so quickly! This is my fave app to use with google fit. Super easy and it works. I have lost 30 pounds since I started using it. Used to love this but since the update I Can no longer connect to Google Fit? Keeps telling me I need to alow activity recognition permission? There is no option for that in the app settings. Have also tried uninstalling and reinstalling both apps.
replyContent: Hi Eva! Thank you for bringing this to our attention. Our developers are investigating this and hope to release a fix in the next few days. If you have any questions, don't hesitate to reach out to us at support@livestrong.com

content: Update: Uninstalling and reinstalling fixed the glitch. Glad to have it working again. I lost 15 pounds already. It's helped me be conscious with food portions and getting more exercise! Overall, I've really liked the app, and I love that it syncs with Google Fit, but over the past two days it won't open for me anymore.
replyContent: Hi Kim! We're sorry to hear the app is not opening. This is the first report we have received of this. Can you please uninstall and reinstall the app. If this does not resolve the issue, please reach out to us at support@livestrong.com. Thank you.

content: It's easy to use and links well with the exercise tracking app too. The only bad thing is when looking up foods there are so many variations of the same foods that it takes a while to build up your personal library. But thumbs up on the calorie tracking.
replyContent: Hi Sam! Thank you for the review and feedback. As we are always adding new content and features to the app, we love getting feedback as it helps guide our designs and tools moving forward.

content: This application has been fantastic and an awesome tool to help me with my dietary goals. Being a vegan, I've come to find that a balanced macro/micronutrient profile is very difficult to maintain and likely impossible for anyone not paying attention to such things and "playing by feel" so to speak. This app allows me quickly scan most items directly, lookup those that don't scan, or even add to the database myself/create custom foods/meals and exercise to keep tracking accurate and streamlined.
replyContent: Hi Donald! We appreciate your thorough review. We're happy to hear the you are finding the app so useful.

content: Awesome App! PROS: I am able to track food, macros, water, weight AND exercise all in one app. It is simple to calculate nutritional info by using barcode scanner, searching for food, OR manually entering info. I love that I can save my own recipes and foods for easy add later on. CONS: I really wish they had an option to toggle between total/ net carbs in the calculations. I hate seeing my carb intake go into the red zone when I've been so good. Its has some glitches.
replyContent: Hi E Nicholson! Thank you for your honest review. We have passed your feedback on to our product team.

content: I have been trying to upload a picture to my profile for several days now, on my phone and my tablet. The app crashes every single time. Going to the Livestrong website doesn't help either - the same crash occurs. Please fix ASAP.
replyContent: Hi kerrycork58! It looks like your profile picture was successfully updated. I apologize for any issues you may have encountered while doing this. If you have any questions or encounter any other difficulties, please feel free to reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: This app is very useful to track your nutrients intake. Also as it allows to connect with exercise app such that google fit, user can compare calories intake and calories burnt. However, one drawback is that there is no option to enter food portions in grams.
replyContent: Hi Lakmal. Thank you for your feedback. Our developers are aware of this issue and working to resolve it. I apologize for the inconvenience.

content: I absolutely loved this app, ive tried so many and this is the only one that did what i want. I tried adding another food and it said food not found, i tried foods i knew they had and it still didn't show up. I uninstalled the add and downloaded it again and it said the server was down. Please fix this, i loved this app so much ----☆Update☆: after a little time it started working again so yay but please try to find out what happened so this doesn't happen again
replyContent: Hi Isabella. Thanks for the review. We appreciate your feedback. We encountered a disruption, our developers were made aware of it, and resolved it quickly. I apologize for the inconvenience. If you ever encounter an issue please reach out to us at support@livestrong.com. Thank you!

content: Seriously? Cannot switch apps to view caloric data from, let's say, a google search for a specific item that's not listed in MyPlate? When I do so, the tab where I was entering data (calories, macros etc.) just goes back to the "Create food" tab. This is ridiculous, I never had issues with this in other apps. This quite frankly makes it impossible for me to enter all the data I found on Google unless I have to write it down or memorize it. Please fix this ASAP!
replyContent: Hi Mertcan! We very much appreciate your feedback and I have passed along your comments to our product development team. We are always adding new content and features to the app and we love getting feedback as it helps guide our designs and tools moving forward.

content: I started using this app on mid March and by mid October, I had lost a total of 13 pounds. It calculates the amount of calories you should consume based on your weight and height. It has a catalogue of foods and exercises with their calories, and it also allows you to add your own. You add the food you've eaten during the day and the exercise done. Certainly, it has been a useful tool during my weight loss journey.
replyContent: Hi Cat! We appreciate you taking the time to leave a review and are happy to be a part of your fitness journey. If you have any questions, please reach out to us at support@livestrong.com. We're happy to help.

content: Mostly good but frustrating at times when the exact food I'm looking at has a different calorie and/or carb count on this site than what's on the package. Some as much as 10 grams off so I don't trust it's accuracy and have to also keep a food journal so use them both to get closer to the real thing. Now that I know how to fix this (see comment in response to this), I have to change rating to 5 stars. I've tried other apps and don't like any others as well as this. It's easy and covers everything, including Macros that I can change at will. I love the progress chart too. Once they get some of the inconsistencies corrected it will be perfect, but it's already great, definitely worth using, especially now that I know how to help in that area. I would recommend this site.
replyContent: Hi Cindi! Thanks for the review. MyPlate uses a third party food database called Nutritionix. If you can please send us the UPC codes for the items you have found to be incorrect, we can send them along to Nutritionix to be updated. You can contact us at support@livestrong.com

content: The app no longer lets me delete or edit entries so I can't change the serving amount. It also doesn't let me add it multiple times if you were wondering. Basically the app is completely useless.
replyContent: Hi Adley! We're sorry to hear you are having trouble editing tracked items. We'd be happy to take a look into this for you, please contact us at support@livestrong.com. Thank you.

content: If you find a good item to track calories today you may not be able to find it tomorrow. I've never seen an app do that function so poorly. You literally cannot get to a stored food item by name. You type it in and the results suddenly do not have the item anymore. Then magically, a week later, you might find it again. Pretty poor development tbh.
replyContent: Hi T R! We sincerely apologize for the troubles you've had with the app. We'd be happy to take a look into this for you, please contact us at support@livestrong.com. Thank you.

content: Easy to use, like the option for reminders and the breakdown for macros. Would like to see the meals grouped instead of by ingredients; it's hard to change the portion of meal/delete a meal entry if you've made a mistake. Secondary reminders for water consumption would also be awesome to have. From what I've seen, there is somewhat minimal integration for inputting exercises but I don't have a wearable tracking Cal's/exercise.
replyContent: Hi Lily! We've forwarded your feedback to our developers. Thank you for taking out the time to send us your suggestions!

content: Very handy app. I use it everyday to track calories and nutrients. Would really, really like to see the option to use NET CARBS as the daily total carbs. That would be very useful to me. Love, love, love the bar-code scanning feature. I think some sort of organizational options for MY FOODS would also be helpful (folders? groups? sorting?) Scrolling through an unordered list of many items is pretty laborious. Overall, it's a very valuable tool to me.
replyContent: Hi Jason! We appreciate your feedback and I have passed along your comments to our product development team. We are always adding new content and features to the app and we love getting feedback as it helps guide our designs and tools moving forward.

content: Pretty good app like how it's setup and would be higher and my favorite, but it's missing net carbs after fiber and alcohol sugar is subtracted and wish it had were you can edit foods nutrition. Overall not bad though looking forward to any new features.
replyContent: Hi Brian. We appreciate your feedback and I have passed along your comments to our product development team. We are always adding new content and features to the app and we love getting feedback as it helps guide our designs and tools moving forward.

content: The only thing I would change is the ability to add foods not in the library with info that I have. Example Dreamfield Pastas I appreciate the correction. Found it, tried it, loved it. Really helping me. It was suggested by my doctor.
replyContent: Hi Debra. To create a custom food tap on the blue plus sign, tap the meal you'd like to track the custom food to (Breakfast, Lunch, Dinner, or Snack). Tap "My Food", scroll to the bottom of the page and "Create A New Food". Enter the name of the food and the nutritional information. When completed tap the check mark in the upper right corner.

content: I've used this app on and off, logging calories or just tracking food. I love it personally because the design is simple and aesthetically pleasing, adding your own foods and nutrition info is easy, and the bar code scanner is convenient for packaged foods.
replyContent: Hi Damon! We appreciate you taking the time to leave a review and we're happy to hear you are loving MyPlate. Thank you.

content: After trying many, this appears to be the one I will keep. Only thing it's missing is the complete nutritional label, including essential vitamins and minerals. I need to track my potassium intake and the entries are missing this data. When dieting it can be easy to come up short on vitamins so it would be nice to see what I am/not getting enough of.
replyContent: Hi Steve! Thank you for your review. I have passed along your comments to our product development team. We're always adding new content and features to the app and love getting feedback.

content: I really like the way this app saves the foods I eat on a regular basis. The information about the food content is great as well. You can track macro and micronutrients easy
replyContent: Hi Sonia! We appreciate you taking the time to leave a review. We’re glad you are enjoying MyPlate. We're constantly looking for new ways to improve our app, and we love getting feedback as it helps guide our process moving forward.

content: The overall tracking is fairly easy to input and it tracks it well, but the community section is pretty annoying. There's no way to tag people or edit your messages which would be very useful. If the devs could input a way to directly reply to people and edit our messages I would rate 5 stars.
replyContent: Hi Amelia! We appreciate your feedback and I have passed along your comments to our product development team. As we are always adding new content and features to the site and app, we love getting feedback as it helps guide our designs and tools moving forward. If you have additional suggestions, please contact us at support@livestrong.com.

content: I rated this app low because I have tried to log in several times and it won't let me. I even changed my pa and it won't take the new one. On top of that I have emailed and called these guys with no response to date. Very disappointing 😕 Thanks for responding! My access has been cleared. The app is working very well for me. I have updated my ratings too.
replyContent: Hi Jermel! Thanks for reaching out. We do not have a customer service phone number and have not received any emails from you. Please email us at support@livestrong.com and we'll be happy to take care of this right away. Thank you.

content: Seems easy to use. Adds up daily food with breakdown of components eg. carbs etc. You can incorporate daily activity as well. I will probably have to uninstall it however as I can't move it to my SD card. It has to stay in internal storage.
replyContent: Hi Alison! Thank you for your feedback. We’re glad you are enjoying MyPlate. If you have any questions regarding the app don't hesitate to reach out to us at support@livestrong.com.

content: The app is great! Everything I need in one place. I've only had it for a week but so far I love it. Love the green,yellow,red foods. I can add a meal before I eat & if it's not fitting into my "budget", I can adjust the amt til it fits. For example, last night I wanted a few tortillas chips & salsa. I just adjusted the amt of chips til it fit. Salsa is a green & I had plenty of calories left, so yay! I had the perfect snack.
replyContent: We love to hear that you find our food tracker so helpful and easy to use, Marleen! Keep up the awesome work building healthier habits with your Noom family!

content: THE PROGRAM ITSELF IS EXCELLENT! Features are missing from the android version. My friends on apple get more features. Custom recipe input is missing, steps don't load in, app laggy when opening. There is more, but the recipe input is a big one since calories are key. I don't want to have to use another app or website to figure out my recipe calories.
replyContent: We’re glad that you’re enjoying what Noom has to offer, Eleasha, and your honest feedback here is appreciated! We want Noom to be the best app we can make, and your feedback is invaluable to that process. If you have any questions or would like to leave further feedback, please send us a message at GPSreviews@noom.com.

content: I have tried a lot of other apps and ideas. NOOM really did change the way I think about food. I was very skeptical but here I am. 25 lbs down so far. I eat completely different now and it's not agonizing. It's how I want to eat. I never thought I'd say that. I have the tools and the "psych tricks" I need to be successful in this life goal achievement of mine. By the way, I still eat cheese burgers and burritos.
replyContent: This is SO awesome, Brian! You are making phenomenal progress, and we are so grateful to be a part of your journey! Great work!

content: Glitchy. It's my first day and I won't mention my issue with the first quiz and the lack instruction or explanation on why an answer was incorrect. This post is about the app glitching when I attempted to log my meals for the day. It bad I couldn't successfully search or select anything. Seriously second guessing my decision to try this app.
replyContent: We're so sorry that you're experiencing some trouble! We would love to assist you, would you mind reaching out to us at GPSreviews@noom.com when you get the chance so that we can get this sorted out for you? Thanks!

content: Got it for the fortnight trial, absolutely no intention of parting with 22 bucks a month for what is basically a calorie counter with some psychology tacked on. App is pretty good, but the rolly wheel seems to default on the premise you're eating a wheelie bin full of (whatever), so if you've only eaten a small amount you'll end up scrolling for a long time. Also, there's free apps that do the same thing but better and FREE. *cough*myfitnesspal*cough*free*cough*
replyContent: We are sorry to hear that you're disappointed with Noom, James! Our Support Team would love to help! Remember- you can always reach us at GPSreviews@noom.com if you need anything.

content: Update: customer service has been excellent and my problem seems resolved. Good concept and the process is good too, but the app is driving me mad as it's stopped syncing with Fitbit for the step count. Apparently it's a known issue at the moment but for a concept that's built on calorie counting that updated with activity this is seriously flawed and it's really demotivating when you're going out of your way to meet a step count goal.

content: Lots of good tips, no pressure. I linked the app to my fitbit to track my steps. Additional exercises can also be input. The daily calorie goal shifts with exercise. replyContent: This is amazing to read, Jennifer! You are doing such a wonderful job embracing each aspect of the program! Keep up the awesome work!

content: it's hard for me to motivate myself but joining Noom has made it fun to track my food and celebrate each pound I lose! replyContent: Hi Gary Grif01! We're sorry to hear about your issue. To resolve, please go to pedometer, tap more, tap Pause counting steps. Tap more again and tap Start counting steps. Perform clear cache and force stop Samsung Health app from device Settings - App manager. Lastly, please restart device. If still having issues, please contact 1-855-795-0509.
