content: Still trying to navigate the app. Gets better every time I use it. It's difficult for a beginner because not all of us are tech savvy.

Amazing program! Only downside is that the 24/7 chat is pretty much useless. It's impossible to get ahold of someone to answer questions. However the Connect feature which is basically a form of social media is helpful because you can ask other participants questions.

I love the app, i wish it would let you do fractions on the food app. i really miss the activity challenges. I was always trying to do more and better tines the following week. I thought something was wrong with my app and i had to go thru 3 people to tell me you had taken them off the system. Not all of your people knew about it.
Great way to track your diet and health. Love the food bar code scanner!
Easy to use. Best features are the bar code reader for entering packaged food & app remembers previous meals for quick re-entry.
The barcode scanner is amazing.. You don't realize how motivating it is to work your points everyday. I love this app.
This app gives me the discipline that I need when it comes to food. Makes me responsible for everything I put in my mouth thank you Weight Watchers!!
Had no issues usingvthis app. Barcode wirks when wifi is available . Packed full of helpful information and great work outs

Hate this app, too much wrong product information, it obvously doesnt get checked, the help page doesn't give the right instructions to change your plan, there's too much info so confuses navigation, everything takes sooo long to do, I think weight watchers are mainly replying on members to update food list as they really haven't got a big list themselves so it's very unreliable. Very very disdapointed with this app.

The app is decent. However, I have major issues with the new WW program. I'm allowed 20 points per day, breakfast and lunch I have consumed less than 500 calories, 20 grams of protein and the program says I'm at 10 points. Half of my daily allowance. At this rate, I'm going to starve, Ive followed the program for 2 months and haven't lost a pound. The old program worked, this one sucks.

Very helpful app for points, recipes, tracking food, water, exercise, sleep, weight loss. Great motivation and support. Love the bar code reader that instantly tells you points 9n any food. Working very well for me
I am gradually learning to use properly and it's helping me to keep on track to lose weight in a safe manner.

I love the app, everything is so much easier now with this app. The 2 issues I have is that there is not a place to log your water consumption. The other issue is that I'm not tech savvy so I have no place to track my exercise. The old way you had a way to track your water and exercise by writing it down. So I wish you gave people a choice to either attach their phone to some device for their physical activity or have a choice to just type it in. Other then those issues it's a great app.
The app makes it easy to discover food points, makes choices, and keep track. There is a lot of useful information available on the app too.
Easy to use. No excuses not to track yourself. It seems like just about every food possible is in the database.

I love the app to keep me on track.i only wish it would log stuff on the correct day without having to check the date.i heard a fix had been put in place but i cant see that is so.its probably me but all in all i love it and the recioe ideas are great if your stuck.fab x
Great for keeping on track especially with the scanner. Everything at your fingertips.
I still learn things about this app. every single day. Love the different ideas, recipes and love connect.
Helps me keep track in real time and the foods are super easy to find and track.
I never review apps, but this program and app is amazing. Ive lost more weight then I have with CICO and I'm eating more and better food. It makes being healthy a fun game.

Weight watchers app is a great tool to help stay focused on my weight loss journey and covers all areas like the podcasts to listen to while walking. It's so awesome! This makes it easier to reach my goals faster.
Not as user friendly as other similar aps. Update: Much easier to use and very helpful

They design and layout of the app is not quick and easy to use. You spend ages searching for what you want to do. It doesn't help you sticking to the diet when you have so much hassle recording what you're eating. Needs a complete redsign. These may sound perty but they add up to frustrating experience. It only lists a few previous foods and you keep having to press 'see more'. I have to search every week when tracking weight, it should be there on the page. I could go on but not enough letters
Just want to type in food to count calories. Is that even a option anymore. I can't scan a slice of pizza. Keep it simple
Makes it easier to track points. Esp.scanning bar codes. Doesn't work for every item but the majority.
Great app and great program. The free points makes this the easiest WW program to follow.
My experience is good with the app. It's slow sometimes because my internet is sketchy but the app is great!
I love weight watchers I couldn't do with out them. Love the point system keeps my weight off.
I love the WW app because it's so easy to keep track of my punts throughout the day. I espically like where I can scan the UPCcode on an item and it tells me how menu points per serving

I find it easy to keep myself in check with the daily points and I use weekly points for a treat or a night out. I have lost 1/2 a stone in 3 weeks and I'm feeling confident that I can lose more. I love digital WW, the support is always with me. Love the coaching, exercises and recipes.

Love it. This is the only app and program that actually works. I've tried at least four other options before i signed up for WW and nothing gave me such wonderful results as this. App is super easy to use, recipes are delish and i can't wait to try more, it connected with my fitness watch with no problem to collect step count. Points are fantastic, i don't have to count calories and best thing is I can have my favorite pastries with extra points collected so you don't have to say no to yourself.
This app has been improved upon since I last used it a few years ago. It has been very helpful in my weight loss journey! Very easy to use and follow
Happy is horrible trying to add a new food. Even if it says that it scanned the food, it won't except it.

The best of the best for loosing weight and staying fit. You can eat foods you like and still loose weight. Will not stay hungry. Also the app provides coaching, videos, walktalks and postcasts that also motivate and help you to believe in yourself to be confident in obtaining what you want and the most important "Feel great, and be healthy". I even went on a cruise, where there is plenty of food and I didn't gain weight. THAT WAS AMAZING FOR ME. You learn how to eat.
Awesome... this app helps you be aware of what you eat and helps form better habits. I love it. 3 weeks in and down 7 pounds.
Love this. It is so easy to track my food compared to when I had to write down calories. I have been on WW for 1 wee8and have lost 6 pounds!
Easy to use. Search function is really good. Love that they have loaded points on for supermarket products.

Thought I couldn't do ww since I have a family with different tastes. Wrong! My fav is eat lots of roasted veg and drink water to add points. I'm sorry that my family eats roasted veg too lol. Chicken & eggs are zero points 4 me. Most days I don't eat all my points, & I'm not hungry. I used to take overeating to a new level. I've lost nine pounds in less than three weeks! Long way to go, but I'll be less than 200 lbs soon for the first time in ages!
It's so easy!! Scan barcodes or search by name. Tracking almost does it by itself!

Really love this app. It's affordable and really easy to utilize and it has tons of resources to help you with your health and wellness goal. It has support groups you can join for extra support, recipes, exercises and so much more. The best part is you get points for keeping track of your progress which you then can turn in for a variety of rewards. Definitely one of the best decisions and apps I have come across thus far.
I was worried at 1st about using the app but it's really not hard at all. I've been using it 3 days and It's going great! It figures everything out for you once you enter the info.
I really enjoy this app because it's easy to find whatever I'm searching for and calculates it rapidly.

I've lost 52 lbs in 6 most a d it was easy. I love the scanner so I can clearly see how many points a food is. I have had my questions answered online quickly. I would recommend this app for anyone that is serious about losing weight.
Love the app. Have occasional issues when there are new updates. Have an Android phone.
Mostly app works well can make own recipes so points more accurate but great recipes already there though you do need to have 5 mins to do it and does help to keep on track
The absolute plan to be on for weight loss. It teaches you not only what to eat but how to make good food choices.
So much easier then keeping a journal. I wish there was a lower price for people who are going to use app for the rest of their life.
Losing weight and not starving doing it! App is easy to navigate.

The WW app just keeps getting better. Yes you could try to track on a free app, but the resources on this app are amazing. My favorite features are the recipes and the barcode scanner. Almost everything I scan in the grocery store is already in their system. It has made losing weight much easier than I thought it could be.

When I tap on the shop, it cycles between the front page with the daily special, and the screen that says my session has expired and to please log in. It keeps cycling back and forth between those two screens and it never stops. So I can't even try to log in. Furthermore when I hit the back button it doesn't go anywhere. So I have to kill the app and launch it again.

Easy to use. Many different ways to add foods that you ate for each meal. Ability to build your own recipes. Able up look up WW recipes for delicious meal ideas. The Connect feature allows you to connect with other WW members to discuss your weight loss journey.
I love the recipe builder, I can make favorite recipes and know exactly how much I can eat!

Ok at tracking food but activity could use more work. Hard to find activity from list if doing manual entry and the time always says 15 minutes with the cursor on the wrong side! Makes changing that time extremely hard! Allow manual time entry! Also, profile all messed up. Doesn't allow for a picture and asks for why with no where to enter the reason. Could be better if someone actually tested areas before putting them out there. Not everyone has a device for activity!

Lots of very useful easy to use items here. I would love to have a little place to make a daily note about what my blood sugar was etc. 7/21/22......And there was a Blood Sugar tracking section. Thank you, I love it!!!!
I love the app. The only problem I have is my phone constantly blink when I try to order food. I don't know if this is a problem on my end or the app.
It is easy to track weight and food. I use the connect to inspire me when I am down.
Easy to use, so helpful and a great way to keep track of all your points.

Easy to use, reliable on function. I'm losing weight using it. I love that you can find a way to determine points for any kind of food, as well as track your sleep habits and your exercise time. I also love that it has no annoying ads.

Love this app. Easy to use and calculate points. But when creating your own meal it's confusing as to whether its calculating points per serving or not or for the whole meal. Still lots of Canadian foods have to be added manually. But there's great support and lots of fun!
Great tool! Love being able to track my progress. It would be great if we could add personalized daily/weekly items to be checked off and tracked as well to keep the motivation going.

Easy peasy! Loving the app and WW now. Gaining points for water, eating vegetables and exercising really is a motivator. So easy and you really learn over time the types of mistakes that make you fat. For me, I eat healthy but salad dressings and loading up coffee with all kinds of flavors and creams was killing me.
I like the app but when I scan a food it might be for future use and I can't save it unless in a meal. The improvement since last use is great. I love the app
Love this app ... easy to use ! It gives me accountability of my everyday decisions. It has become apart of my everyday life.

I've been a member of W W since 1980. I mean a proud lifetime member. I have emence respect for this program and it never fails me. Just when I think they can't make there program any better they do. thanks WW. I've been off ww since 1/2021. I've regained 10 of the fifteen pounds I lost. It was a tough year. I'm back to look better, feel better and wear the clothes I bought in 2020. Hi. Since the end of May 2022. I've lost 8 lbs. and holding. I'm feeling good.
Love the app, easy to use. My only gripe is not being able to enter the weight of food and having to scroll.
I really like the app. I feel like it helps my accountability and it is a well put together app.

Lost a total of 28 pounds, have been a member/user since then today 80's going with my Mother, now I'm 83 and love this new WW app. So glad it has diabetic readings app. This eliminated an additional tracking I have had to do since 1994 when I was diagnosed.
It would be great if we could just enter weights in the recipe builder instead of scrolling.

The app works, but it tries to incorporate too much. I accidentally back out of it more often than I get where I want to go. Food diary and activity calculator are all it needs. The rest is just clutter. WW should review and approve all food calculated before it is shared (to many miscalculated food items entered by members).

Sooooo disappointed in this app. Did weight watchers years ago and it really works. Thought I would try again. So just joined a few days ago. I love the scanner and water counter, but app doesn't stay synced with my Google fit. Obe is a disappointment. Did workout on it this morning and hit track. It didn't track it. My steps never update during day until the very end of the day and yes it says synced with my Google fit. I hate not being able to manually track activities on ww. Not happy
It's very easy to use. There's lots of uses - tracking, exercise, talks. I have lost 3 stone and intend to keep it off using the app.
This is the best weight loss app ever. I have tried them all. I'm down 34 pounds in 3 months!
Great until it failed, it's working now it kept saying I didn't have an account it's fixed now but it's still hard to use, it could be more user friendly.
Love it! Love the support, the community, the bar code scanner, the plan and flexibility. Definitely recommend it.
Keeps me on track and accountable. Love the point system. Super easy to use. Worth the monthly fee.

It's a good app, however it would have been helpful to include a tutorial. It took me awhile to get the hang of logging activities, all the point and zero point foods, etc. A friend joined after seeing my success in the first week, but stated she had the same difficulty I did with navigating the app.
This is the easiest and best ap I have used for food tracking. I love the program.

The app is very personal, but it gives me the support from the WW community I need to continue on my weight loss journey. It's easy to use and has so many features. I especially love the addition to help diabetics.
You are at my fingertips and knowledgeable for my interest. Recipes and points are Terrific! Thank you.

Easy to use. Interesting. A world of info and help aids. WW covers all basis to keep you connected and support you throughout your journey to better health / body, mind and spirit. Amazing! I will continue using the app long after my goal weight is reached.

Easy to use, good features. I have a hard time finding things like recipes, tracking weight, creating recipes, it seems like there's too many layers to get to them sometimes. A Google image type function to add food would be next level!!

This app is very easy to use. The scanning feature helps me find almost any food in just a few seconds. I used it while I was grocery shopping to make good choices at the front end. Being able to link to my fitness tracker is very helpful, and helps me link my activity to my weight loss.
So easy to use and helpful!! It works for me as a vegetarian very well. I'm not hungry and I've steadily averaged a pound a week loss. Twenty pounds and counting
Great way to track what you are eating, allowable points, in an easy fashion.
Fab app. Think WW is great. Really working for me. Just wish I could print my fave recipes out to keep in a folder
This app works great, it allows me to track my points and helps me to stay on plan. I am losing weight and feeling great. This WW app truly is a game changer.

Once I got the hang of where things are in the app, I'm able to make great use of it. At the beginning, though it is not user friendly. It was like I was expected to know where things were just because!
I absolutely love it. I'm down 16 lbs and counting. I got a ways to go. But it definitely works. And I love WalkTalk. I'm looking forward to hearing new ones
This makes tracking and checking so easy. Plus earning points and free foods. Great program change!
Love this app it help me record what I eat. Its easy to use and very informative with advice on menus plus workouts.
Excellent App. I struggled with weight loss. I'm 64 and I recommend WW to all who want to get control of their weight.
Keeps getting better and better. Love the app and program. Walk Talks are the best!
I have lost 15 pounds since the spring...something I couldn't manage to do in years!! I'm never hungry and the tracking app is a huge help. I'm very happy!
Works well, although every now and again, it changes, a little harder to find the foods that normally just popped up, still like the app.
Best decision I ever made, to join on the WW app! I've lost weight, made friends, and improved my eating habits!
This has been the easiest way I' ve ever used to lose weight. I eat a lot on this program and am still losing pounds! Great choices customized for me.
It has been an awesome experience and very easy to sustain. I have lost 47 pound which has helped my back and leg issues. Thank you WW.🤗

This has helped to be accountable for how I live. I am diabetic and wish you had a more specific program to work with. I have had to work carb count on my own. But overall I'm doing well and having someone going through this with me has been a big plus!
Easy, and quick to use. Very effective. ♥️ want to learn to find more breakfast ideas.
Easy to use and an awesome tool to have to be able to stay on track and motivated! Love the recipes, all the positive information that has helped me so much. It's an outstanding app!

The app is easy to use. It has great recipes. Easy to track points, activity and sleep. Being part of the WW community is really great and inspiring to know that we can lean on each to reach out weight loss goals
Works great. Restaurant lookup is good. I wish it could be a little more complete.
It is so full of foods i may eat and keeps track of the ones i repeat. Makes losing weight easy!
Easy to learn and use! There's really a lot on it, from support to exercise and recipes!
I have no trouble tracking food. I just haven't figured out how to track exercise & sleep.
Easy to navigate. Love the fact i can plan my meals, enter my personal recipes to get point value...has made me feel like I'm not dieting and can eat along with my family!
Great WW app to help you focus. Would it be possible to have a grocer shopping list tunction and track serving points? THANKS.

8/26/2022 The app has improved since I wrote the 2019 review. It's still only average. The database can use some work. Terrible. Design is poor. There is so much wrong with the functionality and human interface, I don't have the time or inclination to write it all. WW needs better software designers who understand efficient design. Revert to previous version. So bloody frustrated with this company.

The main way I use the app is to modify my favorite recipes to make them healthier. It is easy to see which ingredients are increasing the calories, fat, etc. and find modifications to make the recipe healthier and less points. Sometimes the modifications don't work and I can decide not to eat it at all or skip the modifications and eat it rarely
I've been using the WW app since October 2021. There can be some delay when trying to update my day. But that's the only problem. I love it 💖
Easy to use and keeps me on track. Inspires a new healthy way to eat. You can get additional help if you request it or want to join social groups

I dont even need to come to a meeting using this app. I have experience with WW in the past. I like the meets but dont always want to go. I can track myself, learn about recipes and get all sorts of helpful hints if necessary. Love this app!
Great app. It is basically intuitive and simple to navigate for the most part.
It's so clearly tells me which foods are a good option and those that aren't. Plus it keeps me on track with fitness
Good app, helps me track and stay in daily points. The search sort is wierd though - it brings up recipes instead of the food item that I 'm searching for.
Lost 29 lbs so far really easy to follow. Love that there are so many free foods.
It helps me track everything I eat. Along with allowing me to make recipes to know how many points each serving is.

I love the program and the app is easy to use. My ONLY issue is that I wish it would indicate, when searching for a food item, which entries are actually figured from WW and which ones are entered from members. I have gotten totally mixed up and gone over points when trusting that the numbers (points) in the search have been calculated by WW and are totally correct.

WW program app uses best features of the many weight mgmt and health tracking apps and adds in recipes, mental health, coaching, community, and more. Virtual meetings available anytime that fits your schedule. The best yet!
Quick and easy. Love being able to scan bar codes while grocery shopping
Helps keep me accountable. I love the create meals, lists features and the ability to scan my food. Awesome app

On 2/12/22 I posted about not being able to use my Samsung Health app and I was told by Customer Service to load Map My Run app so I did. Worked maybe a day. So disappointing. Using Android phone. Update 5/18/22 Map My Run still doesn't work. All I want is for the app to keep track of my steps automatically. I am still disappointed that the WW app does not recognize Android devices. Update 7/26/22 I gave up on Map My Run & purchased a used Fit Bit, now I wear two watches on the same arm.
replyContent:
Hi Christina! Good news! You can sync your Samsung Activity Device - Please, link Samsung Health to MapMyRun to then be able to link to the WW App. You can find the steps here: https://www.weightwatchers.com/us/blog/fitness/syncing-ww-samsung-apple-fitness-trackers

-WW Customer Care-

content: This app holds me accountable for everything I put in my mouth. Still learning how to use it to get all the WW benefits it offers.
Generally great. Occasionally have trouble adding weight on weigh in or getting to the right screen to add activity. Wish I could hard copy recipes from the advertisement page. Thanks!
I like the program. I like the old system better but anything works as long as you follow it. I just felt like I knew more with the first program. I love the connect group. It gives me motivation.
It's easybto use, helps you make on the spot decisions, and it a great tool to help lose weight.
Great for tracking, recipes and tips. Sometimes it freezes and needs a phone reset.

It's good when it works, but there are too many products from members that are incorrect. The database needs to be updated and reviewed more regularly than it currently is, as there's not enough points values done by ww, it's mostly by members and the nutritional information changes; except WW leave all of the different data input by members on there. When you scan something in store, you may buy it. But when you get home the nutritional information may be wrong and I might not have bought it.
replyContent:
We welcome and appreciate your feedback. This will be forwarded on to the proper department for review. Wishing you success in your wellness journey!

--WW Customer Care--

content: It has really helped me focus on healthy eating! Not a diet but education of foods which are not nutritious and good for you. I have lost 13lbs from Feb22 to July 22 slowly and been excersing to get fit. The calculated points value, sharing of others recipes and ideas have been invaluable!! Thank you WW! 😊
It's good, you have to learn some things but once you do know, it's easier There's tons in it, I love it- still using it! And here I am a year later still using it! Tracks so much, take a look!
Find the app so helpful in tracking my progress and meeting my goals. It's easy to use and love the scan/points feature.

The app is very user friendly and helps me immensely with working towards my goals! WW is a better program than others because it focuses on healthy mindset, healthy eating, healthy sleep, and exercise! Love the app and love WW!
Love this app just wish there wasn't so many errors with points. You definitely have to double check that pts are correct

Many foods are not in your system. Sometimes I have to call to resume the app. I love the scanner. Maybe you can show restaurant items in order of points from low to high. For example, what can I eat in Dunkin Donuts that has the least number of points.
The amount of data available (foods, brands, restaurant menu items) is truly amazing.

It's not the app. It's weight watchers, they charge an early cancellation fee of $42 so beware. Also they start with $5 a month and then hike it up to $25 a month. If ypu don't want to pay cancellation fee you habe to keep paying them until your subscription expires. They get their moneys worth out of you when there are so many free apps out there.
it works well and stays current with valuable info. I wish the saved recipe section could be organized alphabetically to find a recipe more quickly.

The WW app makes it easy to follow my program. With access to my points plan, coaching, menu planning, recipes, connection to others in WW, Breethe relaxation and mindfulness meditations, and Obè exercise videos, everything is right on my phone. Thank you WW! ❤️

I never thought I could benefit from using online version of WW and it turns to be best suited thing for me. There are days where you you want to give I started out 6'7 and weighing 484 lbs and now losing weight. Thanks to WW I have the ability to make right decisions.

Love the WW program but the app is a bit difficult sometimes. I wish they would let your smartwatch connect for activity tracking. Have to use a 3rd party for it to sync and even then it doesn't do it all the time.
I like the awareness that the app has brought to my eating habits. I was truly overeating until I started tracking my intake of food.
It does not load every time. You keep asking me to refresh and download your ww app. Well ive downloaded it and it keeps crashing. Grtting fed up with it.
replyContent:
June, we appreciate you for taking the time providing us with your feedback. Make sure you have the most up to date app downloaded to your phone. So sorry to hear about your recent experience with the WW App. Please fill this out, https://bit.ly/3hfCBs4. We would be happy to help. 😃


– WW Customer Care –

content: I am so impressed with this app. It's easy to use, the barcode scanner is great, and so far, never an issue
This app is a great way to keep you accountable for what you are doing example is tracking what you have consumed every day

I am so thankful to WW and this app. It has taught me how to eat and what size portions to stick to. I dont feel like im missing out on anything. I am feeling great and just about at my weight goal. I now have the tools and understanding to carry me on and remain fit and healthy. Thank you WW

Helps keep me on track. However video's do not keep my phone in gaged, it times out while watching or following exercise videos. Example would be Netflixd, my phone does not time out while watching movies niether does it while watching YouTube, which tells me it's the WW app. Not my phone. It would be so nice if this was fixed and would be nice if I could access Ww app on my Amazon fire stick so I can use tv to follow videos or my laptop. Just some ideas. Love the app thank you

It has good features but tracking activity is very difficult so I can not earn points for the week unless it's for steps. I really hate they took out the Fit on and the other training app. Not really feeling this Obe stuff. Also it sometimes doesn't load. At times this app is frustrating
Ive lost over 40 lbs. It needs more current restaurants tho (chucks isn't in the app) but ive learned how to maneuver around meals.
It's too hard for people my age. I'm 70 and want to lose weight, but I don't know how to manuver this program. A printed book is better for us seniors.
I have no problems with this app. However, I don't use it for shopping, restaurants, etc. I just use the basics and it works great!

Great app, great program. We love WW. Been using it with my husband (each our own app accounts) since Nov. 2021. Thanks to our hard work and WW, we are healthier, happier, and the app is a huge part of the WW program that gives us these benefits. WW app is easy to use, has lots to discover to help if you're bored or stuck, and it takes no time at all to enter each day to track food (and exercise and sleep if you like).

Annoying when one is only using part of a 'portion' n doesn't seem to allow you to enter what you actually use. Trying to type in several ingredients n it doesn't have what you are using. At times I give up which isn't conclusive to tracking ones daily points. I've given up at the moment 😥. Once I'm in a better place I will try to get back on track.
Everytime I open this Android app which I need, it's down, or updating and wipes all data I entered. This is linked with my Fitbit. Discouraging.
You can't access the shop from this app. It doesn't work correctly. I really don't like this app it causes me a lot of frustration

Weight watchers itself is very good and does help you lose weight. The app though is frustrating - I think being able to manually type in quantities would be far easier than having to scroll through especially when you're doing a total recipe that may contain several 100s of grams of something. Also not knowing what WW deems as a 'portion' can make it annoying to track initially - have to convert to grams to see what matches the portion so you know how much you can have.
Really great app! Easy to use. Very helpful. Love the ability to scan barcodes.

Sometimes it is hard to get the cursor in the right spot to change numbers for the minutes section for exercise. So that can be frustrating. Also,the planning a meal sometimes can be very time consuming because it does not always track to the meal that was initially choosing.

The app itself is ok. I wish it had an option for diets for PCOS instead of either diabetic or not. So I'm having to combine a keto ish diet with one for diabetics. It's not really the best. The store also crashes any time I select it from the app. Overall the app is good, tracking is easy, it's pretty encouraging just disappointed in some options in the initial survey to set up the right diet.

I love this app and service, but the rewards are pants. It would be so much better if our reward points offered us something that feels like a reward and not another subscription. You should put reward points on items in the ww store. I'm sure people would be more motivated for a healthy chocolate bar. I know I would.
Just starting out on app. I am beyond confused and frustrated trying to navigate anywhere. I thought this would be so easy.

I type in a very simple food to add. For example "cherries" and you'd think cherries the fruit would be an option. Nope, I get everything but....even things that do not contain anything related to cherries. Obnoxious and infuriating. Gave up and everything has to go through the website.
Not able to use it or even read it. Very confusing. No help available so far. One week and counting.

Well....it is not good...as this is where I get delivered when I click on the button that tells me I have "wins" which I can "redeem". I don't consider yet more adverts as a prize! Fix the site! I like WW, and I can always make it work for me, but very annoying continual flow of adverts! And the far too high price is a great thing for the owners, but it is a serious deterrent to those who have weight issues who simply can not afford it at normal prices.
Very disappointed. It don't want to sync with my samsung properly. The never match with my watch. It won't track my activities at the gym. It's getting frustrating.

I really miss the Purple Plan I used to be on for more than 1yr. I lost 65lbs on it. Since I changed appts? It's more confusing & I've gained 10lbs back! I would like having choice to stay with what worked for me!
Terrible have paid for the digital and when i download it ( and have done multiple times ) it does not let me in. Just tells me i have to join. Totally disappointed
I love the ease. I would like more choices for activity. I.e. gardening, exercise at a rehab facility or gym. I do not have fit bit etc.

Gradually finding my way around this ap...would like the option to type in daily activity, as not got a smart watch that is compatable. Not everyone has one. There may be an option, but not found it yet!
I rarely use this app because it doesn't track all my steps. It has full access to my Google fit but I don't understand why it doesn't work.
Helps you lose weight, but forget getting steps or activities tracked if you use Samsung products. I have a galaxy watch4 and it won't sync:/ very unimpressed
replyContent: We value your feedback, Christina.

content: I was a part of the WW program for over 18 months. The program worked for me , but the app needs work. I would suggest looking at Healthi/iTrackBites instead. The value WW is supposed to add is the "personalized" coaching, but it was little more than some employees (not experts) following a script full of bad inspirational quotes. The customer service department also leaves a lot of be desired.
replyContent:
Thank you for providing us with your feedback. Our focus is to create tools that make it easier to build Healthy Habits. Your feedback helps us improve our services. If you need further assistance, please contact 24\7 Chat or send an email over to ResolutionSupport@ww.com. We look forward to assisting you.

-- WW Customer Care --

content: Love, love, love this app. 😀 😀 I track religiously and barcode scan when out shopping. I am able to avoid even buying high point items so no temptation to over indulge.
Very glitchy app. It's easy to use but keeps losing connection to the internet and won't connect to my fitbit. It loses it every day. Customer Debbie was unable to help
replyContent:
Hi! Sorry for any troubles. Please reach out by 24/7 chat on your WW app profile page, or give us a call at 1-800-651-6000. We would be happy to help.

--WW Customer Care

content: A lot of bugs on this app, for example it doesn't always add my fitness points to my weeklies so it means I still have to work out my allowance myself rather than having it all tracked by the app. I would expect more from a paid app from a big company like WW. My family has used free apps with similar function levels as this- I thought WW would be better. Edit for reply: app shows the points in the activity tab but doesn't add them to my weeklies but thanks for the patronising reply. 3* now 1*
replyContent:
Hi! Thanks so much for reaching out. In order for your FitPoints to add to your weeklies, you must first acheive what would be equivalent to 3,000 steps. Any workout or step Points accumulated after that are added to your Weekly total. Feel free to utilize our 24/7 chat option of you have further questions.

--WW Customer Care--

content: I really like the app... but I can't access the shop or reward items asit has a nasty glitch going on. This needs to be fixed!
replyContent:
Thank you for your feedback, Lorri! 😊 Please try uninstalling and reinstalling the WW app. If this does not correct the issue, please fill this form out👉 https://bit.ly/3hfCBs4. We’re here to help.

--WW Customer Care –

content: Edited 6/25/22: Bring back D360! I miss the coaches! The app still works great otherwise, but I miss my coaches posts and videos! LOVE all the tools! This app is so easy to find points, find recipes, and get inspiration and coaching. I am so happy to be on this wellness journey with my D360 teams and this app!

Updating my review from 3 years ago. I still love this WW app. Reading success stories along with helpful tips for every aspect of my journey has definitely been motivating. I still have yet to be able to link my fitness tracker but I don't mind entering it manually. Tracking with WW is just a start because you start to be able to know how many points food is without checking. Success is a sure thing with WW. GOOD LUCK if you trying this for the first time.

First time back on Weight Watchers and I'm not impressed. Maybe I'll get use to it in time but so many things are missing and the way the questions are framed, it leaves no possibility of change or physical limitations.
replyContent:
We do appreciate you reaching out and sharing your feedback. WW is working hard to improve the member experience. Your patience is appreciated.

--WW Customer Care--

content: I've been using the app fir 18 months without any problems. Suddenly every item I've ever tracked has disappeared. I've complained twice to WW i Australia but nothing has chaged. Very disappointing.

I love the app. I do online only and find the connect portion very motivating and encouraging. It took me a little bit of searching to figure out where to go to fully learn about the app but I couldve asked the 24/7 chat line and known sooner. Ive been using the app for 4 weeks and after years of yo yo dieting I feel Ive found something I can stick with for life. You eat the foods you love. The app makes weightloss feel like a game and the rewards portion is a game within a game. Im loving it!

Tried countless times to just get past the personal assessment section to sign in and have been kicked out of the process a dozen times because I apparently have a "slow connection". My internet connection, wifi and phone data, are perfectly fine. Really making it hard to want to use your app.
replyContent:
So sorry about that. Please log into the website, https://www.weightwatchers.com/us/, and login. Take the assessment there and then uninstall and reinstall the WW app. This should do the trick. Thanks for your patience.

--WW Customer Care--

content: So I left a review in 2020...here it is 2022 and the WW app still sucks!!!! Can't find food and the app doesn't automatically sync with my fitness tracker. For all the money Oprah has and the revenue WW makes you would think they would be able to make a better app. Their people need to call MyfitnessPal. For what you pay for the program they have a very poor app. It is very had to find the foods you want. Most days I give up and don't end up tracking. The recipe feature is nice though.
replyContent:
Thank you for reaching out and sharing your feedback. Our teams are always working to improve the member experience. Please fill this out, https://bit.ly/3hfCBs4, with your full device info and the issues that you are having. We are all wishing you success on your wellness journey.

--WW Customer Care--

content: At 1st I found the app a little overwhelming because I had no idea what I was doing but now that I have really dug into it, I find it extremely user friendly and unbelievably motivating

I wish WW would have more options for farming activities for your points. For example I have to hand till gardens, move bails of hay, rake out chicken coops and stalls for animals... Etc. Also to give more options of fresh veggies from gardens and meats. I use almost all my meat and veggies from my farm. We don't buy alot of things but can't find the items in your items for point count.
Not a fan of the new plan as doesn't work for a family all on different points and values very well. The old purple and blue plans worked better in our house with 3 of us on the plan.
replyContent:
We do understand how it is hard to adjust to something new, when the color plan was what was working and what you are used to. I can give you a few tips to get as close to the Purple or Blue plan as possible. Please reach us using 24/7 chat or call at 1-800-651-6000. Wishing you great success.

--WW Customer Care--

content: Easy to track my daily habits; I like the scan function while I shop; I often look for recipes, it's always in my pocket and handy!

I've used WW off and on for decades. The app is a great help and serious improvement. It could be better. My biggest complaint is with WW as a whole. The program is extremely ableist. There aren't any options for anyone with a type physical limitation.

Terrible. The older interface was better. This is so fancy and not really easy and quick to track. The best part of the app is the scanning feature, but adding that to your lig or saved items takes guessing. Fitness tracker is the worst. Overall just so not user friendly.
replyContent:
Thank you for reaching out and sharing your feedback. We have forwarded it to the proper teams for review. Our focus is to create tools that make it easier to build Healthy Habits. As we continue to improve our features, we will continue to ensure we’re creating an intuitive app experience accessible for our WW Family.

--WW Customer Care–

content: Great for weight loss! Uncomplicated and easy way to take weight off in a slow and safe speed, but with lasting results!
Can be slow also not as intuitive as it could be not easy to navigate but has good features overall

I'm very impressed with the recipes! They're easy, almost always from scratch and frequently use fresh herbs. I'm not a fan of the WW junk food ads so prominently displayed, since I'm trying to avoid desserts. Also the big gray banners are really annoying. They stay up much too long! Occasionally there is an obvious error in a recipe. I wish there was a way to notify WW.

This app makes it easy for me to plan and track points for WW. I love how I can add or edit recipes and the program calculated the points. It is also easy to correct entries so that my tracking is always accurate. WW is so easy now!
Sometimes are hard to find on the app such as food choices. Some need to be narrowed down and/or more choices without add-ons in the food choice selections when trying to track meals/food.
Love it for tracking weight and foods. Connect is a fab support system. Loving it.

Got to WW Gold this week (15/06/22) . As instructed by my Coach, I rang WW to update DD bank payments etc. Since the update on my WW Account, I've been unable to access the app - as it's "frozen"! Subsequently, rang WW Tech Support and following their advice, the app appeared to be working again. However, once I got off the phone to them, my WW app has frozen yet again!! No matter how many times I 'uninstall' / 'reinstall'. Arrrgh! Val
replyContent:
So sorry to hear of this. Please imstall the latest WW app update, and make sure you have installed your latest device software update. If hter eis still an issue, please fill this out, https://bit.ly/3hfCBs4. We are all wishing you success on your wellness journey.

--WW Customer Care

content: The app is great except I would like the option to manually enter my steps. Cannot get my watch to sync. Don't think we should be made to spend extra money on a fitness tracker.
replyContent:
Hi! You can certainly enter your steps manually. Please visit the activity section of the WW app by tapping on the three lines in the upper, left hand corner. Scroll down to activity and choose Dashboard. You will then see the Search option. Please call us at 1-800-651-6000 if you need furtner help.

--WW Customer Care--

content: Would give 0 stars but can't I had the app for a week or less and payed for a 6 month plan and asked for a refund because I never used the app and they cancelled my subscription with no refund utter waste of money especially since there are apps that work more effectively and they are free this app is a joke in my opinion

I subscribed to this app, first 3 months were free. Soon, I realized I was not using this app that much. So I contacted customer service and they said you will need a GP's recommendation letter to cancel subscription as I was in 9 months contract. Then, I provided them with the letter and now they are saying I will be charged for first free 3 months as well because I am cancelling the contract and this is in their terms. No one really reads terms and they are taking advantage of this. So cheap.

App is buggy. Randomly will connect to my garmin instinct 2 watch but is not accurately reading. Then when entering in meals, will suddenly delete them. Can't access WW through the app. Page will pop up but can't navigate. I like the recipe ideas and following other members but if I didn't have to pay for the program, this app would be deleted. I spent three days with customer support to try to fix some of this to no avail.
Love the app but my can't get the app to sync with my fitbit! Impossible to track activity levels.
Works perfect for me. Just a little expensive to buy the full version.

Tl;Dr Water and Sugar are behind a Paywall. Nuff said. Far to many paywalled features to justify being on the market. A pen and paper is more cost effective than this app unfortunately. Also it's product database is significantly outdated, try MyFitnessPall. I've used it for all of a day and it's already more feature full and accurate with nutritional information.
replyContent: Behind YAZIO there's a team that is working hard on developing the app further. The following link will provide you with more information on why we charge a fee for YAZIO PRO: https://help.yazio.com/hc/en-us/articles/360000592809 Kind regards, Your YAZIO-Team

content: 7 kg down in 5 weeks using this app. It makes it easier to stick to your calorie goals because there are fasting reminders, lots of foods uploaded by others, and a slick interface. I find this far better than MyFitnessPal
replyContent: Thank you for taking the time to write us your feedback! We're so happy that you enjoy using YAZIO and wish you all the best for your journey. If you have any problems or questions in the future, please contact our support team via request.yazio.com. Kind regards, Your YAZIO-Team

content: I have lost 10 kg with Yazio 2 years ago, but have put on 17 kg in lockdown. I did not renew my subscription, because in my humble opinion 'grosesse' or family planning in a weight loss app is not PC but pq. My sister was well over 100 kg when she started with Yazio a few weeks after my recommendation. She started to loose a few kilos, but then Covid and the war in Ukraine began and our Facebook correspondence was disrupted by aliens. Yazio is the best weight loss program I know.
perfect app for tracking calories and lowering your intake

I used to like this app more, it was the best calorie tracking app in my opinion. Maybe it still is, but now when I try to add a new food it asks useless information that cant even be skipped. Food category, who cares? Company who prduced it, again who cares? Salt, fat, carb content of the food is required, who the fu?!#@k cares? I JUST WANT TO TRACK CALORIES AND PROTEIN, I DONT NEED ANYTHING ELSE!

Can't seem to do anything without paying, and the prices are crazy - more than my WoW subscription or even what I paid for when I was on WW. I could do maybe 5 a month but the choices they have are way out of my justification range. Sad because the features seem like they'd be very interesting unlocked. Can't even sync with Fitbit or Garmin for steps and such, something that has always been a free feature on any other program I use
replyContent: We'll gladly offer you a free trial of our PRO version. Please contact our support team at: request.yazio.com, send us your user ID and our team will inform you. We appreciate your cooperation! Kind regards, Your YAZIO-Team

content: Entire section dedicated to fasting and other ways of inducing anorexia

UPDATED: the support team is great, so I put 4 stars. I still can work around the problem the long way. ORIGINAL: Hard to combine with individual food tracking course. content: Would be cool to be able to remove unnecessary (Intermittent Fasting) menus. Otherwise amazing. Thoughtful placement of icons, saving of previously used values, ... too much to list, great development work!
This app works well for tracking food intake and losing weight
It's exactly what I was looking for. The data base it's amazing

The only BIG problem is it is very hard to enter things manually as you can only use 100g or 100ml as the measurements. So it's easier just to search for something existing that's close. 125g/serving seems to be the most common on labels I have tried to enter so far. Extra disappointing because entering in accurate info helps the app as much as the user and its free data for the app. Maybe I have to pay them to make their app better.

You expect an app that bases everything on calories counting to be precise, but it's absolutely not (too often, >300% or <300% error). As so, this is money wasted. Cencelled subscription and strong encouraging for others to save money and not subscribe. Developers earn your money in an honest way. Period.
Love this app. I've tried others but this one is the best. Easy to navigate, great tips & recipes. I like the fact it has IF times.
Very bad app request money on any steps .and also not calculate calories truely it's fake app .

content: Bait and switch. The app description LITERALLY says no ads. Once past the 20 unskipable 1st-time user load screens, very clunky interface, not streamlined to use

A good app for calorie tracking, however the fact that fasts aren't customizable made me look for another app.
this app is amazing also thanks to its "sharing data" where all users can add "foods" and its calories making it very easy to keep track of your calie intake.

The free version is perfectly fine, I paid 40 eur to be able to sync it with my garmin. At the end it does sync, but not full amount of burnt calories per day, but only activities calories, which I consider useless. So the app works fine without paying for it, just a waste of money.
I like the app but I cannot upgrade to the pro version because the payment is not supported in China

content: Great app but constantly showing ads make eating single or small snacks really frustrating. It's one way to start losing weight... I like that there is a lifetime payment for $229 but that is a steep price for what is a very simple food tracker.

content: Used to be an awesome app, I also had pro for a year, but now, when I wanted to try it again, I had a huge surprise.. All the reports are just for Pro. You can just count calories and the three macro nutrients on the free version. Literally EVERY app on the store have the reports free, because the free users are creating the database for the pro ones. The reason I pay for an app is because I'm lazy enough to add all the food details, and the free users were doing that for me. Install other apps!

The pros. Broad product (calorie counting and intermittant fasting tracker), good range of third party connections (fitness trackers/apps) and great price (the pros). The cons. Intermittant fasting feature poorly programmed (no abiltiy to manually start / stop fasting and edit the fasting history and limited times available to select for fasting). Just poor sadly. Scanning of barcodes is slow an unreliable and in Australia the product database is poor (very low hit rate). MyNetDiary best I've seen so far for this (great scanner that uses phone light to help scan and super fast and has a great database for foods in Australia). But MyNetDiary is too expensive and doesn't have intermittant fasting feature at all. Can't find a good app to do Intermittant fasting and barcode scanning and product lookup and connection with Huawei Health :(

I'd gladly pay one year fee, and sign up without subscription. I do not feel comfortable signing up for yearly subscription. You and I know that I may forget to cancel subscription once I stop using the app in a year. Why taking advantage of that?

Absolutely love the app, the design is very attractive, everything is intuitive, and well explained. I strongly suggest to get the PRO version, as the recipes integrate perfectly well with the calorie counter. Improvement suggestion : I saved a lot of recipes, and I would like to have a way to classify them or sort them. For now the favourites recipes are just a "stack" of saved recipes.

Great app, but I was expecting more substantial feature updates over the past 9 months (only minor updates, and only to Intermittent Fasting), considering the monthly subscription. The fact that you can't input stuff offline, some GUI inputs and actions which are clunky, and most of all slow feature updates brings it to a 2 star rating for the subscription version.

I liked this app at first but switched to a different, BETTER app and realized that YAZIO doesn't track macros and calories like it should! And I hope you don't have to manually enter a new food item because the information it tells you like the calories are all wrong! The barcode scanner only works half the time so you have to try and find what item you need from searching through the data they have. Worst app if your in a caloric deficit because this will put you over your deficit in no time!!

Reset Doesn't Work. I purchased the subscription two days ago without realizing this. All info isn't reset as stated it would be. Looks like I'll again be searching for an app that will actually allow total reset as advertised. Cancelled my subscription.

Great product, although a couple complaints. 1. Please, make "Intermittent fasting" section available for offline use. That would be helpful if you are on plane or in remote areas without internet. 2. I can't edit saved foods.

content: Not useful at all. I just want to count calories, but the interface is so unnecessarily tiring and complicated. I can't imagine using this three times a day. Uninstalling.

Not very impressive app. I paid for a year of it but I regret doing so. Meal plans need to be more customized to the individual. The meal plan is the main reason I tried this app but It falls short of being very customizable or useful.

Used myfitnesspal before but since yazio has a better integration with intermittent fasting I made the switch. Barcode scanning is not as good u feel but the ease with which new products can be added makes up for it.

I love this and track everything i eat for more than a year now on the free version. It's changed my life. It also syncs easily with Google Fit so i know how to adjust my intake based on my exercise/activity. This app is amazing!

Pretty good app overall, however meal plans need to adjust automatically to the recommended calory intake because they are pretty useless otherwise. They were a huge reason for pro for me so i'm a bit disappointed. Still already a 4* because it is well put together and easy to use, but please implement this feature, it would be such a huge quality of life fix. I have seen this suggestion on the forums as well since mid 2020 so it's nothing new. 5* when this update comes.

Discouraging & time consuming. No refunds! No way to set KETO Macros, only adjust calorie goal. Manually enter every single food, as 50% of the time others who've scanned and saved didn't enter accurately. Paid for the PRO to get the scanning convenience. I should have just done CarbManager but that one took time too. Not hours trying to figure out whether they offer adjustments... And they don't. No way to add or scan data using food pics. Not completely useless, but very disappointing.

content: I looked in to clean fasting and downloaded a few apps. At first glance Yazio appealed the most. Used it for a month, only used the free basic features. This app may help some who need to track their behaviour but for me is a little pointless. I know when to eat, I know I've exercised and I know what I chose to eat! I learned a few things about fasting from the app

The free app won't do net carbs. And adding a food sucks. It makes you choose ounces and then you can't adjust it correctly. Like an ounce is 4 pieces. It will just add as 4 ounces? Oh well. All in all its a pretty good tracking app

The food tracking and recipes are great. Would be a 5 start rating but I feel the fasting option lacks flexibility. For example I practice 18:6 fasting through the week and a longer 36 hour fast over the weekend but there is no option to add custom times. If I'm wrong any guidance would be great and I'll swiftly update to 5 stars!

content: A lot of problems and bugs: unexpected delete of products from list when you just swiping without ability of restore and ability to find what is was deleted, Impossible to fix wrong entered data - no way, worst working with photo/images (Impossible take photo - photo just disappear), bad works with bar codes (incorrect code found).

The design is great (although it took me a while to adapt when it was changed a while back). The fasting timer (with presets) is excellent and very easy to use. Kudos to the developers and all users who diligently add new foods. Looking forward to what's to come.

It's ok. You can add your own recipes and food but there's only 4 meals to enter, i would prefer having an evening snack as well. Unfortunately activities are pre-set, there should be an option to modify burned calories etc. (You can enter custom activities but can't really use the existing activities on app)

content: Great app for intermittent fasting with a lot of flexibility for the different ratios. The normal tracking of calories is easy and accurate. It is a bonus that the exercise kcal is added to your profile automatically.

I love this app I used it while on my weight loss journey. I had hit a plateau and found this app. I started logging every single thing I put in my mouth and followed the calorie recommendations. I lost 1/2 a lb each day until I reached my goal of losing the last 15lbs. It really helped me change my lifestyle and realize where I was making mistakes.

Best calorie counter app ever I swear It's true. I've tried over 5 calorie tracking apps and paid for each one of then. Yazio is by far the best one on the market. Not only is the UI better than the rest, even their food database almast captures all food. There is room for new feautures, but I'm sure they are working in it.

Love all the different features this app has. I had loads of different apps for these things so love that it's all in one place! And the more time I spend on it, the more stuff I find. Would defo recommend if you like to keep track of different things.

The experience is very good and it has a variety of foods and drinks. However when I sync my samsung health app with yazio it doesn't sync nothing at all. Neither the steps. Overall 8/10 because of the sync method.

I love this app however It's ingredient management is awful. There's no way to manage ingredients in the shopping list. The possibility of an edit text option would be nice or even a stacked system that adds up ingredients from across multiple recipes. Also, its terrible at encouraging foodwaste! Am I ever going to buy 500g of quinoa to use 100? No, quinoa sucks. So tell me I'll never need quinoa again or let me have an overview of the whole weeks shopping list for the challenge.

Just a cheap Lose It! knockoff. Except this one only lets you count calories for free with a smaller, limited food library. Everything is pushing you to pay for a membership, but if you're going to do that, just buy a Lose It! membership because it is a lot better quality. I have been using them for years, just tried this for a promotion. This just feels gimicky and the UI is really outdated and cheap. Don't bother with this. It can't do as much as Lose It! And doesn't look as nice either.

content: It's a nice app so far. My only issue is that I've chosen lactose free for the Coach and there are a lot of recipes with cheese in them. I love cheese but it doesn't like me one bit. Oh, and the next 9 days have Savoury Muffins for breakfast 5 times, Spinach nests 3 times. Feedback link isn't working for me.

I'm using the pro version of the app, it's very good, but I wish you could customize the Coach feature by yourself. You can only choose recipes from the YAZIO database and "swap" them, while I would like to be able to choose my own recipes. Moreover, for some reason the Coach feature doesn't let you plan ahead your snacks (only breakfast, lunch, and dinner), which I would like to add too. I would appreciate it if YAZIO devs made this feature more flexible. Other than that, it's an amazing app!

A great app but it's a shame it's so expensive to unlock some of the features. I love that you can adjust the fasting times. Also, being able to record body measurements as well as weight is really helpful as this always shows your progress better than weigh-ins. Also, it's not too "naggy" .

Barcode recognizing is to low, sometimes it doesn't happen at all. But one thing I don't appreciate even more Is diary design, specifically nutrition tracker. I absolutely don't get why there are those 4 big squares size of my phone screen? Can you add settings to choose between like some different styles of diary view? I want a list of meals (I suppose once it was like this). Now it looks useful. I need to tap at a square to see my nutrition details.

Welp. Wanted to try this app, but the more advanced fasting options are premium only. It'd be cool to track calories and fasts all on one app, but I'm not gonna pay $35 for that option. Guess I'll just switch between two free apps instead.

content: So far, this app has been amazing and has really helped me with tracking my calories. However, as of this afternoon, it will not let me into the app. I've tried rebooting, I've tried reinstalling. Nothing works. It won't let me sign in either.

With the help of the app I lost 13 kilos and I keep losing. It is the best app to lose weight because you can eat whatever you want and the only limit is the calories you take. I had tried dietician and even if I lost weight, I believe that Yazio gives the most effortless and effective way to success. Also, if you pay for the pro program, there are recipes with little calories which are really good and there are fasting programs too! U would love it.

Anytime I look down at my phone after receive a text message sound only to find an advertisement from an app I installed, I uninstall it and rate that app very low... Push notifications ARE NOT for advertising!!!! Unacceptable!

I paid for the year subscription, $30, and so far its definitely been worth it. It teaches you about intermittent fasting, which is something I've been wanting to try out. The timer keeps me honest. The calorie tracker took me a few days to figure out, but I've got it down now! It also syncs with fitness apps so you can get an accurate count on calories you're burning. Oh, and there's recipes, which is a huge reason I paid for the subscription. I look forward to trying them! Great app!

Frustrating. Time Consuming. It's not easy to navigate or add new product for calorie counting. If you make a mistake and need to remove an item you have to figure it out. This may be good for ppl who nothing else to do in their life. Clearly I didn't join for the year. I gave this app a few days and seemed like I got no where. Not for ppl interested in maintenance or weight loss.

I think this a really great app to monitor and contol my calorie intake and improve the awareness of how much I eat. I have been able to lose weight since I started using this app - about 0.5-1.0 kg/week. There is a good chance that the weight loss will be sustainable thanks to the improved eating habit awareness. I recommended this app to my wife too and she was first hesitant but once she gave it a proper chance she is on the same track with me. I am using the basic free version.

The app in the beginning has no option to create account. Those who didn't check the account section will never know that there is such option within the app at a corner. If the app is deleted from phone, all your progress and data is lost. It's having indian food but major foods missing..! 🙄

I've been using the free version for sometime (and loving it). Have been ready to move on to paid subscription, when a friend who uses YAZIO on a similar phone (I've got Galaxy Note 9, she has galaxy S9) warned me that sync with Samsung Health hasn't been working at all for some time for her. Since being able to sync data from and to Samsung Health is the main reason I want to upgrade my plan, I've been obviously worried. Any comment on the issue from the developers, please?

content: Easy to use & keep track of your eating. Good choice of eating plans to suit your lifestyle. I bought the pro version as it's very affordable, I'm a very picky eater, it's going to take a while to go through all the recipes to ♡ the ones I'll eat & add my regular meals/recipes. Not hard, I'm just slow with technology.

It is simple to use, not overly complicated and it does all the calculations for you. Tried many other apps and were always frustrating, this one makes it easier for you to keep up with your diary and logging your exercises. Excellent, very satisfied.

One of the best fitness tracking app. I m used to My fitness pal. But this app has a lot to offer and I am past that. Love the fact that it integrates with Samsung health. I hope they integrate with Water Drink reminder app as well in the future.

Brilliant app! It will give us step by step to lose weight and allow you to choose method of ways to lose weight. Since last June (I lost the app when I reset my device last week and couldn't give accurate weight number so important to back up) I lost nearly 5 stone!

Works great. Takes a bit of time to learn to navigate the app. Surprised at the number of vegan recipes available. Some food were incorrectly inputted so I sent a report and also updated what I have. I wish you could update the info yourself. Also, I wish there was more flexibility with the intermitten fasting time. Overall, happy and hopeful it will help me achieve my weight loss goal.

I can recommend the app with the slight reservation that the burned calories per activity seem a bit implausible (for example calories per step taken are more in the range you'd expect for hiking rather than everyday walking). Unfortunately I can't find where I could adapt those values.

I'm using it to track my dietary supplements, it's pretty straight forward, and you can add your own foods (like your mom's recipe and stuff). I wish I could be more precise with the measurements (Adding Vitamin D in milligrams is pretty useless, for example) and that it accepted more nutrients (my supplement has a ton of vitamins and minerals, and it would be nice to track those. I wish I knew an app that could approximately the micronutrients content of my mom's recipe too...)

content: I really love how many options of food there are, I can always find the exact thing I've eaten on here and how much I had. The only thing I don't really like is the feature connecting the app with a step counter app like Google fit, it doesn't really seem to work properly and update my steps so I've started just adding them in manually. Aside from that it does all I need.
replyContent: Hi, Thank you for your feedback. Would you mind please getting in touch with our support team at: request.yazio.com, describing your issue in more detail, and sending screenshots? That way we can look into your problem further and try to help you find a solution. Kind regards, Your YAZIO-Team

content: When you search food it doesn't have as many options as I would like, such as restaurants. It might have one calorie count for something and the one below it is completely different. It's hard to know what's right or wrong. You can add them in but I don't want to do that every time so I feel like I am guessing. I wish it would have things set as peice or amount. It reminds you frequently to log info and encourages you which I like, and has a lot of meal options. The meal calorie count is nice.
replyContent: Hi Sarah, Thank you for your feedback. Would you mind please getting in touch with our support team at: request.yazio.com, describing your issue in more detail, and sending screenshots? That way we can look into your problem further and try to help you find a solution. Kind regards, Your YAZIO-Team

content: Great app. Its very precisely. Also a lof of avialable products. It helped me to lose weight and also realise how much "hidden" kcals we take in every day. My recommendation. Only defect is that you cannot pick two or more chalanges at the same time (for example 21 dan without chololade and no fast food) Not a big deal, definitly its not crucial thing in app, but here is an idea what you can improve with next update 🙂 )

I've been using this app for quite a few years and it is pretty decent. However, I was quite disappointed that the search option for one's own foods was removed; now one has to scroll endlessly until they find the food they are looking for. Furthermore, I would suggest adding a meal prep feature where one inputs the nutrition details for what one eats, but then the actual calories and stuff is only added to the daily counter once it has been eaten(a check off system).

Great app with tasty recipes. I wish I could plan the meals for a week and have unified groceries list. Now it is shown per dish so each meal = another round in the shop. I think it would be great for it to be grouped by vegetables, dairy etc instead

I m very disapointed. Very! I ve been using Lifesum for a long time and after a friend s recommendation I changed for Yazio (I use Polar Flow and the possibility to get data directly from Polar Flow was the main reason for the choice). But I got a surprise. Nor Jesus Christ can export the data from Polar App to Yazio!!! Steps, sports activities, nothing. To got the data I must import to Google Fit, and then to Yazio. Its not fair. I ll ask my money back.

content: Primarily downloaded to help with intermittent fasting. Worked great for two days. Then I suddenly ended up on a generic screen that had some of my personal info but the name field was blank. Could not move past this screen without deleting it which then took me to the login screen where I'm apparently now locked out. Asked for a password reset several times, contacted developer thru email 2 days ago with no response.They just took me $19.99. Have requested a refund from Google pay. Disappointed
replyContent:
Hi Janice,

content: This app is pretty good, it has a very extensive list of foods you can eat to get the calories, even many local foods only found in my country (south africa). Very impressed overall, and it is also useful if you want to gain weight like I did, as it gives a recommended amount of food and exercise per day. I'd give it a 9/10, only improvement I would like is a nicer ui.

It was good until I`ve decided to extend functionality and pay for subscription. I really regret about paying for full year :( Fasting functionality is so limited, especially usability of the component. No progress at all with this app, have to switch to another one even considering I've already paid for yazio :(

I love this app! This app has food tracker, recipe creator, sync with other fitness trackers, coaching tips, menu suggestions & analysis tools. Very cool! Oh and I really like the challenges! There are some bugs, but I use this app all day and there's nothing that stops me from using it. Also, I'd update a few of the features, but this is a superior tool for weight management and loss. I've used many of the competitor apps, I've been looking for a tool like this one!!

Doesn't show fiber in food, it worst and most of imporant thing to feel full when losing weight, and fiber is the key, but app doesn't show it even in Pro version, what I paid for. Very bad. My advice, add fiber : get better, reform, make program more useful.
replyContent:
