content: Easy to use, has lots of products to choose from, good overview of calorie intake, exercise output and remaining intake. So far happy with the free version although I'm getting flooded with popups and reminders which is not my thing!
replyContent:
Hi Adriana,
Thank you for your feedback.
You can disable the reminders when you go to Profile - Settings - Reminders.
Kind regards,
Your YAZIO-Team

content: SUBSCRIBERS BEWARE!! Very disappointing app. Overcharged me. Wouldn't refund the overcharge, said it was my problem with google, but they sure accepted money from google, calorie count on most foods is way off, barely syncs with fitbit, they have no real phone people to help with problems only email. I would definitely research other options!

Awesome and easy to use app that has helped me along the way to better eating. The fact that you can scan barcodes on the menu of items is fantastic. Love the recipe options and the variety is amazing! Thank you for creating such an awesome app!

Very functional good app, but I didn't like it because it's too precise. I just wanted to simply track my meals, but if it's not in a list, I need to register it with the calories etc. I don't think I can continue it so deleted the app immediately.

The best tracking App for food that I have found. ❤️ I have tried several but this one is my favorite. It has a pretty design. It finds the products I scan or write in by hand easily - not like others. I also like the options you can choose. Totally recommend if you are searching for an app to track your food. 👍🏻

So far, so good! Nice and easy to navigate. I really like the simple interface. Easy to find what you need. It has a wealth of food in its library when counting calories. And no annoying pop up videos!!
I like the app so far. It's user-friendly and love their reminders. It would be better though if there are a lot more recipes available that we could choose on their meal plan.

So far I'm really impressed with this app (only been on it a week). Logging meals, water is great & you're able to portion size it and transfer yesterdays meal onto the next day (unlike another that I used and have now left). I would however like to be able to put in under the water section, Coconut Water etc.

Quit working... Just kept spinning circles, and when it did work (only a few days)..it wasn't user friendly. Had to keep going back to see what I had already added, which was cumbersome, a big waste of time and money. Be warned...They dont let you have a free trial cause they know you wouldn't want to upgrade...so they sucker you with a low price. Then its to late... I tried to cancel the very same day I joined...then was refused a refund. All this to get 20$.... Scam artists!

This is such a wonderful app. I really like the interface and its user-friendliness. I was (and still am) pleasantly surprised at the food selection it has for you to upload. This part has made the experience more fun. I also really like the cute and friendly reminders; they keep you mindful and on your feet. Although you have to pay for extras, the free version still gives you all the basics that you need without feeling like you need more. Overall a great app! Well done😊.

I love this application. It makes everything so much easier. I like how it has many databases so in case you are cooking something that is Mediterranean or Mexican or whatever, you'll always find the ingredient in the database. When you purchase it, you can following a coach and this made my food planning way much easier. I would take a look on the recipes, write down the ingredients and go shopping for a week. This helped me finance better, save more food, and eat a variety of dishes everyday!!

The design is great and you're not bombed with advertisements. The only thing thats left to wish for in my opinion is there are only a few activity tracking apps you can connect to this app. Personally, I use MiFit and I can't connect the two. I'm still going to use it tho because the rest convinced me :)
replyContent:
Hi Talica,
Thank you for your feedback.
Unfortunately, we are not able to develop a connection for Mi Fit, because Xiaomi doesn't provide anything for developers (SDK or API). However, you should be able to connect through Google Fit.
Kind regards,
Your YAZIO-Team

content: Really user-friendly and easy to input food quickly. Had an issue with garmin Connect synchronization, but by resetting the connection on Garmin's website, it's now working properly. One suggestion: it would be great to be able to easily see from which foods specific nutrients come from when analyzing their trends in my diet, or offer suggestions for foods high in those deficient nutrients as is possible in the app Chronometer. This would be great actionable info for optimizing nutrient status

I've been using this for over a year now and really recommend it. Really helps to tracking calories with it's huge database of foods and stuff. And it syncs with Google Fit app, so you can see calories burned as well. Great job :)

I normally don't leave reviews but I actually had to this time. I'm an overweight teen trying to find a free meal planner and calorie counter app whereas this? It gives the impression it's free but you can access practically none of it. I'm vegetarian. You have to PAY to access that diet. How it has so many positive reviews, I really don't know.
replyContent:
Hi,
The basic version of YAZIO is completely free. Only if you would like to use the PRO features, you need to purchase an upgrade.
To understand the benefits of our PRO subscription, please refer to the information in this article: 
https://help.yazio.com/hc/articles/208847005
Kind regards, 
Your YAZIO-Team

content: The last two updates haven't really improved the app. I am no longer able to select food from a list of favourites or search the favourites. Some additions look helpful, but the app has become a chore to use...

Very good app, easy to use. A huge positive aspect is the lack of an avalanche of ads, like most apps do. One thing that could be improved, perhaps, is the accuracy of calories for the same types of foods, and measures (some use cups or ounces, when tablespoon would more appropriate, like for oats and cottage cheese). Overall, it's a nice app that can help with keeping the focus on the amount of food and water intaken, and activities done.

Great app overall, certainly one of the best in terms of convenience and visual appeal, some features are lackluster and some are locked behind a paywall. They are by no means crucial, some aren't even all that benefitial, but I'll still consider picking up pro since it's cheaper than most other paid subscription in similar apps
